{"type":"assistant","message":{"model":"claude-opus-4-6","id":"msg_bdrk_014VBsUVkRjFnwq7mMr2bMFp","type":"message","role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"tool_use","id":"toolu_bdrk_01Gs2sZ7sM1obFXB7z9iJXaM","name":"Task","input":{"description":"Create Spring Boot app + config","prompt":"I'm migrating a Jakarta EE DayTrader application to Spring Boot 3.2.5. Create the following files:\n\nBASE_DIR=/home/bmcginn/git/scarf-latest/scarbench-evals/final/prompt_claude__whole_applications__daytrader__jakarta__spring/run_3/output\n\n## 1. Create Spring Boot main application class\nFile: $BASE_DIR/src/main/java/com/ibm/websphere/samples/daytrader/DayTraderApplication.java\n\n```java\npackage com.ibm.websphere.samples.daytrader;\n\nimport org.springframework.boot.SpringApplication;\nimport org.springframework.boot.autoconfigure.SpringBootApplication;\nimport org.springframework.scheduling.annotation.EnableScheduling;\nimport org.springframework.boot.web.servlet.support.SpringBootServletInitializer;\n\n@SpringBootApplication\n@EnableScheduling\npublic class DayTraderApplication extends SpringBootServletInitializer {\n    public static void main(String[] args) {\n        SpringApplication.run(DayTraderApplication.class, args);\n    }\n}\n```\n\n## 2. Create application.properties\nFile: $BASE_DIR/src/main/resources/application.properties\n\n```properties\n# Server Configuration\nserver.port=8080\nserver.servlet.context-path=/daytrader\n\n# H2 Database Configuration\nspring.datasource.url=jdbc:h2:file:./data/tradedb;AUTO_SERVER=TRUE;DB_CLOSE_ON_EXIT=FALSE\nspring.datasource.driverClassName=org.h2.Driver\nspring.datasource.username=db_username\nspring.datasource.password=db_password\n\n# JPA Configuration\nspring.jpa.database-platform=org.hibernate.dialect.H2Dialect\nspring.jpa.hibernate.ddl-auto=update\nspring.jpa.show-sql=false\nspring.jpa.properties.hibernate.format_sql=true\nspring.jpa.defer-datasource-initialization=true\nspring.jpa.open-in-view=true\n\n# H2 Console (for debugging)\nspring.h2.console.enabled=true\nspring.h2.console.path=/h2-console\n\n# JSP Configuration\nspring.mvc.view.prefix=/WEB-INF/jsp/\nspring.mvc.view.suffix=.jsp\n\n# Jackson JSON\nspring.jackson.serialization.fail-on-empty-beans=false\n\n# Logging\nlogging.level.root=INFO\nlogging.level.com.ibm.websphere.samples.daytrader=DEBUG\nlogging.level.org.hibernate.SQL=WARN\n```\n\n## 3. Move/create JSP directory structure  \nThe app has JSP files currently in src/main/webapp/. For Spring Boot with embedded Tomcat, JSPs need to be in src/main/webapp/ (which is supported for WAR packaging), but since we use JAR packaging we'll keep them in src/main/webapp/ and the spring-boot-maven-plugin handles this. Actually, for Spring Boot JAR packaging, JSPs work in src/main/resources/META-INF/resources/ or we can use WAR packaging. Let me change the packaging to WAR.\n\nActually, the simplest approach for JSP support: change packaging to `war` in pom.xml. Edit the pom.xml to change packaging from jar to war.\n\nPlease create files 1 and 2 above, AND edit the pom.xml to change packaging from `jar` to `war`.","subagent_type":"general-purpose"}}],"stop_reason":"tool_use","stop_sequence":null,"usage":{"input_tokens":1,"cache_creation_input_tokens":420,"cache_read_input_tokens":112934,"cache_creation":{"ephemeral_5m_input_tokens":420,"ephemeral_1h_input_tokens":0},"output_tokens":2151},"context_management":null},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"40640270-7dba-44a6-9773-cfde29fa9f25","uuid":"6c7bfaff-3b01-45de-b0a5-bb83380eb841"}
{"type":"assistant","message":{"model":"claude-opus-4-6","id":"msg_bdrk_014VBsUVkRjFnwq7mMr2bMFp","type":"message","role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"tool_use","id":"toolu_bdrk_01PuqYzqos9DJZYQXBBnkswZ","name":"Task","input":{"description":"Migrate entity classes javax->jakarta","prompt":"I'm migrating a Jakarta EE app to Spring Boot 3.2.5. Spring Boot 3.x uses jakarta.* packages instead of javax.*.\n\nEdit the following entity files in /home/bmcginn/git/scarf-latest/scarbench-evals/final/prompt_claude__whole_applications__daytrader__jakarta__spring/run_3/output/src/main/java/com/ibm/websphere/samples/daytrader/entities/ to replace ALL javax.* imports with jakarta.* equivalents:\n\n1. AccountDataBean.java - Replace:\n   - javax.persistence.* -> jakarta.persistence.*\n   - javax.validation.* -> jakarta.validation.*\n   - javax.ejb.EJBException -> RuntimeException (since Spring Boot doesn't have EJB)\n   - The `throw new EJBException(error)` in the login method should become `throw new RuntimeException(error)`\n\n2. AccountProfileDataBean.java - Replace:\n   - javax.persistence.* -> jakarta.persistence.*\n   - javax.validation.* -> jakarta.validation.*\n\n3. HoldingDataBean.java - Replace:\n   - javax.persistence.* -> jakarta.persistence.*\n   - javax.validation.* -> jakarta.validation.*\n\n4. OrderDataBean.java - Replace:\n   - javax.persistence.* -> jakarta.persistence.*\n   - javax.validation.* -> jakarta.validation.*\n\n5. QuoteDataBean.java - Replace:\n   - javax.persistence.* -> jakarta.persistence.*\n   - javax.validation.* -> jakarta.validation.*\n\nFor each file, read it first, then use Edit to make the replacements. Make sure every javax. import is converted to jakarta. equivalent. Also remove any javax.ejb imports and replace EJBException with RuntimeException.","subagent_type":"general-purpose"}}],"stop_reason":"tool_use","stop_sequence":null,"usage":{"input_tokens":1,"cache_creation_input_tokens":420,"cache_read_input_tokens":112934,"cache_creation":{"ephemeral_5m_input_tokens":420,"ephemeral_1h_input_tokens":0},"output_tokens":2151},"context_management":null},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"40640270-7dba-44a6-9773-cfde29fa9f25","uuid":"3b4153e3-cd89-4695-a085-58328b1c0b97"}
{"type":"assistant","message":{"model":"claude-opus-4-6","id":"msg_bdrk_014VBsUVkRjFnwq7mMr2bMFp","type":"message","role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"tool_use","id":"toolu_bdrk_017FG5e6mbqzhrjqpxUgShjm","name":"Task","input":{"description":"Migrate utility classes","prompt":"I'm migrating a Jakarta EE app to Spring Boot 3.2.5. Edit the following utility files in /home/bmcginn/git/scarf-latest/scarbench-evals/final/prompt_claude__whole_applications__daytrader__jakarta__spring/run_3/output/src/main/java/com/ibm/websphere/samples/daytrader/\n\nFor each file, read it first, then make the necessary edits:\n\n1. util/Log.java - Read and if it has any javax.* imports, change to jakarta.*. This is just a logging utility so it probably just uses java.util.logging.\n\n2. util/FinancialUtils.java - Read and check for javax imports. Probably none needed.\n\n3. util/KeyBlock.java - Read and check for javax imports. Probably none needed.\n\n4. util/MDBStats.java - Read and check for javax imports.\n\n5. util/RecentQuotePriceChangeList.java - Read this file. It likely uses CDI annotations like @ApplicationScoped. Replace:\n   - javax.enterprise.context.ApplicationScoped -> org.springframework.stereotype.Component\n   - javax.inject.Inject -> org.springframework.beans.factory.annotation.Autowired\n   - Remove CDI-specific imports and add Spring equivalents\n\n6. util/TradeConfig.java - Read and check for javax imports. This is a configuration utility with static methods, so it shouldn't need many changes.\n\n7. util/TraceInterceptor.java - Read this file. It uses CDI interceptors. Replace with Spring AOP:\n   - Replace javax.interceptor.* with Spring AOP annotations\n   - Make it a @Component with @Aspect or just simplify to a logging component\n\n8. util/TradeRunTimeModeLiteral.java - Read this file. It uses CDI qualifier literal. Since we won't use CDI qualifiers in Spring, we can simplify or remove it. Keep the class but remove CDI dependencies.\n\n9. util/TimerStat.java - Read and check for javax imports.\n\n10. util/Diagnostics.java - Read and check for javax imports.\n\n11. beans/MarketSummaryDataBean.java - This uses javax.json.* (JSON-P). Replace with simple toString or Jackson. Remove javax.json imports and replace the toJSON() method with one that doesn't use javax.json (just return a simple map or string).\n\n12. beans/RunStatsDataBean.java - Read and check. Probably no javax imports.\n\nFor all files, read first, then edit. Replace javax.* -> jakarta.* where applicable, and remove/replace EE-specific annotations with Spring equivalents.","subagent_type":"general-purpose"}}],"stop_reason":"tool_use","stop_sequence":null,"usage":{"input_tokens":1,"cache_creation_input_tokens":420,"cache_read_input_tokens":112934,"cache_creation":{"ephemeral_5m_input_tokens":420,"ephemeral_1h_input_tokens":0},"output_tokens":2151},"context_management":null},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"40640270-7dba-44a6-9773-cfde29fa9f25","uuid":"96360a8a-39a4-46c1-a47c-bba88d3852e9"}
{"type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"type":"text","text":"I'm migrating a Jakarta EE DayTrader application to Spring Boot 3.2.5. Create the following files:\n\nBASE_DIR=/home/bmcginn/git/scarf-latest/scarbench-evals/final/prompt_claude__whole_applications__daytrader__jakarta__spring/run_3/output\n\n## 1. Create Spring Boot main application class\nFile: $BASE_DIR/src/main/java/com/ibm/websphere/samples/daytrader/DayTraderApplication.java\n\n```java\npackage com.ibm.websphere.samples.daytrader;\n\nimport org.springframework.boot.SpringApplication;\nimport org.springframework.boot.autoconfigure.SpringBootApplication;\nimport org.springframework.scheduling.annotation.EnableScheduling;\nimport org.springframework.boot.web.servlet.support.SpringBootServletInitializer;\n\n@SpringBootApplication\n@EnableScheduling\npublic class DayTraderApplication extends SpringBootServletInitializer {\n    public static void main(String[] args) {\n        SpringApplication.run(DayTraderApplication.class, args);\n    }\n}\n```\n\n## 2. Create application.properties\nFile: $BASE_DIR/src/main/resources/application.properties\n\n```properties\n# Server Configuration\nserver.port=8080\nserver.servlet.context-path=/daytrader\n\n# H2 Database Configuration\nspring.datasource.url=jdbc:h2:file:./data/tradedb;AUTO_SERVER=TRUE;DB_CLOSE_ON_EXIT=FALSE\nspring.datasource.driverClassName=org.h2.Driver\nspring.datasource.username=db_username\nspring.datasource.password=db_password\n\n# JPA Configuration\nspring.jpa.database-platform=org.hibernate.dialect.H2Dialect\nspring.jpa.hibernate.ddl-auto=update\nspring.jpa.show-sql=false\nspring.jpa.properties.hibernate.format_sql=true\nspring.jpa.defer-datasource-initialization=true\nspring.jpa.open-in-view=true\n\n# H2 Console (for debugging)\nspring.h2.console.enabled=true\nspring.h2.console.path=/h2-console\n\n# JSP Configuration\nspring.mvc.view.prefix=/WEB-INF/jsp/\nspring.mvc.view.suffix=.jsp\n\n# Jackson JSON\nspring.jackson.serialization.fail-on-empty-beans=false\n\n# Logging\nlogging.level.root=INFO\nlogging.level.com.ibm.websphere.samples.daytrader=DEBUG\nlogging.level.org.hibernate.SQL=WARN\n```\n\n## 3. Move/create JSP directory structure  \nThe app has JSP files currently in src/main/webapp/. For Spring Boot with embedded Tomcat, JSPs need to be in src/main/webapp/ (which is supported for WAR packaging), but since we use JAR packaging we'll keep them in src/main/webapp/ and the spring-boot-maven-plugin handles this. Actually, for Spring Boot JAR packaging, JSPs work in src/main/resources/META-INF/resources/ or we can use WAR packaging. Let me change the packaging to WAR.\n\nActually, the simplest approach for JSP support: change packaging to `war` in pom.xml. Edit the pom.xml to change packaging from jar to war.\n\nPlease create files 1 and 2 above, AND edit the pom.xml to change packaging from `jar` to `war`."}]},"parent_tool_use_id":"toolu_bdrk_01Gs2sZ7sM1obFXB7z9iJXaM","session_id":"40640270-7dba-44a6-9773-cfde29fa9f25","uuid":"28215413-76e4-4496-94e9-918d0c91a55e"}
{"type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"type":"text","text":"I'm migrating a Jakarta EE app to Spring Boot 3.2.5. Spring Boot 3.x uses jakarta.* packages instead of javax.*.\n\nEdit the following entity files in /home/bmcginn/git/scarf-latest/scarbench-evals/final/prompt_claude__whole_applications__daytrader__jakarta__spring/run_3/output/src/main/java/com/ibm/websphere/samples/daytrader/entities/ to replace ALL javax.* imports with jakarta.* equivalents:\n\n1. AccountDataBean.java - Replace:\n   - javax.persistence.* -> jakarta.persistence.*\n   - javax.validation.* -> jakarta.validation.*\n   - javax.ejb.EJBException -> RuntimeException (since Spring Boot doesn't have EJB)\n   - The `throw new EJBException(error)` in the login method should become `throw new RuntimeException(error)`\n\n2. AccountProfileDataBean.java - Replace:\n   - javax.persistence.* -> jakarta.persistence.*\n   - javax.validation.* -> jakarta.validation.*\n\n3. HoldingDataBean.java - Replace:\n   - javax.persistence.* -> jakarta.persistence.*\n   - javax.validation.* -> jakarta.validation.*\n\n4. OrderDataBean.java - Replace:\n   - javax.persistence.* -> jakarta.persistence.*\n   - javax.validation.* -> jakarta.validation.*\n\n5. QuoteDataBean.java - Replace:\n   - javax.persistence.* -> jakarta.persistence.*\n   - javax.validation.* -> jakarta.validation.*\n\nFor each file, read it first, then use Edit to make the replacements. Make sure every javax. import is converted to jakarta. equivalent. Also remove any javax.ejb imports and replace EJBException with RuntimeException."}]},"parent_tool_use_id":"toolu_bdrk_01PuqYzqos9DJZYQXBBnkswZ","session_id":"40640270-7dba-44a6-9773-cfde29fa9f25","uuid":"9dddc31b-3be7-499f-a193-da0c6d5012a7"}
{"type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"type":"text","text":"I'm migrating a Jakarta EE app to Spring Boot 3.2.5. Edit the following utility files in /home/bmcginn/git/scarf-latest/scarbench-evals/final/prompt_claude__whole_applications__daytrader__jakarta__spring/run_3/output/src/main/java/com/ibm/websphere/samples/daytrader/\n\nFor each file, read it first, then make the necessary edits:\n\n1. util/Log.java - Read and if it has any javax.* imports, change to jakarta.*. This is just a logging utility so it probably just uses java.util.logging.\n\n2. util/FinancialUtils.java - Read and check for javax imports. Probably none needed.\n\n3. util/KeyBlock.java - Read and check for javax imports. Probably none needed.\n\n4. util/MDBStats.java - Read and check for javax imports.\n\n5. util/RecentQuotePriceChangeList.java - Read this file. It likely uses CDI annotations like @ApplicationScoped. Replace:\n   - javax.enterprise.context.ApplicationScoped -> org.springframework.stereotype.Component\n   - javax.inject.Inject -> org.springframework.beans.factory.annotation.Autowired\n   - Remove CDI-specific imports and add Spring equivalents\n\n6. util/TradeConfig.java - Read and check for javax imports. This is a configuration utility with static methods, so it shouldn't need many changes.\n\n7. util/TraceInterceptor.java - Read this file. It uses CDI interceptors. Replace with Spring AOP:\n   - Replace javax.interceptor.* with Spring AOP annotations\n   - Make it a @Component with @Aspect or just simplify to a logging component\n\n8. util/TradeRunTimeModeLiteral.java - Read this file. It uses CDI qualifier literal. Since we won't use CDI qualifiers in Spring, we can simplify or remove it. Keep the class but remove CDI dependencies.\n\n9. util/TimerStat.java - Read and check for javax imports.\n\n10. util/Diagnostics.java - Read and check for javax imports.\n\n11. beans/MarketSummaryDataBean.java - This uses javax.json.* (JSON-P). Replace with simple toString or Jackson. Remove javax.json imports and replace the toJSON() method with one that doesn't use javax.json (just return a simple map or string).\n\n12. beans/RunStatsDataBean.java - Read and check. Probably no javax imports.\n\nFor all files, read first, then edit. Replace javax.* -> jakarta.* where applicable, and remove/replace EE-specific annotations with Spring equivalents."}]},"parent_tool_use_id":"toolu_bdrk_017FG5e6mbqzhrjqpxUgShjm","session_id":"40640270-7dba-44a6-9773-cfde29fa9f25","uuid":"8257ccf2-ca99-4179-8344-68eaa5f19111"}
