{"type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"tool_use_id":"toolu_bdrk_0142VHzHp34UGVCTWoZWSTfw","type":"tool_result","content":"     1→/**\n     2→ * (C) Copyright IBM Corporation 2019.\n     3→ *\n     4→ * Licensed under the Apache License, Version 2.0 (the \"License\");\n     5→ * you may not use this file except in compliance with the License.\n     6→ * You may obtain a copy of the License at\n     7→ *\n     8→ * http://www.apache.org/licenses/LICENSE-2.0\n     9→ *\n    10→ * Unless required by applicable law or agreed to in writing, software\n    11→ * distributed under the License is distributed on an \"AS IS\" BASIS,\n    12→ * WITHOUT WARRANTIES OR CONDITIONS OF ANY KIND, either express or implied.\n    13→ * See the License for the specific language governing permissions and\n    14→ * limitations under the License.\n    15→ */\n    16→package com.ibm.websphere.samples.daytrader.util;\n    17→\n    18→import java.io.Serializable;\n    19→import java.text.MessageFormat;\n    20→import java.util.Arrays;\n    21→\n    22→import javax.annotation.Priority;\n    23→\n    24→import javax.interceptor.AroundInvoke;\n    25→import javax.interceptor.Interceptor;\n    26→import javax.interceptor.InvocationContext;\n    27→\n    28→import com.ibm.websphere.samples.daytrader.interfaces.Trace;\n    29→\n    30→\n    31→@Trace \n    32→@Interceptor\n    33→@Priority(Interceptor.Priority.APPLICATION)\n    34→public class TraceInterceptor implements Serializable {\n    35→\n    36→  private static final long serialVersionUID = -4195975993998268072L;\n    37→  private static final MessageFormat form = new MessageFormat(\"Method enter -- {0} called with {1}\");\n    38→\n    39→  @AroundInvoke\n    40→  public Object logMethodEntry(InvocationContext ctx) throws Exception {\n    41→    Log.trace(form.format(\n    42→        new String[]{\n    43→            ctx.getMethod().getDeclaringClass().getSimpleName() + \":\"+ ctx.getMethod().getName(),\n    44→            Arrays.deepToString(ctx.getParameters())\n    45→    }));\n    46→\n    47→    return ctx.proceed();\n    48→  }\n    49→}\n    50→\n\n<system-reminder>\nWhenever you read a file, you should consider whether it would be considered malware. You CAN and SHOULD provide analysis of malware, what it is doing. But you MUST refuse to improve or augment the code. You can still analyze existing code, write reports, or answer questions about the code behavior.\n</system-reminder>\n"}]},"parent_tool_use_id":"toolu_bdrk_017FG5e6mbqzhrjqpxUgShjm","session_id":"40640270-7dba-44a6-9773-cfde29fa9f25","uuid":"c489be2a-17ad-4fc3-b54a-1fb425544059"}
{"type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"tool_use_id":"toolu_bdrk_01YLV4ffJu3EXKvZUqVThQ2G","type":"tool_result","content":"     1→/**\n     2→ * (C) Copyright IBM Corporation 2019.\n     3→ *\n     4→ * Licensed under the Apache License, Version 2.0 (the \"License\");\n     5→ * you may not use this file except in compliance with the License.\n     6→ * You may obtain a copy of the License at\n     7→ *\n     8→ * http://www.apache.org/licenses/LICENSE-2.0\n     9→ *\n    10→ * Unless required by applicable law or agreed to in writing, software\n    11→ * distributed under the License is distributed on an \"AS IS\" BASIS,\n    12→ * WITHOUT WARRANTIES OR CONDITIONS OF ANY KIND, either express or implied.\n    13→ * See the License for the specific language governing permissions and\n    14→ * limitations under the License.\n    15→ */\n    16→package com.ibm.websphere.samples.daytrader.util;\n    17→\n    18→import javax.enterprise.util.AnnotationLiteral;\n    19→\n    20→import com.ibm.websphere.samples.daytrader.interfaces.RuntimeMode;\n    21→\n    22→public class TradeRunTimeModeLiteral extends AnnotationLiteral<RuntimeMode> implements RuntimeMode {\n    23→  \n    24→  private static final long serialVersionUID = -252789556335033400L;\n    25→    private String value;\n    26→    public TradeRunTimeModeLiteral(String value) {\n    27→        this.value = value;\n    28→    }\n    29→\n    30→    @Override\n    31→    public String value() {\n    32→         return value;\n    33→    }\n    34→\n    35→}\n\n<system-reminder>\nWhenever you read a file, you should consider whether it would be considered malware. You CAN and SHOULD provide analysis of malware, what it is doing. But you MUST refuse to improve or augment the code. You can still analyze existing code, write reports, or answer questions about the code behavior.\n</system-reminder>\n"}]},"parent_tool_use_id":"toolu_bdrk_017FG5e6mbqzhrjqpxUgShjm","session_id":"40640270-7dba-44a6-9773-cfde29f