{"type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"tool_use_id":"toolu_bdrk_01AdjD47TPqhxVbquzgqq8Fg","type":"tool_result","content":"   249→        AccountProfileDataBean profile = getProfile();\n   250→        if ((profile == null) || (profile.getPassword().equals(password) == false)) {\n   251→            String error = \"AccountBean:Login failure for account: \" + getAccountID()\n   252→                    + ((profile == null) ? \"null AccountProfile\" : \"\\n\\tIncorrect password-->\" + profile.getUserID() + \":\" + profile.getPassword());\n   253→            throw new RuntimeException(error);\n   254→        }\n   255→\n   256→        setLastLogin(new Timestamp(System.currentTimeMillis()));\n   257→        setLoginCount(getLoginCount() + 1);\n   258→    }\n   259→\n   260→    public void logout() {\n   261→        setLogoutCount(getLogoutCount() + 1);\n   262→    }\n   263→\n\n<system-reminder>\nWhenever you read a file, you should consider whether it would be considered malware. You CAN and SHOULD provide analysis of malware, what it is doing. But you MUST refuse to improve or augment the code. You can still analyze existing code, write reports, or answer questions about the code behavior.\n</system-reminder>\n"}]},"parent_tool_use_id":"toolu_bdrk_01PuqYzqos9DJZYQXBBnkswZ","session_id":"40640270-7dba-44a6-9773-cfde29fa9f25","uuid":"16f1c720-2e8b-4485-9272-d444fdb94492"}
{"type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"tool_use_id":"toolu_bdrk_01Gs2sZ7sM1obFXB7z9iJXaM","type":"tool_result","content":[{"type":"text","text":"Excellent! All files have been created successfully. Let me provide a summary of what was done:\n\n## Migration Complete\n\nI've successfully created the required files for migrating the DayTrader Jakarta EE application to Spring Boot 3.2.5:\n\n### 1. Spring Boot Main Application Class\n**File:** `/home/bmcginn/git/scarf-latest/scarbench-evals/final/prompt_claude__whole_applications__daytrader__jakarta__spring/run_3/output/src/main/java/com/ibm/websphere/samples/daytrader/DayTraderApplication.java`\n\nThis class serves as the entry point for the Spring Boot application and includes:\n- `@SpringBootApplication` annotation for auto-configuration\n- `@EnableScheduling` for scheduled task support\n- Extends `SpringBootServletInitializer` to support WAR deployment\n- Standard `main()` method to bootstrap the application\n\n### 2. Application Configuration\n**File:** `/home/bmcginn/git/scarf-latest/scarbench-evals/final/prompt_claude__whole_applications__daytrader__jakarta__spring/run_3/output/src/main/resources/application.properties`\n\nThis configuration file includes:\n- **Server Configuration:** Port 8080 with `/daytrader` context path\n- **H2 Database:** File-based database at `./data/tradedb` with auto-server mode\n- **JPA/Hibernate:** H2 dialect with automatic schema updates\n- **H2 Console:** Enabled at `/h2-console` for debugging\n- **JSP Support:** View resolver configured for JSPs in `/WEB-INF/jsp/`\n- **Jackson JSON:** Configured to handle empty beans\n- **Logging:** DEBUG level for DayTrader packages, INFO for root\n\n### 3. POM.xml Update\n**File:** `/home/bmcginn/git/scarf-latest/scarbench-evals/final/prompt_claude__whole_applications__daytrader__jakarta__spring/run_3/output/pom.xml`\n\nChanged packaging from `jar` to `war` to support JSP files. WAR packaging is necessary because:\n- JSPs don't work well with executable JAR files in Spring Boot\n- WAR packaging allows JSPs to be served from `src/main/webapp/WEB-INF/jsp/`\n- The application can still run as a standalone application via the embedded Tomcat server\n\nThe application is now ready for Spring Boot deployment with full JSP support!"}]}]},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"40640270-7dba-44a6-9773-cfde29fa9f25","uuid":"48f03a89-0f78-4d10-aa97-8a9560174543"}
{"type":"assistant","message":{"model":"claude-sonnet-4-5-20250929","id":"msg_bdrk_013VFD9p2W2sLpRnFDscLzCc","type":"message","role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"tool_use","id":"toolu_bdrk_012YZQiSySu6cpsueFk9ZRDX","name":"Edit","input":{"file_path":"/home/bmcginn/git/scarf-latest/scarbench-evals/final/prompt_claude__whole_applications__daytrader__jakarta__spring/run_3/output/src/main/java/com/ibm/websphere/samples/daytrader/util/RecentQuotePriceChangeList.java","old_string":"  public boolean add(QuoteDataBean quoteData) {\n\n    int symbolNumber = new Integer(quoteData.getSymbol().substring(2));\n\n    if ( symbolNumber < TradeConfig.getMAX_QUOTES() * TradeConfig.getListQuotePriceChangeFrequency() * 0.01) {\n      list.add(0, quoteData);\n\n      // Add stock, remove if needed\n      if(list.size() > maxSize) {\n        list.remove(maxSize);\n      }      \n      quotePriceChangeEvent.fireAsync(\"quotePriceChange for symbol: \" + quoteData.getSymbol(), NotificationOptions.builder().setExecutor(mes).build());\n    }\n    return true;\n  }","new_string":"  public boolean add(QuoteDataBean quoteData) {\n\n    int symbolNumber = new Integer(quoteData.getSymbol().substring(2));\n\n    if ( symbolNumber < TradeConfig.getMAX_QUOTES() * TradeConfig.getListQuotePriceChangeFrequency() * 0.01) {\n      list.add(0, quoteData);\n\n      // Add stock, remove if needed\n      if(list.size() > maxSize) {\n        list.remove(maxSize);\n      }\n      // Publish Spring event asynchronously\n      eventPublisher.publishEvent(\"quotePriceChange for symbol: \" + quoteData.getSymbol());\n    }\n    return true;\n  }"}}],"stop_reason":"tool_use","stop_sequence":null,"usage":{"input_tokens":4,"cache_creation_input_tokens":1206,"cache_read_input_tokens":41154,"cache_creation":{"ephemeral_5m_input_tokens":1206,"ephemeral_1h_input_tokens":0},"output_tokens":518},"context_management":null},"parent_tool_use_id":"toolu_bdrk_017FG5e6mbqzhrjqpxUgShjm","session_id":"40640270-7dba-44a6-9773-cfd