{"type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"tool_use_id":"toolu_bdrk_01BAR2qbjUoibD9R6LAUpFvX","type":"tool_result","content":"     1→/**\n     2→ * (C) Copyright IBM Corporation 2019.\n     3→ *\n     4→ * Licensed under the Apache License, Version 2.0 (the \"License\");\n     5→ * you may not use this file except in compliance with the License.\n     6→ * You may obtain a copy of the License at\n     7→ *\n     8→ * http://www.apache.org/licenses/LICENSE-2.0\n     9→ *\n    10→ * Unless required by applicable law or agreed to in writing, software\n    11→ * distributed under the License is distributed on an \"AS IS\" BASIS,\n    12→ * WITHOUT WARRANTIES OR CONDITIONS OF ANY KIND, either express or implied.\n    13→ * See the License for the specific language governing permissions and\n    14→ * limitations under the License.\n    15→ */\n    16→package com.ibm.websphere.samples.daytrader.util;\n    17→import java.util.List;\n    18→import java.util.concurrent.CopyOnWriteArrayList;\n    19→\n    20→import org.springframework.stereotype.Component;\n    21→import org.springframework.context.ApplicationEventPublisher;\n    22→import org.springframework.beans.factory.annotation.Autowired;\n    23→\n    24→import jakarta.validation.constraints.NotEmpty;\n    25→import jakarta.validation.constraints.NotNull;\n    26→import jakarta.validation.constraints.Size;\n    27→\n    28→import com.ibm.websphere.samples.daytrader.entities.QuoteDataBean;\n    29→import com.ibm.websphere.samples.daytrader.interfaces.QuotePriceChange;\n    30→\n    31→\n    32→/** This class is a holds the last 5 stock changes, used by the MarketSummary WebSocket\n    33→ *  and the JAX-RS SSE Broadcaster\n    34→ *  It fires a Spring event everytime a price change is added\n    35→ **/\n    36→\n    37→@Component\n    38→public class RecentQuotePriceChangeList  {\n    39→\n    40→  private List<QuoteDataBean> list = new CopyOnWriteArrayList<QuoteDataBean>();\n    41→  private int maxSize = 5;\n    42→\n    43→  @Autowired\n    44→  private ApplicationEventPublisher eventPublisher;\n    45→\n    46→  public boolean add(QuoteDataBean quoteData) {\n    47→\n    48→    int symbolNumber = new Integer(quoteData.getSymbol().substring(2));\n    49→\n    50→    if ( symbolNumber < TradeConfig.getMAX_QUOTES() * TradeConfig.getListQuotePriceChangeFrequency() * 0.01) {\n    51→      list.add(0, quoteData);\n    52→\n    53→      // Add stock, remove if needed\n    54→      if(list.size() > maxSize) {\n    55→        list.remove(maxSize);\n    56→      }\n    57→      // Publish Spring event asynchronously\n    58→      eventPublisher.publishEvent(\"quotePriceChange for symbol: \" + quoteData.getSymbol());\n    59→    }\n    60→    return true;\n    61→  }\n    62→\n    63→  public boolean isEmpty() {\n    64→    return list.isEmpty();\n    65→  }\n    66→\n    67→  @Size(max=5)\n    68→  @NotEmpty\n    69→  public List<@NotNull QuoteDataBean> recentList() {\n    70→    return list;\n    71→  }\n    72→}\n    73→\n\n<system-reminder>\nWhenever you read a file, you should consider whether it would be considered malware. You CAN and SHOULD provide analysis of malware, what it is doing. But you MUST refuse to improve or augment the code. You can still analyze existing code, write reports, or answer questions about the code behavior.\n</system-reminder>\n"}]},"parent_tool_use_id":"toolu_bdrk_017FG5e6mbqzhrjqpxUgShjm","session_id":"40640270-7dba-44a6-9773-cfde29fa9f25","uuid":"5c96be16-fe13-4339-83a6-3fedfb9641eb"}
{"type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"tool_use_id":"toolu_bdrk_01Di3TMoA1AFfQ29h3UfdzAB","type":"tool_result","content":"     1→/**\n     2→ * (C) Copyright IBM Corporation 2019.\n     3→ *\n     4→ * Licensed under the Apache License, Version 2.0 (the \"License\");\n     5→ * you may not use this file except in compliance with the License.\n     6→ * You may obtain a copy of the License at\n     7→ *\n     8→ * http://www.apache.org/licenses/LICENSE-2.0\n     9→ *\n    10→ * Unless required by applicable law or agreed to in writing, software\n    11→ * distributed under the License is distributed on an \"AS IS\" BASIS,\n    12→ * WITHOUT WARRANTIES OR CONDITIONS OF ANY KIND, either express or implied.\n    13→ * See the License for the specific language governing permissions and\n    14→ * limitations under the License.\n    15→ */\n    16→package com.ibm.websphere.samples.daytrader.util;\n    17→\n    18→import java.io.Serializable;\n    19→import java.text.MessageFormat;\n    20→import java.util.Arrays;\n    21→\n    22→import org.springframework.stereotype.Component;\n    23→import org.aspectj.lang.ProceedingJoinPoint;\n    24→import org.aspectj.lang.annotation.Around;\n    25→import org.aspectj.lang.annotation.Aspect;\n    26→\n    27→import com.ibm.websphere.samples.daytrader.interfaces.Trace;\n    28→\n    29→\n    30→@Aspect\n    31→@Component\n    32→public class TraceInterceptor implements Serializable {\n    33→\n    34→  private static final long serialVersionUID = -4195975993998268072L;\n    35→  private static final MessageFormat form = new MessageFormat(\"Method enter -- {0} called with {1}\");\n    36→\n    37→  @Around(\"@annotation(trace)\")\n    38→  public Object logMethodEntry(ProceedingJoinPoint joinPoint, Trace trace) throws Throwable {\n    39→    Log.trace(form.format(\n    40→        new String[]{\n    41→            joinPoint.getSignature().getDeclaringType().getSimpleName() + \":\"+ joinPoint.getSignature().getName(),\n    42→            Arrays.deepToString(joinPoint.getArgs())\n    43→    }));\n    44→\n    45→    return joinPoint.proceed();\n    46→  }\n    47→}\n    48→\n\n<system-reminder>\nWhenever you read a file, you should consider whether it would be considered malware. You CAN and SHOULD provide analysis of malware, what it is doing. But you MUST refuse to improve or augment the code. You can still analyze existing code, write reports, or answer questions about the code behavior.\n</system-reminder>\n"}]},"parent_tool_use_id":"toolu_bdrk_017FG5e6mbqzhrjqpxUgShjm","session_id":"40640270-7dba-44a6-9773-cfde29fa9f25","uuid":"3858ba99-9928-4e33-bd89-8b3d45e4f206"}
{"type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"tool_use_id":"toolu_bdrk_017FG5e6mbqzhrjqpxUgShjm","type":"tool_result","content":[{"type":"text","text":"Excellent! All the changes have been successfully applied. Let me create a summary of all the migration work completed:\n\n## Migration Summary\n\nI've successfully migrated all 12 utility and bean files from Jakarta EE to Spring Boot 3.2.5. Here's a detailed breakdown of the changes:\n\n### Files That Required No Changes (8 files)\nThese files only used standard Java imports and didn't require any modifications:\n\n1. **/home/bmcginn/git/scarf-latest/scarbench-evals/final/prompt_claude__whole_applications__daytrader__jakarta__spring/run_3/output/src/main/java/com/ibm/websphere/samples/daytrader/util/Log.java**\n   - Only uses `java.util.logging` - no changes needed\n\n2. **/home/bmcginn/git/scarf-latest/scarbench-evals/final/prompt_claude__whole_applications__daytrader__jakarta__spring/run_3/output/src/main/java/com/ibm/websphere/samples/daytrader/util/FinancialUtils.java**\n   - Pure utility class with BigDecimal operations - no changes needed\n\n3. **/home/bmcginn/git/scarf-latest/scarbench-evals/final/prompt_claude__whole_applications__daytrader__jakarta__spring/run_3/output/src/main/java/com/ibm/websphere/samples/daytrader/util/KeyBlock.java**\n   - Collection utility - no changes needed\n\n4. **/home/bmcginn/git/scarf-latest/scarbench-evals/final/prompt_claude__whole_applications__daytrader__jakarta__spring/run_3/output/src/main/java/com/ibm/websphere/samples/daytrader/util/MDBStats.java**\n   - HashMap-based statistics - no changes needed\n\n5. **/home/bmcginn/git/scarf-latest/scarbench-evals/final/prompt_claude__whole_applications__daytrader__jakarta__spring/run_3/output/src/main/java/com/ibm/websphere/samples/daytrader/util/TradeConfig.java**\n   - Static configuration utility - no changes needed\n\n6. **/home/bmcginn/git/scarf-latest/scarbench-evals/final/prompt_claude__whole_applications__daytrader__jakarta__spring/run_3/output/src/main/java/com/ibm/websphere/samples/daytrader/util/TimerStat.java**\n   - POJO with timing statistics - no changes needed\n\n7. **/home/bmcginn/git/scarf-latest/scarbench-evals/final/prompt_claude__whole_applications__daytrader__jakarta__spring/run_3/output/src/main/java/com/ibm/websphere/samples/daytrader/util/Diagnostics.java**\n   - Diagnostic utility - no changes needed\n\n8. **/home/bmcginn/git/scarf-latest/scarbench-evals/final/prompt_claude__whole_applications__daytrader__jakarta__spring/run_3/output/src/main/java/com/ibm/websphere/samples/daytrader/beans/RunStatsDataBean.java**\n   - Simple data bean - no changes needed\n\n### Files Modified (4 files)\n\n#### 1. RecentQuotePriceChangeList.java\n**Changes:**\n- Replaced `@ApplicationScoped` with `@Component` (CDI → Spring)\n- Replaced `@Inject` with `@Autowired` (CDI → Spring)\n- Removed `@Resource` for ManagedExecutorService\n- Replaced CDI `Event<String>` with Spring `ApplicationEventPublisher`\n- Changed `quotePriceChangeEvent.fireAsync()` to `eventPublisher.publishEvent()`\n- Changed validation imports from `javax.validation.*` to `jakarta.validation.*`\n- Updated comments to reflect Spring usage\n\n**Key replacements:**\n- `javax.enterprise.context.ApplicationScoped` → `org.springframework.stereotype.Component`\n- `javax.inject.Inject` → `org.springframework.beans.factory.annotation.Autowired`\n- `javax.validation.*` → `jakarta.validation.*`\n\n#### 2. TraceInterceptor.java\n**Changes:**\n- Replaced CDI interceptor with Spring AOP\n- Replaced `@Interceptor` and `@Priority` with `@Aspect` and `@Component`\n- Changed `@AroundInvoke` to `@Around(\"@annotation(trace)\")`\n- Replaced `InvocationContext` with Spring AOP's `ProceedingJoinPoint`\n- Updated method signature to use AOP join point API\n\n**Key replacements:**\n- `javax.interceptor.*` → Spring AOP (`org.aspectj.lang.*`)\n- `@Interceptor` → `@Aspect` + `@Component`\n- `@AroundInvoke` → `@Around`\n\n#### 3. TradeRunTimeModeLiteral.java\n**Changes:**\n- Removed CDI `AnnotationLiteral` extension\n- Simplified to a plain Java class that implements `RuntimeMode`\n- Removed `javax.enterprise.util.AnnotationLiteral` import\n- Added documentation explaining the simplification\n\n**Key replacements:**\n- Removed CDI-specific `AnnotationLiteral` parent class\n- Kept interface implementation for compatibility\n\n#### 4. MarketSummaryDataBean.java\n**Changes:**\n- Removed JSON-P (javax.json) dependencies\n- Replaced `JsonObject` return type with `Map<String, Object>`\n- Replaced `Json.createObjectBuilder()` with `LinkedHashMap<>`\n- Changed `.add()` calls to `.put()` calls\n- Added imports for `LinkedHashMap` and `Map`\n\n**Key replacements:**\n- `javax.json.Json` → `java.util.LinkedHashMap`\n- `javax.json.JsonObject` → `java.util.Map<String, Object>`\n- `javax.json.JsonObjectBuilder` → removed\n\n### Summary of Patterns Applied\n\n1. **CDI to Spring Dependency Injection:**\n   - `@ApplicationScoped` → `@Component`\n   - `@Inject` → `@Autowired`\n\n2. **CDI Events to Spring Events:**\n   - `Event<T>` → `ApplicationEventPublisher`\n   - `fireAsync()` → `publishEvent()`\n\n3. **CDI Interceptors to Spring AOP:**\n   - `@Interceptor` → `@Aspect` + `@Component`\n   - `@AroundInvoke` → `@Around`\n   - `InvocationContext` → `ProceedingJoinPoint`\n\n4. **Validation API:**\n   - `javax.validation.*` → `jakarta.validation.*`\n\n5. **JSON Processing:**\n   - Removed JSON-P (javax.json) in favor of standard Java collections\n   - Return types changed to `Map<String, Object>` for JSON serialization\n\nAll files have been successfully migrated and are now compatible with Spring Boot 3.2.5!"}]}]},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"40640270-7dba-44a6-9773-cfde29fa9f25","uuid":"0d057576-8754-4f5d-be59-1ed83936fe62"}
{"type":"assistant","message":{"model":"claude-opus-4-6","id":"msg_bdrk_01UTiW3vpRYgi71ENTiRowck","type":"message","role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"text","text":"Good progress. Now let me migrate the core service classes - the interfaces, EJB implementations, and JAX-RS endpoints:"}],"stop_reason":"tool_use","stop_sequence":null,"usage":{"input_tokens":1,"cache_creation_input_tokens":5650,"cache_read_input_tokens":113354,"cache_creation":{"ephemeral_5m_input_tokens":5650,"ephemeral_1h_input_tokens":0},"output_tokens":1763},"context_management":null},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"40640270-7dba-44a6-9773-cfde29fa9f25","uuid":"1410db00-7d43-4744-9040-55ad9659392f"}
{"type":"assistant","message":{"model":"claude-opus-4-6","id":"msg_bdrk_01UTiW3vpRYgi71ENTiRowck","type":"message","role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"tool_use","id":"toolu_bdrk_01EeSZucn9yTiTByaKPqsLrJ","name":"Task","input":{"description":"Migrate interfaces and qualifiers","prompt":"I'm migrating a Jakarta EE DayTrader app to Spring Boot 3.2.5. Edit the following interface files in /home/bmcginn/git/scarf-latest/scarbench-evals/final/prompt_claude__whole_applications__daytrader__jakarta__spring/run_3/output/src/main/java/com/ibm/websphere/samples/daytrader/interfaces/\n\nFor each file, read it first, then make necessary edits:\n\n1. TradeServices.java - This is a plain interface with no javax imports. Verify and leave as is.\n\n2. TradeEJB.java - This is a CDI qualifier annotation. Read it and simplify - it uses javax.inject.Qualifier and javax.enterprise.util.Nonbinding. Since Spring doesn't use CDI qualifiers, convert it to a simple Spring annotation or marker. Replace with:\n   - Keep it as a custom annotation but remove CDI imports\n   - Change javax.inject.Qualifier to org.springframework.beans.factory.annotation.Qualifier\n   - Remove @InterceptorBinding if present\n\n3. TradeJDBC.java - Same as TradeEJB.java - it's a CDI qualifier. Convert similarly.\n\n4. TradeSession2Direct.java - Same pattern - CDI qualifier. Convert similarly.\n\n5. TradeDB.java - Read and check what it is. Convert CDI to Spring if needed.\n\n6. Trace.java - This is an interceptor binding annotation. Since we're using Spring AOP, convert to a simple annotation (no CDI @InterceptorBinding). Keep it as:\n```java\npackage com.ibm.websphere.samples.daytrader.interfaces;\nimport java.lang.annotation.*;\n@Target({ElementType.METHOD, ElementType.TYPE})\n@Retention(RetentionPolicy.RUNTIME)\npublic @interface Trace {\n}\n```\n\n7. RuntimeMode.java - CDI qualifier for runtime mode. Convert to a simple annotation with a String value.\n\n8. MarketSummaryUpdate.java - CDI qualifier. Convert to a simple annotation.\n\n9. QuotePriceChange.java - CDI qualifier. Convert to a simple annotation.\n\nFor all CDI qualifier annotations, the pattern is: remove javax.inject.Qualifier, javax.enterprise.inject.*, etc. and make them plain Java annotations with @Target, @Retention. Keep them usable as markers.","subagent_type":"general-purpose"}}],"stop_reason":"tool_use","stop_sequence":null,"usage":{"input_tokens":1,"cache_creation_input_tokens":5650,"cache_read_input_tokens":113354,"cache_creation":{"ephemeral_5m_input_tokens":5650,"ephemeral_1h_input_tokens":0},"output_tokens":1763},"context_management":null},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"40640270-7dba-44a6-9773-cfde29fa9f25","uuid":"f347d146-0f5b-4ad4-9a9e-d932bb7a3ba1"}
{"type":"assistant","message":{"model":"claude-opus-4-6","id":"msg_bdrk_01UTiW3vpRYgi71ENTiRowck","type":"message","role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"tool_use","id":"toolu_bdrk_01KzDwRdzp8WCzQcWTAk4Fum","name":"Task","input":{"description":"Migrate EJB TradeSLSBBean to Spring","prompt":"I'm migrating the DayTrader Jakarta EE app to Spring Boot 3.2.5. The most critical migration is converting the EJB stateless session bean TradeSLSBBean to a Spring @Service.\n\nRead the file at: /home/bmcginn/git/scarf-latest/scarbench-evals/final/prompt_claude__whole_applications__daytrader__jakarta__spring/run_3/output/src/main/java/com/ibm/websphere/samples/daytrader/impl/ejb3/TradeSLSBBean.java\n\nThen REWRITE it completely to be a Spring Boot @Service class. The key changes needed:\n\n1. Replace @Stateless with @Service\n2. Replace @TransactionAttribute/@TransactionManagement with @Transactional from Spring\n3. Replace @PersistenceContext with @Autowired or @PersistenceContext from jakarta.persistence\n4. Remove all JMS-related code (no JMS broker in Spring Boot) - for the queueOrder method, just call completeOrder directly\n5. Replace @EJB with @Autowired\n6. Replace @Inject with @Autowired\n7. Replace @Resource with @Autowired\n8. Replace javax.ejb.EJBException with RuntimeException\n9. Replace javax.* imports with jakarta.* where applicable (javax.persistence -> jakarta.persistence, etc)\n10. Remove SessionContext - not needed in Spring\n11. Keep @TradeEJB and @RuntimeMode annotations (they're now plain markers)\n12. For the Trace interceptor, just keep the @Trace annotation\n13. For async order completion, use @Async from Spring instead of ManagedExecutorService\n14. Replace javax.validation with jakarta.validation\n15. Remove javax.jms imports entirely\n16. The publishQuotePriceChange method should be simplified - just log it instead of JMS\n17. For the completeOrderAsync method, just call completeOrder synchronously for simplicity (or use Spring @Async)\n18. Replace javax.transaction.RollbackException with just Exception in the login method\n\nWrite the complete new file content. Make it a proper Spring @Service with @Transactional.","subagent_type":"general-purpose"}}],"stop_reason":"tool_use","stop_sequence":null,"usage":{"input_tokens":1,"cache_creation_input_tokens":5650,"cache_read_input_tokens":113354,"cache_creation":{"ephemeral_5m_input_tokens":5650,"ephemeral_1h_input_tokens":0},"output_tokens":1763},"context_management":null},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"40640270-7dba-44a6-9773-cfde29fa9f25","uuid":"ea7dddc3-c3b7-4b6b-bebb-7768c136b3b4"}
{"type":"assistant","message":{"model":"claude-opus-4-6","id":"msg_bdrk_01UTiW3vpRYgi71ENTiRowck","type":"message","role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"tool_use","id":"toolu_bdrk_017uhPsrHKo3A3VHJj1hPuNv","name":"Task","input":{"description":"Migrate MarketSummarySingleton to Spring","prompt":"I'm migrating the DayTrader Jakarta EE app to Spring Boot 3.2.5. Convert the MarketSummarySingleton EJB to a Spring component.\n\nRead the file at: /home/bmcginn/git/scarf-latest/scarbench-evals/final/prompt_claude__whole_applications__daytrader__jakarta__spring/run_3/output/src/main/java/com/ibm/websphere/samples/daytrader/impl/ejb3/MarketSummarySingleton.java\n\nThen rewrite it as a Spring component:\n\n1. Replace @Singleton with @Component\n2. Replace @Schedule with @Scheduled from Spring (use fixedRate = 20000 for 20 seconds)\n3. Replace @PersistenceContext with injection (keep @PersistenceContext from jakarta.persistence)\n4. Replace @Lock(READ/WRITE) with synchronized or ReentrantReadWriteLock\n5. Replace CDI Event with Spring's ApplicationEventPublisher\n6. Replace @Resource ManagedExecutorService - not needed in Spring (scheduling is handled by Spring)\n7. Replace @Inject with @Autowired\n8. Replace javax.* with jakarta.* (javax.persistence -> jakarta.persistence, etc.)\n9. Remove javax.enterprise.* imports\n10. Remove javax.ejb.* imports\n11. Remove javax.json.* if present\n12. Remove javax.annotation.Resource and replace with Spring equivalents\n13. Add @Transactional(readOnly = true) for the updateMarketSummary method since it reads from DB\n14. Keep the MarketSummaryDataBean caching logic\n\nThe method signatures should stay the same. Write the complete new file.","subagent_type":"general-purpose"}}],"stop_reason":"tool_use","stop_sequence":null,"usage":{"input_tokens":1,"cache_creation_input_tokens":5650,"cache_read_input_tokens":113354,"cache_creation":{"ephemeral_5m_input_tokens":5650,"ephemeral_1h_input_tokens":0},"output_tokens":1763},"context_management":null},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"40640270-7dba-44a6-9773-cfde29fa9f25","uuid":"4d437c1d-be17-4d40-bbfd-d43010ccc757"}
{"type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"type":"text","text":"I'm migrating a Jakarta EE DayTrader app to Spring Boot 3.2.5. Edit the following interface files in /home/bmcginn/git/scarf-latest/scarbench-evals/final/prompt_claude__whole_applications__daytrader__jakarta__spring/run_3/output/src/main/java/com/ibm/websphere/samples/daytrader/interfaces/\n\nFor each file, read it first, then make necessary edits:\n\n1. TradeServices.java - This is a plain interface with no javax imports. Verify and leave as is.\n\n2. TradeEJB.java - This is a CDI qualifier annotation. Read it and simplify - it uses javax.inject.Qualifier and javax.enterprise.util.Nonbinding. Since Spring doesn't use CDI qualifiers, convert it to a simple Spring annotation or marker. Replace with:\n   - Keep it as a custom annotation but remove CDI imports\n   - Change javax.inject.Qualifier to org.springframework.beans.factory.annotation.Qualifier\n   - Remove @InterceptorBinding if present\n\n3. TradeJDBC.java - Same as TradeEJB.java - it's a CDI qualifier. Convert similarly.\n\n4. TradeSession2Direct.java - Same pattern - CDI qualifier. Convert similarly.\n\n5. TradeDB.java - Read and check what it is. Convert CDI to Spring if needed.\n\n6. Trace.java - This is an interceptor binding annotation. Since we're using Spring AOP, convert to a simple annotation (no CDI @InterceptorBinding). Keep it as:\n```java\npackage com.ibm.websphere.samples.daytrader.interfaces;\nimport java.lang.annotation.*;\n@Target({ElementType.METHOD, ElementType.TYPE})\n@Retention(RetentionPolicy.RUNTIME)\npublic @interface Trace {\n}\n```\n\n7. RuntimeMode.java - CDI qualifier for runtime mode. Convert to a simple annotation with a String value.\n\n8. MarketSummaryUpdate.java - CDI qualifier. Convert to a simple annotation.\n\n9. QuotePriceChange.java - CDI qualifier. Convert to a simple annotation.\n\nFor all CDI qualifier annotations, the pattern is: remove javax.inject.Qualifier, javax.enterprise.inject.*, etc. and make them plain Java annotations with @Target, @Retention. Keep them usable as markers."}]},"parent_tool_use_id":"toolu_bdrk_01EeSZucn9yTiTByaKPqsLrJ","session_id":"40640270-7dba-44a6-9773-cfde29fa9f25","uuid":"fa52260b-a481-4fab-92f4-76341f3b856c"}
{"type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"type":"text","text":"I'm migrating the DayTrader Jakarta EE app to Spring Boot 3.2.5. The most critical migration is converting the EJB stateless session bean TradeSLSBBean to a Spring @Service.\n\nRead the file at: /home/bmcginn/git/scarf-latest/scarbench-evals/final/prompt_claude__whole_applications__daytrader__jakarta__spring/run_3/output/src/main/java/com/ibm/websphere/samples/daytrader/impl/ejb3/TradeSLSBBean.java\n\nThen REWRITE it completely to be a Spring Boot @Service class. The key changes needed:\n\n1. Replace @Stateless with @Service\n2. Replace @TransactionAttribute/@TransactionManagement with @Transactional from Spring\n3. Replace @PersistenceContext with @Autowired or @PersistenceContext from jakarta.persistence\n4. Remove all JMS-related code (no JMS broker in Spring Boot) - for the queueOrder method, just call completeOrder directly\n5. Replace @EJB with @Autowired\n6. Replace @Inject with @Autowired\n7. Replace @Resource with @Autowired\n8. Replace javax.ejb.EJBException with RuntimeException\n9. Replace javax.* imports with jakarta.* where applicable (javax.persistence -> jakarta.persistence, etc)\n10. Remove SessionContext - not needed in Spring\n11. Keep @TradeEJB and @RuntimeMode annotations (they're now plain markers)\n12. For the Trace interceptor, just keep the @Trace annotation\n13. For async order completion, use @Async from Spring instead of ManagedExecutorService\n14. Replace javax.validation with jakarta.validation\n15. Remove javax.jms imports entirely\n16. The publishQuotePriceChange method should be simplified - just log it instead of JMS\n17. For the completeOrderAsync method, just call completeOrder synchronously for simplicity (or use Spring @Async)\n18. Replace javax.transaction.RollbackException with just Exception in the login method\n\nWrite the complete new file content. Make it a proper Spring @Service with @Transactional."}]},"parent_tool_use_id":"toolu_bdrk_01KzDwRdzp8WCzQcWTAk4Fum","session_id":"40640270-7dba-44a6-9773-cfde29fa9f25","uuid":"2aba3a88-1a4f-4733-9aa1-388cc4ba1b7a"}
{"type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"type":"text","text":"I'm migrating the DayTrader Jakarta EE app to Spring Boot 3.2.5. Convert the MarketSummarySingleton EJB to a Spring component.\n\nRead the file at: /home/bmcginn/git/scarf-latest/scarbench-evals/final/prompt_claude__whole_applications__daytrader__jakarta__spring/run_3/output/src/main/java/com/ibm/websphere/samples/daytrader/impl/ejb3/MarketSummarySingleton.java\n\nThen rewrite it as a Spring component:\n\n1. Replace @Singleton with @Component\n2. Replace @Schedule with @Scheduled from Spring (use fixedRate = 20000 for 20 seconds)\n3. Replace @PersistenceContext with injection (keep @PersistenceContext from jakarta.persistence)\n4. Replace @Lock(READ/WRITE) with synchronized or ReentrantReadWriteLock\n5. Replace CDI Event with Spring's ApplicationEventPublisher\n6. Replace @Resource ManagedExecutorService - not needed in Spring (scheduling is handled by Spring)\n7. Replace @Inject with @Autowired\n8. Replace javax.* with jakarta.* (javax.persistence -> jakarta.persistence, etc.)\n9. Remove javax.enterprise.* imports\n10. Remove javax.ejb.* imports\n11. Remove javax.json.* if present\n12. Remove javax.annotation.Resource and replace with Spring equivalents\n13. Add @Transactional(readOnly = true) for the updateMarketSummary method since it reads from DB\n14. Keep the MarketSummaryDataBean caching logic\n\nThe method signatures should stay the same. Write the complete new file."}]},"parent_tool_use_id":"toolu_bdrk_017uhPsrHKo3A3VHJj1hPuNv","session_id":"40640270-7dba-44a6-9773-cfde29fa9f25","uuid":"945c0b2c-9c6b-493f-a249-b877557ca95a"}
