{"type":"assistant","message":{"model":"claude-opus-4-6","id":"msg_bdrk_01SXGM8ydCDggSQ8DkUevu7c","type":"message","role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"tool_use","id":"toolu_bdrk_01GU47pNQoS8nHQfwvNhau6s","name":"Task","input":{"description":"Migrate remaining EJB3 impl classes","prompt":"I'm migrating a Jakarta EE DayTrader app to Spring Boot 3.2.5. Migrate the remaining EJB3 implementation classes.\n\nBASE=/home/bmcginn/git/scarf-latest/scarbench-evals/final/prompt_claude__whole_applications__daytrader__jakarta__spring/run_3/output\n\nRead and edit each of these files:\n\n1. $BASE/src/main/java/com/ibm/websphere/samples/daytrader/impl/ejb3/AsyncScheduledOrderSubmitter.java\n   - This uses @Dependent, ManagedExecutorService, @Resource. Convert to Spring:\n   - Replace @Dependent with @Component\n   - Replace @Resource ManagedExecutorService with @Autowired TaskExecutor or just use Spring's @Async\n   - Replace javax.* imports with jakarta.* or Spring equivalents\n   - Keep it simple - use a ThreadPoolTaskExecutor or just submit to a simple executor\n\n2. $BASE/src/main/java/com/ibm/websphere/samples/daytrader/impl/ejb3/AsyncScheduledOrder.java\n   - This is a Runnable that calls TradeSLSBBean.completeOrder(). \n   - Remove javax.ejb.* imports\n   - Replace EJBException with RuntimeException\n   - Keep it as a plain Runnable class\n\n3. $BASE/src/main/java/com/ibm/websphere/samples/daytrader/impl/session2direct/DirectSLSBBean.java\n   - This is a @Stateless EJB that wraps TradeDirect. Convert:\n   - Replace @Stateless with @Service\n   - Replace @Inject/@EJB with @Autowired\n   - Replace javax.* with jakarta.* or Spring equivalents\n   - Replace EJBException with RuntimeException\n   - This class delegates to TradeDirect for all operations\n\n4. $BASE/src/main/java/com/ibm/websphere/samples/daytrader/impl/direct/TradeDirect.java\n   - This is the largest file (1838 lines). It uses JDBC directly with DataSource and JMS.\n   - Replace @Dependent with @Component (or @Service with @Scope(\"prototype\"))\n   - Replace javax.sql.DataSource lookup (JNDI) with @Autowired DataSource\n   - Replace javax.jms.* - remove JMS entirely, simplify queueOrder to call completeOrder directly\n   - Replace javax.transaction.UserTransaction with Spring's @Transactional or PlatformTransactionManager\n   - Replace EJBException with RuntimeException\n   - Replace javax.naming.* JNDI lookups with Spring DI\n   - Replace javax.annotation.Resource with @Autowired\n   - The DATASOURCE JNDI lookup should use @Autowired DataSource instead\n   - Keep all the SQL logic intact, just change the framework integration\n\n5. $BASE/src/main/java/com/ibm/websphere/samples/daytrader/impl/direct/TradeDirectDBUtils.java\n   - Similar to TradeDirect - uses DataSource via JNDI. Convert JNDI to Spring DI.\n   - Replace javax.sql.DataSource JNDI lookups with @Autowired\n   - Replace javax.naming.* with Spring\n   - Make it a @Component\n\n6. $BASE/src/main/java/com/ibm/websphere/samples/daytrader/impl/direct/KeySequenceDirect.java\n   - Read and convert javax.* to jakarta.*/Spring equivalents\n\n7. $BASE/src/main/java/com/ibm/websphere/samples/daytrader/impl/direct/AsyncOrderSubmitter.java\n   - Similar to AsyncScheduledOrderSubmitter. Convert ManagedExecutorService to Spring.\n\n8. $BASE/src/main/java/com/ibm/websphere/samples/daytrader/impl/direct/AsyncOrder.java\n   - Similar to AsyncScheduledOrder. Remove EJB dependencies.\n\nFor each file: READ it first, then EDIT it with the necessary changes. Be thorough - convert every javax.* reference.","subagent_type":"general-purpose"}}],"stop_reason":"tool_use","stop_sequence":null,"usage":{"input_tokens":1,"cache_creation_input_tokens":434,"cache_read_input_tokens":123194,"cache_creation":{"ephemeral_5m_input_tokens":434,"ephemeral_1h_input_tokens":0},"output_tokens":2979},"context_management":null},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"40640270-7dba-44a6-9773-cfde29fa9f25","uuid":"951531a7-86f3-41e7-95ba-d54230239686"}
{"type":"assistant","message":{"model":"claude-opus-4-6","id":"msg_bdrk_01SXGM8ydCDggSQ8DkUevu7c","type":"message","role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"tool_use","id":"toolu_bdrk_012aMR5A3KkRzkkSfc9EdGWg","name":"Task","input":{"description":"Migrate MDB and JAX-RS to Spring","prompt":"I'm migrating a Jakarta EE DayTrader app to Spring Boot 3.2.5. Convert the MDB and JAX-RS classes to Spring equivalents.\n\nBASE=/home/bmcginn/git/scarf-latest/scarbench-evals/final/prompt_claude__whole_applications__daytrader__jakarta__spring/run_3/output\n\nRead and edit each file:\n\n1. $BASE/src/main/java/com/ibm/websphere/samples/daytrader/mdb/DTBroker3MDB.java\n   - This is a Message-Driven Bean that processes order messages from JMS queue\n   - Since Spring Boot doesn't have JMS (without ActiveMQ/etc), convert to a Spring @Component\n   - Remove @MessageDriven and javax.jms.* annotations\n   - Make the onMessage method a regular public method that can be called directly\n   - Replace javax.ejb.* with Spring equivalents\n   - Replace @Inject with @Autowired\n   - Replace EJBException with RuntimeException\n   - Keep the business logic (calling completeOrder, cancelOrder)\n\n2. $BASE/src/main/java/com/ibm/websphere/samples/daytrader/mdb/DTStreamer3MDB.java\n   - Another MDB for streaming quote updates\n   - Same treatment as DTBroker3MDB - convert to @Component\n   - Remove JMS dependencies\n   - Keep business logic\n\n3. $BASE/src/main/java/com/ibm/websphere/samples/daytrader/jaxrs/JAXRSApplication.java\n   - This extends javax.ws.rs.core.Application with @ApplicationPath(\"/rest\")\n   - NOT NEEDED in Spring Boot. Either delete or replace with an empty class.\n   - Actually, just rewrite it to be empty or mark it as deprecated since Spring MVC handles REST\n   - REWRITE to just be a simple empty class or configuration class:\n   ```java\n   package com.ibm.websphere.samples.daytrader.jaxrs;\n   // JAX-RS Application config - no longer needed in Spring Boot\n   // REST endpoints are now Spring @RestController classes\n   ```\n\n4. $BASE/src/main/java/com/ibm/websphere/samples/daytrader/jaxrs/QuoteResource.java\n   - Convert from JAX-RS @Path to Spring @RestController\n   - Replace @Path(\"quotes\") with @RestController + @RequestMapping(\"/rest/quotes\")\n   - Replace @GET with @GetMapping\n   - Replace @POST with @PostMapping\n   - Replace @Produces/@Consumes with produces/consumes in mapping annotations\n   - Replace @PathParam with @PathVariable\n   - Replace @FormParam with @RequestParam\n   - Replace CDI Instance<TradeServices> injection with @Autowired TradeServices (just inject the EJB one directly)\n   - Replace javax.ws.rs.* with Spring web annotations\n   - Replace @RequestScoped - not needed in Spring (controllers are singletons by default)\n\n5. $BASE/src/main/java/com/ibm/websphere/samples/daytrader/jaxrs/BroadcastResource.java\n   - Convert from JAX-RS SSE to Spring SseEmitter\n   - Replace @Path with @RestController + @RequestMapping\n   - Replace JAX-RS SSE (SseBroadcaster, SseEventSink) with Spring's SseEmitter\n   - Replace @Context with Spring injection\n   - Replace CDI @ObservesAsync with Spring @EventListener\n   - Simplify SSE to use Spring's SseEmitter pattern\n\nFor each file: READ it first, then EDIT with complete rewrites where needed.","subagent_type":"general-purpose"}}],"stop_reason":"tool_use","stop_sequence":null,"usage":{"input_tokens":1,"cache_creation_input_tokens":434,"cache_read_input_tokens":123194,"cache_creation":{"ephemeral_5m_input_tokens":434,"ephemeral_1h_input_tokens":0},"output_tokens":2979},"context_management":null},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"40640270-7dba-44a6-9773-cfde29fa9f25","uuid":"d6eb159b-3285-47ea-ab42-bfac4593c9af"}
{"type":"assistant","message":{"model":"claude-opus-4-6","id":"msg_bdrk_01SXGM8ydCDggSQ8DkUevu7c","type":"message","role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"tool_use","id":"toolu_bdrk_01LJeeEApPYxuC3Y6WHXiLUw","name":"Task","input":{"description":"Migrate JSF and servlet classes","prompt":"I'm migrating a Jakarta EE DayTrader app to Spring Boot 3.2.5. Convert the JSF backing beans and remaining web classes.\n\nBASE=/home/bmcginn/git/scarf-latest/scarbench-evals/final/prompt_claude__whole_applications__daytrader__jakarta__spring/run_3/output\n\nFor the JSF web tier - since Spring Boot doesn't support JSF well, we need to convert the JSF backing beans to Spring MVC controllers. However, given the complexity, the simplest approach is:\n- Convert JSF backing beans to Spring @Controller classes\n- The existing JSP files can serve as views (the app already has JSP files)\n- Create a simple Spring MVC controller that handles the main web flows\n\nRead and edit each of these files. For EVERY file, read it first then edit:\n\n1. $BASE/src/main/java/com/ibm/websphere/samples/daytrader/web/jsf/TradeAppJSF.java\n   - This is the main JSF backing bean with @Named(\"tradeapp\") @SessionScoped\n   - Convert to Spring @Controller @SessionScope\n   - Replace javax.faces.* imports\n   - Replace javax.enterprise.context.SessionScoped with org.springframework.web.context.annotation.SessionScope\n   - Replace @Named with @Controller\n   - Replace @Inject with @Autowired\n   - Replace javax.validation with jakarta.validation\n   - The JSF-specific FacesContext usage needs to be removed or replaced with Spring equivalents\n\n2. $BASE/src/main/java/com/ibm/websphere/samples/daytrader/web/jsf/TradeConfigJSF.java\n   - JSF config backing bean. Convert similarly.\n   - Replace @Named/@SessionScoped with @Controller/@SessionScope\n   - Replace @Inject with @Autowired\n\n3. $BASE/src/main/java/com/ibm/websphere/samples/daytrader/web/jsf/MarketSummaryJSF.java\n   - Replace JSF annotations with Spring equivalents\n\n4-10. Read ALL other JSF files in web/jsf/ directory:\n   - QuoteJSF.java, PortfolioJSF.java, QuoteData.java, HoldingData.java, OrderData.java, OrderDataJSF.java, AccountDataJSF.java, JSFLoginFilter.java, LoginValidator.java\n   - For each: Replace javax.faces.* with jakarta.faces.* or Spring equivalents\n   - Replace @Named with @Component or @Controller\n   - Replace @RequestScoped/@SessionScoped with Spring scopes\n   - Replace javax.enterprise.* with Spring\n   - Replace @Inject with @Autowired\n   - Replace javax.validation with jakarta.validation\n   - For the JSFLoginFilter (servlet filter), convert javax.servlet to jakarta.servlet\n\n11. Also read and migrate ALL servlet/prims classes in web/prims/ directory. There are many PingServlet*.java files.\n   For ALL of these: Replace javax.servlet.* with jakarta.servlet.*\n   This is a bulk find-and-replace across ~30+ files.\n\n12. Also migrate web/prims/beanval/*.java files - replace javax.validation with jakarta.validation, javax.inject with Spring, javax.enterprise with Spring.\n\n13. Also migrate web/prims/cdi/*.java files - replace CDI annotations with Spring equivalents.\n\nThis is a lot of files. The most important ones are the JSF beans (items 1-3) and the servlet files. For the servlet files, the key change is just javax.servlet -> jakarta.servlet.","subagent_type":"general-purpose"}}],"stop_reason":"tool_use","stop_sequence":null,"usage":{"input_tokens":1,"cache_creation_input_tokens":434,"cache_read_input_tokens":123194,"cache_creation":{"ephemeral_5m_input_tokens":434,"ephemeral_1h_input_tokens":0},"output_tokens":2979},"context_management":null},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"40640270-7dba-44a6-9773-cfde29fa9f25","uuid":"bbed8f48-63bb-4cb2-80ca-d4962934ccea"}
{"type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"type":"text","text":"I'm migrating a Jakarta EE DayTrader app to Spring Boot 3.2.5. Migrate the remaining EJB3 implementation classes.\n\nBASE=/home/bmcginn/git/scarf-latest/scarbench-evals/final/prompt_claude__whole_applications__daytrader__jakarta__spring/run_3/output\n\nRead and edit each of these files:\n\n1. $BASE/src/main/java/com/ibm/websphere/samples/daytrader/impl/ejb3/AsyncScheduledOrderSubmitter.java\n   - This uses @Dependent, ManagedExecutorService, @Resource. Convert to Spring:\n   - Replace @Dependent with @Component\n   - Replace @Resource ManagedExecutorService with @Autowired TaskExecutor or just use Spring's @Async\n   - Replace javax.* imports with jakarta.* or Spring equivalents\n   - Keep it simple - use a ThreadPoolTaskExecutor or just submit to a simple executor\n\n2. $BASE/src/main/java/com/ibm/websphere/samples/daytrader/impl/ejb3/AsyncScheduledOrder.java\n   - This is a Runnable that calls TradeSLSBBean.completeOrder(). \n   - Remove javax.ejb.* imports\n   - Replace EJBException with RuntimeException\n   - Keep it as a plain Runnable class\n\n3. $BASE/src/main/java/com/ibm/websphere/samples/daytrader/impl/session2direct/DirectSLSBBean.java\n   - This is a @Stateless EJB that wraps TradeDirect. Convert:\n   - Replace @Stateless with @Service\n   - Replace @Inject/@EJB with @Autowired\n   - Replace javax.* with jakarta.* or Spring equivalents\n   - Replace EJBException with RuntimeException\n   - This class delegates to TradeDirect for all operations\n\n4. $BASE/src/main/java/com/ibm/websphere/samples/daytrader/impl/direct/TradeDirect.java\n   - This is the largest file (1838 lines). It uses JDBC directly with DataSource and JMS.\n   - Replace @Dependent with @Component (or @Service with @Scope(\"prototype\"))\n   - Replace javax.sql.DataSource lookup (JNDI) with @Autowired DataSource\n   - Replace javax.jms.* - remove JMS entirely, simplify queueOrder to call completeOrder directly\n   - Replace javax.transaction.UserTransaction with Spring's @Transactional or PlatformTransactionManager\n   - Replace EJBException with RuntimeException\n   - Replace javax.naming.* JNDI lookups with Spring DI\n   - Replace javax.annotation.Resource with @Autowired\n   - The DATASOURCE JNDI lookup should use @Autowired DataSource instead\n   - Keep all the SQL logic intact, just change the framework integration\n\n5. $BASE/src/main/java/com/ibm/websphere/samples/daytrader/impl/direct/TradeDirectDBUtils.java\n   - Similar to TradeDirect - uses DataSource via JNDI. Convert JNDI to Spring DI.\n   - Replace javax.sql.DataSource JNDI lookups with @Autowired\n   - Replace javax.naming.* with Spring\n   - Make it a @Component\n\n6. $BASE/src/main/java/com/ibm/websphere/samples/daytrader/impl/direct/KeySequenceDirect.java\n   - Read and convert javax.* to jakarta.*/Spring equivalents\n\n7. $BASE/src/main/java/com/ibm/websphere/samples/daytrader/impl/direct/AsyncOrderSubmitter.java\n   - Similar to AsyncScheduledOrderSubmitter. Convert ManagedExecutorService to Spring.\n\n8. $BASE/src/main/java/com/ibm/websphere/samples/daytrader/impl/direct/AsyncOrder.java\n   - Similar to AsyncScheduledOrder. Remove EJB dependencies.\n\nFor each file: READ it first, then EDIT it with the necessary changes. Be thorough - convert every javax.* reference."}]},"parent_tool_use_id":"toolu_bdrk_01GU47pNQoS8nHQfwvNhau6s","session_id":"40640270-7dba-44a6-9773-cfde29fa9f25","uuid":"e2ca755e-b78d-4a4e-8d12-67314d75d139"}
{"type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"type":"text","text":"I'm migrating a Jakarta EE DayTrader app to Spring Boot 3.2.5. Convert the MDB and JAX-RS classes to Spring equivalents.\n\nBASE=/home/bmcginn/git/scarf-latest/scarbench-evals/final/prompt_claude__whole_applications__daytrader__jakarta__spring/run_3/output\n\nRead and edit each file:\n\n1. $BASE/src/main/java/com/ibm/websphere/samples/daytrader/mdb/DTBroker3MDB.java\n   - This is a Message-Driven Bean that processes order messages from JMS queue\n   - Since Spring Boot doesn't have JMS (without ActiveMQ/etc), convert to a Spring @Component\n   - Remove @MessageDriven and javax.jms.* annotations\n   - Make the onMessage method a regular public method that can be called directly\n   - Replace javax.ejb.* with Spring equivalents\n   - Replace @Inject with @Autowired\n   - Replace EJBException with RuntimeException\n   - Keep the business logic (calling completeOrder, cancelOrder)\n\n2. $BASE/src/main/java/com/ibm/websphere/samples/daytrader/mdb/DTStreamer3MDB.java\n   - Another MDB for streaming quote updates\n   - Same treatment as DTBroker3MDB - convert to @Component\n   - Remove JMS dependencies\n   - Keep business logic\n\n3. $BASE/src/main/java/com/ibm/websphere/samples/daytrader/jaxrs/JAXRSApplication.java\n   - This extends javax.ws.rs.core.Application with @ApplicationPath(\"/rest\")\n   - NOT NEEDED in Spring Boot. Either delete or replace with an empty class.\n   - Actually, just rewrite it to be empty or mark it as deprecated since Spring MVC handles REST\n   - REWRITE to just be a simple empty class or configuration class:\n   ```java\n   package com.ibm.websphere.samples.daytrader.jaxrs;\n   // JAX-RS Application config - no longer needed in Spring Boot\n   // REST endpoints are now Spring @RestController classes\n   ```\n\n4. $BASE/src/main/java/com/ibm/websphere/samples/daytrader/jaxrs/QuoteResource.java\n   - Convert from JAX-RS @Path to Spring @RestController\n   - Replace @Path(\"quotes\") with @RestController + @RequestMapping(\"/rest/quotes\")\n   - Replace @GET with @GetMapping\n   - Replace @POST with @PostMapping\n   - Replace @Produces/@Consumes with produces/consumes in mapping annotations\n   - Replace @PathParam with @PathVariable\n   - Replace @FormParam with @RequestParam\n   - Replace CDI Instance<TradeServices> injection with @Autowired TradeServices (just inject the EJB one directly)\n   - Replace javax.ws.rs.* with Spring web annotations\n   - Replace @RequestScoped - not needed in Spring (controllers are singletons by default)\n\n5. $BASE/src/main/java/com/ibm/websphere/samples/daytrader/jaxrs/BroadcastResource.java\n   - Convert from JAX-RS SSE to Spring SseEmitter\n   - Replace @Path with @RestController + @RequestMapping\n   - Replace JAX-RS SSE (SseBroadcaster, SseEventSink) with Spring's SseEmitter\n   - Replace @Context with Spring injection\n   - Replace CDI @ObservesAsync with Spring @EventListener\n   - Simplify SSE to use Spring's SseEmitter pattern\n\nFor each file: READ it first, then EDIT with complete rewrites where needed."}]},"parent_tool_use_id":"toolu_bdrk_012aMR5A3KkRzkkSfc9EdGWg","session_id":"40640270-7dba-44a6-9773-cfde29fa9f25","uuid":"e00a2c52-257f-4d06-a7d2-5b28b58b2cb3"}
{"type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"type":"text","text":"I'm migrating a Jakarta EE DayTrader app to Spring Boot 3.2.5. Convert the JSF backing beans and remaining web classes.\n\nBASE=/home/bmcginn/git/scarf-latest/scarbench-evals/final/prompt_claude__whole_applications__daytrader__jakarta__spring/run_3/output\n\nFor the JSF web tier - since Spring Boot doesn't support JSF well, we need to convert the JSF backing beans to Spring MVC controllers. However, given the complexity, the simplest approach is:\n- Convert JSF backing beans to Spring @Controller classes\n- The existing JSP files can serve as views (the app already has JSP files)\n- Create a simple Spring MVC controller that handles the main web flows\n\nRead and edit each of these files. For EVERY file, read it first then edit:\n\n1. $BASE/src/main/java/com/ibm/websphere/samples/daytrader/web/jsf/TradeAppJSF.java\n   - This is the main JSF backing bean with @Named(\"tradeapp\") @SessionScoped\n   - Convert to Spring @Controller @SessionScope\n   - Replace javax.faces.* imports\n   - Replace javax.enterprise.context.SessionScoped with org.springframework.web.context.annotation.SessionScope\n   - Replace @Named with @Controller\n   - Replace @Inject with @Autowired\n   - Replace javax.validation with jakarta.validation\n   - The JSF-specific FacesContext usage needs to be removed or replaced with Spring equivalents\n\n2. $BASE/src/main/java/com/ibm/websphere/samples/daytrader/web/jsf/TradeConfigJSF.java\n   - JSF config backing bean. Convert similarly.\n   - Replace @Named/@SessionScoped with @Controller/@SessionScope\n   - Replace @Inject with @Autowired\n\n3. $BASE/src/main/java/com/ibm/websphere/samples/daytrader/web/jsf/MarketSummaryJSF.java\n   - Replace JSF annotations with Spring equivalents\n\n4-10. Read ALL other JSF files in web/jsf/ directory:\n   - QuoteJSF.java, PortfolioJSF.java, QuoteData.java, HoldingData.java, OrderData.java, OrderDataJSF.java, AccountDataJSF.java, JSFLoginFilter.java, LoginValidator.java\n   - For each: Replace javax.faces.* with jakarta.faces.* or Spring equivalents\n   - Replace @Named with @Component or @Controller\n   - Replace @RequestScoped/@SessionScoped with Spring scopes\n   - Replace javax.enterprise.* with Spring\n   - Replace @Inject with @Autowired\n   - Replace javax.validation with jakarta.validation\n   - For the JSFLoginFilter (servlet filter), convert javax.servlet to jakarta.servlet\n\n11. Also read and migrate ALL servlet/prims classes in web/prims/ directory. There are many PingServlet*.java files.\n   For ALL of these: Replace javax.servlet.* with jakarta.servlet.*\n   This is a bulk find-and-replace across ~30+ files.\n\n12. Also migrate web/prims/beanval/*.java files - replace javax.validation with jakarta.validation, javax.inject with Spring, javax.enterprise with Spring.\n\n13. Also migrate web/prims/cdi/*.java files - replace CDI annotations with Spring equivalents.\n\nThis is a lot of files. The most important ones are the JSF beans (items 1-3) and the servlet files. For the servlet files, the key change is just javax.servlet -> jakarta.servlet."}]},"parent_tool_use_id":"toolu_bdrk_01LJeeEApPYxuC3Y6WHXiLUw","session_id":"40640270-7dba-44a6-9773-cfde29fa9f25","uuid":"2cf3a207-1201-4122-a69d-1f947cc5db13"}
