{"type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"tool_use_id":"toolu_bdrk_01GU47pNQoS8nHQfwvNhau6s","type":"tool_result","content":[{"type":"text","text":"Perfect! All 8 files have been successfully converted. Let me create a summary of all the changes made:\n\n## Migration Summary\n\nI have successfully migrated all 8 remaining EJB3 implementation classes to Spring Boot 3.2.5. Here's a detailed breakdown of the conversions:\n\n### 1. **AsyncScheduledOrderSubmitter.java** \n**Location:** `/home/bmcginn/git/scarf-latest/scarbench-evals/final/prompt_claude__whole_applications__daytrader__jakarta__spring/run_3/output/src/main/java/com/ibm/websphere/samples/daytrader/impl/ejb3/AsyncScheduledOrderSubmitter.java`\n\n**Changes:**\n- Replaced `@RequestScoped` with `@Component` and `@RequestScope`\n- Replaced `@Resource ManagedScheduledExecutorService` with `@Autowired ThreadPoolTaskScheduler`\n- Replaced `javax.enterprise` imports with Spring equivalents\n- Changed `mes.schedule()` call to use `taskScheduler.schedule()` with a Date object\n\n### 2. **AsyncScheduledOrder.java**\n**Location:** `/home/bmcginn/git/scarf-latest/scarbench-evals/final/prompt_claude__whole_applications__daytrader__jakarta__spring/run_3/output/src/main/java/com/ibm/websphere/samples/daytrader/impl/ejb3/AsyncScheduledOrder.java`\n\n**Changes:**\n- Replaced `@Dependent` with `@Component`\n- Removed CDI `Instance<TradeServices>` injection pattern\n- Added `@Autowired ApplicationContext` for dynamic bean lookup\n- Modified `setProperties()` to fetch the appropriate TradeServices implementation dynamically\n- Replaced `javax.enterprise` and `javax.inject` imports with Spring equivalents\n\n### 3. **DirectSLSBBean.java**\n**Location:** `/home/bmcginn/git/scarf-latest/scarbench-evals/final/prompt_claude__whole_applications__daytrader__jakarta__spring/run_3/output/src/main/java/com/ibm/websphere/samples/daytrader/impl/session2direct/DirectSLSBBean.java`\n\n**Changes:**\n- Replaced `@Stateless` with `@Service`\n- Removed `@TransactionAttribute` and `@TransactionManagement` annotations\n- Added `@Transactional` for transaction management\n- Replaced `@Inject` with `@Autowired` and added `@Qualifier(\"tradeDirect\")`\n- Changed `javax.validation` to `jakarta.validation`\n- Replaced `javax.ejb.*` imports with Spring equivalents\n\n### 4. **TradeDirect.java** (Large file - 1838 lines)\n**Location:** `/home/bmcginn/git/scarf-latest/scarbench-evals/final/prompt_claude__whole_applications__daytrader__jakarta__spring/run_3/output/src/main/java/com/ibm/websphere/samples/daytrader/impl/direct/TradeDirect.java`\n\n**Major Changes:**\n- Replaced `@Dependent` with `@Component(\"tradeDirect\")` and `@Scope(\"prototype\")`\n- **Removed all JMS dependencies** (`QueueConnectionFactory`, `TopicConnectionFactory`, `Queue`, `Topic`, `JMSContext`)\n- Replaced `@Resource DataSource` with `@Autowired DataSource`\n- Replaced `@Resource UserTransaction` with `@Autowired PlatformTransactionManager`\n- Replaced `@Resource ManagedExecutorService` with `@Autowired TaskExecutor`\n- Replaced CDI `Event<String>` with Spring's `ApplicationEventPublisher`\n- **Simplified `queueOrder()` method** - now directly calls `completeOrder()` instead of using JMS\n- **Simplified `publishQuotePriceChange()` method** - uses Spring's event publisher instead of JMS topic\n- Removed `txn.begin()`, `txn.commit()`, `txn.rollback()` calls - Spring manages transactions\n- Replaced `javax.ejb.FinderException` with `RuntimeException`\n- Replaced `JMSException` with generic `Exception` in catch blocks\n- Changed `javax.validation` to `jakarta.validation`\n\n### 5. **TradeDirectDBUtils.java**\n**Location:** `/home/bmcginn/git/scarf-latest/scarbench-evals/final/prompt_claude__whole_applications__daytrader__jakarta__spring/run_3/output/src/main/java/com/ibm/websphere/samples/daytrader/impl/direct/TradeDirectDBUtils.java`\n\n**Changes:**\n- Replaced `@ApplicationScoped` with `@Component`\n- Replaced `@Resource(lookup = \"jdbc/TradeDataSource\")` with `@Autowired DataSource`\n- Replaced `@Inject` with `@Autowired` and added `@Qualifier(\"tradeDirect\")`\n- Replaced `javax.annotation`, `javax.enterprise`, and `javax.inject` imports with Spring equivalents\n\n### 6. **KeySequenceDirect.java**\n**Location:** `/home/bmcginn/git/scarf-latest/scarbench-evals/final/prompt_claude__whole_applications__daytrader__jakarta__spring/run_3/output/src/main/java/com/ibm/websphere/samples/daytrader/impl/direct/KeySequenceDirect.java`\n\n**Changes:**\n- No changes needed - this is a plain utility class with no EJB/CDI dependencies\n\n### 7. **AsyncOrderSubmitter.java**\n**Location:** `/home/bmcginn/git/scarf-latest/scarbench-evals/final/prompt_claude__whole_applications__daytrader__jakarta__spring/run_3/output/src/main/java/com/ibm/websphere/samples/daytrader/impl/direct/AsyncOrderSubmitter.java`\n\n**Changes:**\n- Replaced `@RequestScoped` with `@Component` and `@RequestScope`\n- Replaced `@Resource ManagedExecutorService` with `@Autowired AsyncTaskExecutor`\n- Replaced `@Inject` with `@Autowired`\n- Replaced `javax.enterprise` and `javax.annotation` imports with Spring equivalents\n\n### 8. **AsyncOrder.java**\n**Location:** `/home/bmcginn/git/scarf-latest/scarbench-evals/final/prompt_claude__whole_applications__daytrader__jakarta__spring/run_3/output/src/main/java/com/ibm/websphere/samples/daytrader/impl/direct/AsyncOrder.java`\n\n**Changes:**\n- Replaced `@Dependent` with `@Component`\n- Replaced `@Inject` with `@Autowired` and added `@Qualifier(\"tradeDirect\")`\n- Replaced `@Resource UserTransaction` with `@Autowired PlatformTransactionManager`\n- Rewrote transaction management in `run()` method to use Spring's `PlatformTransactionManager`\n- Replaced manual `ut.begin()`, `ut.commit()`, `ut.rollback()` with Spring transaction API\n- Replaced `javax.transaction`, `javax.enterprise`, and `javax.annotation` imports with Spring equivalents\n\n## Key Architectural Changes\n\n1. **Transaction Management:** All JTA `UserTransaction` usage replaced with Spring's declarative transaction management via `@Transactional` or programmatic `PlatformTransactionManager`\n\n2. **JMS Removal:** All JMS queue and topic operations simplified to direct method calls or Spring event publishing - this significantly reduces complexity\n\n3. **Dependency Injection:** All CDI annotations (`@Inject`, `@Dependent`, `@RequestScoped`, `@ApplicationScoped`) replaced with Spring equivalents (`@Autowired`, `@Component`, `@Service`, `@RequestScope`)\n\n4. **Resource Injection:** All `@Resource` JNDI lookups replaced with Spring's dependency injection\n\n5. **Async Execution:** Java EE Concurrency Utilities (`ManagedExecutorService`, `ManagedScheduledExecutorService`) replaced with Spring's `TaskExecutor` and `ThreadPoolTaskScheduler`\n\n6. **Exception Handling:** EJB-specific exceptions like `FinderException` and `EJBException` replaced with `RuntimeException`\n\nAll SQL logic and business logic remain intact - only the framework integration layer has been converted to Spring Boot."}]}]},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"40640270-7dba-44a6-9773-cfde29fa9f25","uuid":"c421ab24-d808-45b0-b751-773125966bd5"}
