{"type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"tool_use_id":"toolu_bdrk_01LJeeEApPYxuC3Y6WHXiLUw","type":"tool_result","content":[{"type":"text","text":"Excellent! All non-JNDI javax imports have been converted. Let me provide a summary of what was done:\n\n## Summary of JSF Backing Beans and Web Classes Migration\n\nI have successfully converted the JSF backing beans and remaining web classes from Jakarta EE/CDI to Spring Boot 3.2.5. Here's what was accomplished:\n\n### **JSF Backing Beans Converted (web/jsf/):**\n\n1. **TradeAppJSF.java** - Main JSF backing bean\n   - Converted `@Named(\"tradeapp\")` to `@Controller(\"tradeapp\")`\n   - Converted `@SessionScoped` (javax.enterprise.context) to `@SessionScope` (Spring)\n   - Replaced `@Inject` with `@Autowired`\n   - Replaced `ExternalContext` usage with Spring `RequestContextHolder`\n   - Converted from CDI `Instance<TradeServices>` to direct `@Autowired TradeServices`\n\n2. **TradeConfigJSF.java** - Configuration backing bean\n   - Converted `@Named` to `@Controller`\n   - Converted `@RequestScoped` to `@RequestScope`\n   - Replaced `@Inject` with `@Autowired`\n   - Replaced `ExternalContext` with Spring equivalents\n\n3. **MarketSummaryJSF.java** - Market data bean\n   - Converted to `@Controller` with `@RequestScope`\n   - Replaced CDI annotations with Spring equivalents\n\n4. **QuoteJSF.java** - Quote management bean\n   - Converted to Spring `@Controller`\n   - Replaced `HtmlDataTable` (JSF-specific) with generic `Object` type\n\n5. **PortfolioJSF.java** - Portfolio management\n   - Converted to Spring with proper scoping\n   - Migrated validation annotations from `javax.validation` to `jakarta.validation`\n\n6. **OrderDataJSF.java**, **AccountDataJSF.java** - Data beans\n   - Converted to Spring controllers\n   - Updated all dependency injection\n\n7. **HoldingData.java**, **OrderData.java**, **QuoteData.java**\n   - Simple POJOs with minimal changes (just annotation updates)\n\n8. **JSFLoginFilter.java** - Servlet filter\n   - Converted all `javax.servlet.*` to `jakarta.servlet.*`\n\n9. **LoginValidator.java** - JSF validator\n   - Converted `javax.faces.*` to `jakarta.faces.*`\n\n### **Servlet Classes (web/prims/):**\n\nConverted **35+ servlet files** including:\n- All `PingServlet*.java` files (30+ files)\n- Replaced `javax.servlet.*` with `jakarta.servlet.*`\n- Replaced `javax.websocket.*` with `jakarta.websocket.*`\n- Replaced `@Inject` with `@Autowired`\n- Replaced `javax.json.*` with `jakarta.json.*`\n\n### **Bean Validation Classes (web/prims/beanval/):**\n\nConverted **6 files**:\n- `PingServletBeanValSimple1.java`, `PingServletBeanValSimple2.java`\n- `PingServletBeanValCDI.java`\n- `SimpleBean1.java`, `SimpleBean2.java`\n- `CDIMethodConstraintBean.java`\n- Replaced `javax.validation.*` with `jakarta.validation.*`\n- Replaced `javax.inject` with Spring `@Autowired`\n- Converted `@RequestScoped` to `@RequestScope`\n\n### **CDI Classes (web/prims/cdi/):**\n\nConverted **15 files** including:\n- `PingCDIBean.java` - Replaced CDI `BeanManager` with Spring `ApplicationContext`\n- `PingCDIJSFBean.java` - Converted `@Named/@SessionScoped` to Spring equivalents\n- `PingEJBLocal.java` - Converted from `@Stateful/@Local` EJB to Spring `@Component`\n- `PingEJBLocalDecorator.java` - Converted CDI Decorator to Spring `@Component`\n- `PingInterceptor.java` - Converted CDI Interceptor to Spring AOP `MethodInterceptor`\n- `PingServletCDI.java` and others - Replaced `@EJB` with `@Autowired`\n- Replaced all `javax.enterprise.*` with Spring equivalents\n- Converted CDI event observers (`@ObservesAsync`) to Spring-compatible methods\n\n### **Other Web Classes:**\n\n- **web/servlet/** - Converted `TradeServletAction.java`, `OrdersAlertFilter.java`, `TestServlet.java`\n- **web/websocket/** - Converted `MarketSummaryWebSocket.java` with WebSocket and CDI event handling\n- **web/prims/ejb3/** - Converted EJB annotations to Spring equivalents\n\n### **Key Conversions Applied:**\n\n| Original (Java EE/CDI) | Converted To (Spring Boot) |\n|------------------------|----------------------------|\n| `javax.servlet.*` | `jakarta.servlet.*` |\n| `javax.faces.*` | `jakarta.faces.*` |\n| `javax.validation.*` | `jakarta.validation.*` |\n| `javax.websocket.*` | `jakarta.websocket.*` |\n| `javax.ws.rs.*` | `jakarta.ws.rs.*` |\n| `javax.json.*` | `jakarta.json.*` |\n| `javax.persistence.*` | `jakarta.persistence.*` |\n| `javax.xml.bind.*` | `jakarta.xml.bind.*` |\n| `javax.jms.*` | `jakarta.jms.*` |\n| `javax.annotation.*` (PostConstruct, etc.) | `jakarta.annotation.*` |\n| `@Named` | `@Controller` or `@Component` |\n| `@Inject` | `@Autowired` |\n| `@RequestScoped` | `@RequestScope` |\n| `@SessionScoped` | `@SessionScope` |\n| `@EJB` | `@Autowired` |\n| `ExternalContext` (JSF) | `RequestContextHolder` (Spring) |\n| `Instance<T>` (CDI) | Direct `@Autowired` (Spring) |\n| `BeanManager` (CDI) | `ApplicationContext` (Spring) |\n\n### **Statistics:**\n\n- **Total files processed:** 100 Java files in web layer\n- **Files with Jakarta imports:** 84 files\n- **Files with Spring imports:** 40 files\n- **Remaining javax imports:** Only `javax.naming` (JNDI) which is intentionally kept\n\n### **Notes:**\n\n1. **JSF to Spring MVC:** The JSF backing beans were converted to Spring `@Controller` classes. The application will need Spring MVC configuration to work properly, but the JSP views can remain largely unchanged.\n\n2. **CDI Features:** Some CDI-specific features like Decorators, Interceptors, and async event observers have Spring equivalents but may require additional configuration or manual implementation.\n\n3. **HtmlDataTable:** JSF-specific UI components like `HtmlDataTable` were changed to generic types - these will need proper Spring MVC binding.\n\n4. **JNDI:** The `javax.naming` package was intentionally left unchanged as JNDI is not part of the Jakarta EE namespace migration and remains valid in modern Java applications.\n\nThe migration is complete for all JSF backing beans and web tier classes!"}]}]},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"40640270-7dba-44a6-9773-cfde29fa9f25","uuid":"1237e0f8-67b0-4968-a93a-74dc8a6bb716"}
