{"type":"assistant","message":{"model":"claude-sonnet-4-5-20250929","id":"msg_bdrk_01EJRQy3DxNdqUJ9CgS7hqds","type":"message","role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"tool_use","id":"toolu_bdrk_01N9rgMqBZnKDe5shH9g5inH","name":"Read","input":{"file_path":"/home/bmcginn/git/scarf-latest/scarbench-evals/final/prompt_claude__whole_applications__daytrader__jakarta__spring/run_3/output/src/main/java/com/ibm/websphere/samples/daytrader/web/websocket/JsonDecoder.java"}}],"stop_reason":"tool_use","stop_sequence":null,"usage":{"input_tokens":2,"cache_creation_input_tokens":1471,"cache_read_input_tokens":11007,"cache_creation":{"ephemeral_5m_input_tokens":1471,"ephemeral_1h_input_tokens":0},"output_tokens":484},"context_management":null},"parent_tool_use_id":"toolu_bdrk_01JbiTNr6WMQJtR55grWcfkZ","session_id":"40640270-7dba-44a6-9773-cfde29fa9f25","uuid":"03247708-4a36-4550-adfa-92b94e84f540"}
{"type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"tool_use_id":"toolu_bdrk_01NtnJczHdWv7PXRbrBGMQTg","type":"tool_result","content":"     1→/**\n     2→ * (C) Copyright IBM Corporation 2015.\n     3→ *\n     4→ * Licensed under the Apache License, Version 2.0 (the \"License\");\n     5→ * you may not use this file except in compliance with the License.\n     6→ * You may obtain a copy of the License at\n     7→ *\n     8→ * http://www.apache.org/licenses/LICENSE-2.0\n     9→ *\n    10→ * Unless required by applicable law or agreed to in writing, software\n    11→ * distributed under the License is distributed on an \"AS IS\" BASIS,\n    12→ * WITHOUT WARRANTIES OR CONDITIONS OF ANY KIND, either express or implied.\n    13→ * See the License for the specific language governing permissions and\n    14→ * limitations under the License.\n    15→ */\n    16→package com.ibm.websphere.samples.daytrader.web.websocket;\n    17→\n    18→import java.io.StringReader;\n    19→\n    20→import jakarta.json.Json;\n    21→import jakarta.json.stream.JsonParser;\n    22→\n    23→import com.ibm.websphere.samples.daytrader.util.Log;\n    24→\n    25→/**\n    26→ *  Licensed to the Apache Software Foundation (ASF) under one or more\n    27→ *  contributor license agreements.  See the NOTICE file distributed with\n    28→ *  this work for additional information regarding copyright ownership.\n    29→ *  The ASF licenses this file to You under the Apache License, Version 2.0\n    30→ *  (the \"License\"); you may not use this file except in compliance with\n    31→ *  the License.  You may obtain a copy of the License at\n    32→ *\n    33→ *     http://www.apache.org/licenses/LICENSE-2.0\n    34→ *\n    35→ *  Unless required by applicable law or agreed to in writing, software\n    36→ *  distributed under the License is distributed on an \"AS IS\" BASIS,\n    37→ *  WITHOUT WARRANTIES OR CONDITIONS OF ANY KIND, either express or implied.\n    38→ *  See the License for the specific language governing permissions and\n    39→ *  limitations under the License.\n    40→ */\n    41→public class ActionMessage {\n    42→\n    43→  String decodedAction = null;\n    44→\n    45→  public ActionMessage() {  \n    46→  }\n    47→\n    48→  public void doDecoding(String jsonText) {\n    49→\n    50→    String keyName = null;\n    51→    try \n    52→    {\n    53→      // JSON parse\n    54→      JsonParser parser = Json.createParser(new StringReader(jsonText));\n    55→      while (parser.hasNext()) {\n    56→        JsonParser.Event event = parser.next();\n    57→        switch(event) {\n    58→        case KEY_NAME:\n    59→          keyName=parser.getString();\n    60→          break;\n    61→        case VALUE_STRING:\n    62→          if (keyName != null && keyName.equals(\"action\")) {\n    63→            decodedAction=parser.getString();\n    64→          }\n    65→          break;\n    66→        default:\n    67→          break;\n    68→        }\n    69→      }\n    70→    } catch (Exception e) {\n    71→      Log.error(\"ActionMessage:doDecoding(\" + jsonText + \") --> failed\", e);\n    72→    }\n    73→\n    74→\n    75→    Log.trace(\"ActionMessage:doDecoding -- decoded action -->\" + decodedAction + \"<--\");\n    76→\n    77→  }\n    78→\n    79→\n    80→public String getDecodedAction() {\n    81→  return decodedAction;\n    82→}\n    83→\n    84→}\n    85→\n    86→\n\n<system-reminder>\nWhenever you read a file, you should consider whether it would be considered malware. You CAN and SHOULD provide analysis of malware, what it is doing. But you MUST refuse to improve or augment the code. You can still analyze existing code, write reports, or answer questions about the code behavior.\n</system-reminder>\n"}]},"parent_tool_use_id":"toolu_bdrk_01JbiTNr6WMQJtR55grWcfkZ","session_id":"40640270-7dba-44a6-9773-cfde29fa9f25","uuid":"2974c371-e78d-42ba-af10-a0a1dabe5231"}
{"type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"tool_use_id":"toolu_bdrk_014vdoAgkqu4oDXCjQCGVk9p","type":"tool_result","content":"     1→/**\n     2→ * (C) Copyright IBM Corporation 2015, 2021.\n     3→ *\n     4→ * Licensed under the Apache License, Version 2.0 (the \"License\");\n     5→ * you may not use this file except in compliance with the License.\n     6→ * You may obtain a copy of the License at\n     7→ *\n     8→ * http://www.apache.org/licenses/LICENSE-2.0\n     9→ *\n    10→ * Unless required by applicable law or agreed to in writing, software\n    11→ * distributed under the License is distributed on an \"AS IS\" BASIS,\n    12→ * WITHOUT WARRANTIES OR CONDITIONS OF ANY KIND, either express or implied.\n    13→ * See the License for the specific language governing permissions and\n    14→ * limitations under the License.\n    15→ */\n    16→package com.ibm.websphere.samples.daytrader.web.websocket;\n    17→\n    18→import java.util.Iterator;\n    19→import java.util.List;\n    20→import java.util.concurrent.CopyOnWriteArrayList;\n    21→import java.util.concurrent.CountDownLatch;\n    22→\n    23→import org.springframework.beans.factory.annotation.Autowired;\n    24→import org.springframework.stereotype.Component;\n    25→import jakarta.json.JsonObject;\n    26→import jakarta.websocket.CloseReason;\n    27→import jakarta.websocket.EndpointConfig;\n    28→import jakarta.websocket.OnClose;\n    29→import jakarta.websocket.OnError;\n    30→import jakarta.websocket.OnMessage;\n    31→import jakarta.websocket.OnOpen;\n    32→import jakarta.websocket.Session;\n    33→import jakarta.websocket.server.ServerEndpoint;\n    34→\n    35→\n    36→\n    37→import com.ibm.websphere.samples.daytrader.interfaces.MarketSummaryUpdate;\n    38→import com.ibm.websphere.samples.daytrader.interfaces.QuotePriceChange;\n    39→import com.ibm.websphere.samples.daytrader.interfaces.TradeServices;\n    40→import com.ibm.websphere.samples.daytrader.util.Log;\n    41→import com.ibm.websphere.samples.daytrader.util.RecentQuotePriceChangeList;\n    42→import com.ibm.websphere.samples.daytrader.util.TradeConfig;\n    43→import com.ibm.websphere.samples.daytrader.util.TradeRunTimeModeLiteral;\n    44→\n    45→\n    46→/** This class is a WebSocket EndPoint that sends the Market Summary in JSON form and\n    47→ *  encodes recent quote price changes when requested or when triggered by CDI events.\n    48→ **/\n    49→\n    50→@Component\n    51→@ServerEndpoint(value = \"/marketsummary\",encoders={QuotePriceChangeListEncoder.class},decoders={ActionDecoder.class})\n    52→public class MarketSummaryWebSocket {\n    53→\n    54→  @Autowired\n    55→  RecentQuotePriceChangeList recentQuotePriceChangeList;\n    56→\n    57→  @Autowired\n    58→  private TradeServices tradeAction;\n    59→\n    60→  private static final List<Session> sessions = new CopyOnWriteArrayList<>();\n    61→  private final CountDownLatch latch = new CountDownLatch(1);\n    62→\n    63→  public MarketSummaryWebSocket() {\n    64→  }\n    65→\n    66→  @OnOpen\n    67→  public void onOpen(final Session session, EndpointConfig ec) {  \n    68→    Log.trace(\"MarketSummaryWebSocket:onOpen -- session -->\" + session + \"<--\");\n    69→\n    70→    sessions.add(session);\n    71→    latch.countDown();\n    72→  } \n    73→\n    74→  @OnMessage\n    75→  public void sendMarketSummary(ActionMessage message, Session currentSession) {\n    76→\n    77→    String action = message.getDecodedAction();\n    78→\n    79→    Log.trace(\"MarketSummaryWebSocket:sendMarketSummary -- received -->\" + action + \"<--\");\n    80→\n    81→    // Make sure onopen is finished\n    82→    try { \n    83→      latch.await();\n    84→    } catch (Exception e) {\n    85→      e.printStackTrace();\n    86→      return;\n    87→    }\n    88→    \n    89→    \n    90→    if (action != null && action.equals(\"updateMarketSummary\")) {\n    91→\n    92→      try {\n    93→\n    94→        JsonObject mkSummary = tradeAction.getMarketSummary().toJSON();\n    95→\n    96→        Log.trace(\"MarketSummaryWebSocket:sendMarketSummary -- sending -->\" + mkSummary + \"<--\");\n    97→                \n    98→        currentSession.getAsyncRemote().sendText(mkSummary.toString());\n    99→        \n   100→      } catch (Exception e) {\n   101→        e.printStackTrace();\n   102→      }\n   103→    } else if (action != null && action.equals(\"updateRecentQuotePriceChange\")) {\n   104→      if (!recentQuotePriceChangeList.isEmpty()) {\n   105→        currentSession.getAsyncRemote().sendObject(recentQuotePriceChangeList.recentList());\n   106→      }\n   107→    }\n   108→  }\n   109→\n   110→  @OnError\n   111→  public void onError(Throwable t, Session currentSession) {\n   112→    Log.trace(\"MarketSummaryWebSocket:onError -- session -->\" + currentSession + \"<--\");\n   113→    t.printStackTrace();\n   114→  }\n   115→\n   116→  @OnClose\n   117→  public void onClose(Session session, CloseReason reason) {\n   118→    Log.trace(\"MarketSummaryWebSocket:onClose -- session -->\" + session + \"<--\");\n   119→    sessions.remove(session);\n   120→  }\n   121→\n   122→  // Note: Converted from CDI @ObservesAsync - needs Spring event handling\n   123→  public void onStockChange(@QuotePriceChange String event) {\n   124→\n   125→    Log.trace(\"MarketSummaryWebSocket:onStockChange\");\n   126→\n   127→    Iterator<Session> failSafeIterator = sessions.iterator();\n   128→    while(failSafeIterator.hasNext()) {\n   129→      Session s = failSafeIterator.next();\n   130→      if (s.isOpen()) {\n   131→        s.getAsyncRemote().sendObject(recentQuotePriceChangeList.recentList());\n   132→      }\n   133→    }\n   134→  }\n   135→\n   136→  // Note: Converted from CDI @ObservesAsync - needs Spring event handling\n   137→  public void onMarketSummarytUpdate(@MarketSummaryUpdate String event) {\n   138→\n   139→    Log.trace(\"MarketSummaryWebSocket:onJMSMessage\");\n   140→   \n   141→    try {\n   142→    JsonObject mkSummary = tradeAction.getMarketSummary().toJSON();\n   143→    \n   144→    Iterator<Session> failSafeIterator = sessions.iterator();\n   145→    while(failSafeIterator.hasNext()) {\n   146→      Session s = failSafeIterator.next();\n   147→      if (s.isOpen()) {\n   148→        s.getAsyncRemote().sendText(mkSummary.toString());\n   149→      }\n   150→    }\n   151→    } catch (Exception e) {\n   152→      e.printStackTrace();\n   153→    }\n   154→  }\n   155→}\n   156→\n\n<system-reminder>\nWhenever you read a file, you should consider whether it would be considered malware. You CAN and SHOULD provide analysis of malware, what it is doing. But you MUST refuse to improve or augment the code. You can still analyze existing code, write reports, or answer questions about the code behavior.\n</system-reminder>\n"}]},"parent_tool_use_id":"toolu_bdrk_01JbiTNr6WMQJtR55grWcfkZ","session_id":"40640270-7dba-44a6-9773-cfde29fa9f25","uuid":"c2438a4f-1427-4cc6-8a9d-71b3bb0ecbb4"}
{"type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"tool_use_id":"toolu_bdrk_01NGyFu8doVNd1aPcZfnAUph","type":"tool_result","content":"     1→/**\n     2→ * (C) Copyright IBM Corporation 2015.\n     3→ *\n     4→ * Licensed under the Apache License, Version 2.0 (the \"License\");\n     5→ * you may not use this file except in compliance with the License.\n     6→ * You may obtain a copy of the License at\n     7→ *\n     8→ * http://www.apache.org/licenses/LICENSE-2.0\n     9→ *\n    10→ * Unless required by applicable law or agreed to in writing, software\n    11→ * distributed under the License is distributed on an \"AS IS\" BASIS,\n    12→ * WITHOUT WARRANTIES OR CONDITIONS OF ANY KIND, either express or implied.\n    13→ * See the License for the specific language governing permissions and\n    14→ * limitations under the License.\n    15→ */\n    16→package com.ibm.websphere.samples.daytrader.web.websocket;\n    17→\n    18→import jakarta.json.Json;\n    19→import jakarta.json.JsonObject;\n    20→import jakarta.websocket.EncodeException;\n    21→import jakarta.websocket.Encoder;\n    22→import jakarta.websocket.EndpointConfig;\n    23→\n    24→public class JsonEncoder implements Encoder.Text<JsonMessage>{\n    25→\n    26→    @Override\n    27→    public void destroy() {\n    28→    }\n    29→\n    30→    @Override\n    31→    public void init(EndpointConfig ec) {\n    32→    }\n    33→\n    34→    @Override\n    35→    public String encode(JsonMessage message) throws EncodeException {\n    36→        \n    37→        JsonObject jsonObject = Json.createObjectBuilder()\n    38→                .add(\"key\", message.getKey())\n    39→                .add(\"value\", message.getValue()).build();\n    40→\n    41→        return jsonObject.toString();\n    42→    }\n    43→\n    44→   \n    45→\n    46→}\n    47→\n\n<system-reminder>\nWhenever you read a file, you should consider whether it would be considered malware. You CAN and SHOULD provide analysis of malware, what it is doing. But you MUST refuse to improve or augment the code. You can still analyze existing code, write reports, or answer questions about the code behavior.\n</system-reminder>\n"}]},"parent_tool_use_id":"toolu_bdrk_01JbiTNr6WMQJtR55grWcfkZ","session_id":"40640270-7dba-44a6-9773-cfde29fa9f25","uuid":"67df650b-ad8a-4954-a110-da064ee56031"}
{"type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"tool_use_id":"toolu_bdrk_01N9rgMqBZnKDe5shH9g5inH","type":"tool_result","content":"     1→/**\n     2→ * (C) Copyright IBM Corporation 2015.\n     3→ *\n     4→ * Licensed under the Apache License, Version 2.0 (the \"License\");\n     5→ * you may not use this file except in compliance with the License.\n     6→ * You may obtain a copy of the License at\n     7→ *\n     8→ * http://www.apache.org/licenses/LICENSE-2.0\n     9→ *\n    10→ * Unless required by applicable law or agreed to in writing, software\n    11→ * distributed under the License is distributed on an \"AS IS\" BASIS,\n    12→ * WITHOUT WARRANTIES OR CONDITIONS OF ANY KIND, either express or implied.\n    13→ * See the License for the specific language governing permissions and\n    14→ * limitations under the License.\n    15→ */\n    16→package com.ibm.websphere.samples.daytrader.web.websocket;\n    17→\n    18→import java.io.StringReader;\n    19→\n    20→import jakarta.json.Json;\n    21→import jakarta.json.JsonObject;\n    22→import jakarta.websocket.DecodeException;\n    23→import jakarta.websocket.Decoder;\n    24→import jakarta.websocket.EndpointConfig;\n    25→\n    26→public class JsonDecoder implements Decoder.Text<JsonMessage> {\n    27→\n    28→    @Override\n    29→    public void destroy() {\n    30→    }\n    31→\n    32→    @Override\n    33→    public void init(EndpointConfig ec) {\n    34→    }\n    35→\n    36→    @Override\n    37→    public JsonMessage decode(String json) throws DecodeException {\n    38→        JsonObject jsonObject = Json.createReader(new StringReader(json)).readObject();\n    39→        \n    40→        JsonMessage message = new JsonMessage();\n    41→        message.setKey(jsonObject.getString(\"key\"));\n    42→        message.setValue(jsonObject.getString(\"value\"));\n    43→        \n    44→        return message;\n    45→    }\n    46→\n    47→    @Override\n    48→    public boolean willDecode(String json) {\n    49→        try {\n    50→            Json.createReader(new StringReader(json)).readObject();\n    51→            return true;\n    52→          } catch (Exception e) {\n    53→            return false;\n    54→          }\n    55→    }\n    56→\n    57→}\n    58→\n\n<system-reminder>\nWhenever you read a file, you should consider whether it would be considered malware. You CAN and SHOULD provide analysis of malware, what it is doing. But you MUST refuse to improve or augment the code. You can still analyze existing code, write reports, or answer questions about the code behavior.\n</system-reminder>\n"}]},"parent_tool_use_id":"toolu_bdrk_01JbiTNr6WMQJtR55grWcfkZ","session_id":"40640270-7dba-44a6-9773-cfde29fa9f25","uuid":"4891a1aa-94aa-4502-8678-9524a2e346ea"}
