{"type":"assistant","message":{"model":"claude-sonnet-4-5-20250929","id":"msg_bdrk_01HY6qMWABfAEVFGW2usq7sW","type":"message","role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"tool_use","id":"toolu_bdrk_0199J9E4816pwhVwknFCwDPv","name":"Read","input":{"file_path":"/home/bmcginn/git/scarf-latest/scarbench-evals/final/prompt_claude__whole_applications__daytrader__jakarta__spring/run_3/output/src/main/java/com/ibm/websphere/samples/daytrader/web/prims/PingJSONPObjectFactory.java"}}],"stop_reason":"tool_use","stop_sequence":null,"usage":{"input_tokens":6,"cache_creation_input_tokens":5083,"cache_read_input_tokens":12478,"cache_creation":{"ephemeral_5m_input_tokens":5083,"ephemeral_1h_input_tokens":0},"output_tokens":485},"context_management":null},"parent_tool_use_id":"toolu_bdrk_01JbiTNr6WMQJtR55grWcfkZ","session_id":"40640270-7dba-44a6-9773-cfde29fa9f25","uuid":"ec0d01e0-cab5-4cd9-9be0-65f37459a5f1"}
{"type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"tool_use_id":"toolu_bdrk_01AUyPV94VPr4xFFZmJkwsSL","type":"tool_result","content":"     1→/**\n     2→ * (C) Copyright IBM Corporation 2019.\n     3→ *\n     4→ * Licensed under the Apache License, Version 2.0 (the \"License\");\n     5→ * you may not use this file except in compliance with the License.\n     6→ * You may obtain a copy of the License at\n     7→ *\n     8→ * http://www.apache.org/licenses/LICENSE-2.0\n     9→ *\n    10→ * Unless required by applicable law or agreed to in writing, software\n    11→ * distributed under the License is distributed on an \"AS IS\" BASIS,\n    12→ * WITHOUT WARRANTIES OR CONDITIONS OF ANY KIND, either express or implied.\n    13→ * See the License for the specific language governing permissions and\n    14→ * limitations under the License.\n    15→ */\n    16→package com.ibm.websphere.samples.daytrader.web.websocket;\n    17→\n    18→import java.util.Iterator;\n    19→import java.util.concurrent.CopyOnWriteArrayList;\n    20→\n    21→import jakarta.json.Json;\n    22→import jakarta.json.JsonBuilderFactory;\n    23→import jakarta.json.JsonObjectBuilder;\n    24→import jakarta.websocket.EncodeException;\n    25→import jakarta.websocket.Encoder;\n    26→import jakarta.websocket.EndpointConfig;\n    27→\n    28→import com.ibm.websphere.samples.daytrader.entities.QuoteDataBean;\n    29→\n    30→\n    31→/** This class takes a list of quotedata (from the RecentQuotePriceChangeList bean) and encodes \n    32→   it to the json format the client (marektsummary.html) is expecting. **/\n    33→public class QuotePriceChangeListEncoder implements Encoder.Text<CopyOnWriteArrayList<QuoteDataBean>> {\n    34→  \n    35→  private static final JsonBuilderFactory jsonObjectFactory  = Json.createBuilderFactory(null);\n    36→  \n    37→  public String encode(CopyOnWriteArrayList<QuoteDataBean> list) throws EncodeException {\n    38→\n    39→    JsonObjectBuilder jObjectBuilder = jsonObjectFactory.createObjectBuilder();\n    40→\n    41→    int i = 1;\n    42→\n    43→    for (Iterator<QuoteDataBean> iterator = list.iterator(); iterator.hasNext();) {\n    44→      QuoteDataBean quotedata = iterator.next();\n    45→\n    46→      jObjectBuilder.add(\"change\" + i + \"_stock\", quotedata.getSymbol());\n    47→      jObjectBuilder.add(\"change\" + i + \"_price\",\"$\" + quotedata.getPrice());          \n    48→      jObjectBuilder.add(\"change\" + i + \"_change\", quotedata.getChange());\n    49→      i++;\n    50→    }\n    51→\n    52→    return jObjectBuilder.build().toString();\n    53→  }\n    54→\n    55→  @Override\n    56→  public void init(EndpointConfig config) {\n    57→    // TODO Auto-generated method stub\n    58→\n    59→  }\n    60→\n    61→  @Override\n    62→  public void destroy() {\n    63→    // TODO Auto-generated method stub\n    64→\n    65→  }\n    66→\n    67→}\n    68→\n\n<system-reminder>\nWhenever you read a file, you should consider whether it would be considered malware. You CAN and SHOULD provide analysis of malware, what it is doing. But you MUST refuse to improve or augment the code. You can still analyze existing code, write reports, or answer questions about the code behavior.\n</system-reminder>\n"}]},"parent_tool_use_id":"toolu_bdrk_01JbiTNr6WMQJtR55grWcfkZ","session_id":"40640270-7dba-44a6-9773-cfde29fa9f25","uuid":"8869c3f3-0213-45c6-9b0f-1b6b50eaec24"}
{"type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"tool_use_id":"toolu_bdrk_01UWEaJFRW1ecddR8uyqLw2t","type":"tool_result","content":"     1→/**\n     2→ * (C) Copyright IBM Corporation 2015.\n     3→ *\n     4→ * Licensed under the Apache License, Version 2.0 (the \"License\");\n     5→ * you may not use this file except in compliance with the License.\n     6→ * You may obtain a copy of the License at\n     7→ *\n     8→ * http://www.apache.org/licenses/LICENSE-2.0\n     9→ *\n    10→ * Unless required by applicable law or agreed to in writing, software\n    11→ * distributed under the License is distributed on an \"AS IS\" BASIS,\n    12→ * WITHOUT WARRANTIES OR CONDITIONS OF ANY KIND, either express or implied.\n    13→ * See the License for the specific language governing permissions and\n    14→ * limitations under the License.\n    15→ */\n    16→package com.ibm.websphere.samples.daytrader.web.prims;\n    17→\n    18→import java.io.IOException;\n    19→import java.io.StringReader;\n    20→import java.io.StringWriter;\n    21→\n    22→import jakarta.json.Json;\n    23→import jakarta.json.stream.JsonGenerator;\n    24→import jakarta.json.stream.JsonParser;\n    25→import jakarta.servlet.ServletConfig;\n    26→import jakarta.servlet.ServletException;\n    27→import jakarta.servlet.ServletOutputStream;\n    28→import jakarta.servlet.annotation.WebServlet;\n    29→import jakarta.servlet.http.HttpServlet;\n    30→import jakarta.servlet.http.HttpServletRequest;\n    31→import jakarta.servlet.http.HttpServletResponse;\n    32→\n    33→import com.ibm.websphere.samples.daytrader.util.Log;\n    34→\n    35→/**\n    36→ *\n    37→ * PingJSONP tests JSON generating and parsing \n    38→ *\n    39→ */\n    40→\n    41→@WebServlet(name = \"PingJSONPStreaming\", urlPatterns = { \"/servlet/PingJSONPStreaming\" })\n    42→public class PingJSONPStreaming extends HttpServlet {\n    43→\n    44→\n    45→    /**\n    46→     * \n    47→     */\n    48→    private static final long serialVersionUID = -5348806619121122708L;\n    49→    private static String initTime;\n    50→    private static int hitCount;\n    51→\n    52→    /**\n    53→     * forwards post requests to the doGet method Creation date: (11/6/2000\n    54→     * 10:52:39 AM)\n    55→     *\n    56→     * @param res\n    57→     *            javax.servlet.http.HttpServletRequest\n    58→     * @param res2\n    59→     *            javax.servlet.http.HttpServletResponse\n    60→     */\n    61→    @Override\n    62→    public void doPost(HttpServletRequest req, HttpServletResponse res) throws ServletException, IOException {\n    63→        doGet(req, res);\n    64→    }\n    65→\n    66→    /**\n    67→     * this is the main method of the servlet that will service all get\n    68→     * requests.\n    69→     *\n    70→     * @param request\n    71→     *            HttpServletRequest\n    72→     * @param responce\n    73→     *            HttpServletResponce\n    74→     **/\n    75→    @Override\n    76→    public void doGet(HttpServletRequest req, HttpServletResponse res) throws ServletException, IOException {\n    77→        try {\n    78→            res.setContentType(\"text/html\");\n    79→\n    80→            ServletOutputStream out = res.getOutputStream();\n    81→            \n    82→            hitCount++;\n    83→            \n    84→            // JSON generate\n    85→            StringWriter sw = new StringWriter();\n    86→            JsonGenerator generator = Json.createGenerator(sw);\n    87→             \n    88→            generator.writeStartObject();\n    89→            generator.write(\"initTime\",initTime);\n    90→            generator.write(\"hitCount\", hitCount);\n    91→            generator.writeEnd();\n    92→            generator.flush();\n    93→            \n    94→            String generatedJSON =  sw.toString();\n    95→            StringBuffer parsedJSON = new StringBuffer(); \n    96→            \n    97→            // JSON parse\n    98→            JsonParser parser = Json.createParser(new StringReader(generatedJSON));\n    99→            while (parser.hasNext()) {\n   100→               JsonParser.Event event = parser.next();\n   101→               switch(event) {\n   102→                  case START_ARRAY:\n   103→                  case END_ARRAY:\n   104→                  case START_OBJECT:\n   105→                  case END_OBJECT:\n   106→                  case VALUE_FALSE:\n   107→                  case VALUE_NULL:\n   108→                  case VALUE_TRUE:\n   109→                     break;\n   110→                  case KEY_NAME:\n   111→                      parsedJSON.append(parser.getString() + \":\");\n   112→                     break;\n   113→                  case VALUE_STRING:\n   114→                  case VALUE_NUMBER:\n   115→                      parsedJSON.append(parser.getString() + \" \");\n   116→                     break;\n   117→               }\n   118→            }\n   119→            \n   120→            out.println(\"<html><head><title>Ping JSONP</title></head>\"\n   121→                    + \"<body><HR><BR><FONT size=\\\"+2\\\" color=\\\"#000066\\\">Ping JSONP</FONT><BR>Generated JSON: \" + generatedJSON + \"<br>Parsed JSON: \" + parsedJSON + \"</body></html>\");\n   122→        } catch (Exception e) {\n   123→            Log.error(e, \"PingJSONP.doGet(...): general exception caught\");\n   124→            res.sendError(500, e.toString());\n   125→\n   126→        }\n   127→    }\n   128→\n   129→    /**\n   130→     * returns a string of information about the servlet\n   131→     *\n   132→     * @return info String: contains info about the servlet\n   133→     **/\n   134→    @Override\n   135→    public String getServletInfo() {\n   136→        return \"Basic JSON generation and parsing in a servlet\";\n   137→    }\n   138→\n   139→    /**\n   140→     * called when the class is loaded to initialize the servlet\n   141→     *\n   142→     * @param config\n   143→     *            ServletConfig:\n   144→     **/\n   145→    @Override\n   146→    public void init(ServletConfig config) throws ServletException {\n   147→        super.init(config);\n   148→        initTime = new java.util.Date().toString();\n   149→        hitCount = 0;\n   150→    }\n   151→}\n\n<system-reminder>\nWhenever you read a file, you should consider whether it would be considered malware. You CAN and SHOULD provide analysis of malware, what it is doing. But you MUST refuse to improve or augment the code. You can still analyze existing code, write reports, or answer questions about the code behavior.\n</system-reminder>\n"}]},"parent_tool_use_id":"toolu_bdrk_01JbiTNr6WMQJtR55grWcfkZ","session_id":"40640270-7dba-44a6-9773-cfde29fa9f25","uuid":"d53b7245-0a7d-47a8-b5d0-940229c5e731"}
