{"type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"tool_use_id":"toolu_bdrk_01LsdVFwY2vs3z9s4c4QgJZu","type":"tool_result","content":"     1→/**\n     2→ * (C) Copyright IBM Corporation 2015.\n     3→ *\n     4→ * Licensed under the Apache License, Version 2.0 (the \"License\");\n     5→ * you may not use this file except in compliance with the License.\n     6→ * You may obtain a copy of the License at\n     7→ *\n     8→ * http://www.apache.org/licenses/LICENSE-2.0\n     9→ *\n    10→ * Unless required by applicable law or agreed to in writing, software\n    11→ * distributed under the License is distributed on an \"AS IS\" BASIS,\n    12→ * WITHOUT WARRANTIES OR CONDITIONS OF ANY KIND, either express or implied.\n    13→ * See the License for the specific language governing permissions and\n    14→ * limitations under the License.\n    15→ */\n    16→package com.ibm.websphere.samples.daytrader.web.servlet;\n    17→\n    18→import static javax.faces.annotation.FacesConfig.Version.JSF_2_3;\n    19→\n    20→import java.io.InputStream;\n    21→import java.util.Properties;\n    22→\n    23→import jakarta.faces.annotation.FacesConfig;\n    24→import jakarta.servlet.ServletContextEvent;\n    25→import jakarta.servlet.ServletContextListener;\n    26→import jakarta.servlet.annotation.WebListener;\n    27→\n    28→import com.ibm.websphere.samples.daytrader.util.Log;\n    29→import com.ibm.websphere.samples.daytrader.util.TradeConfig;\n    30→\n    31→@WebListener()\n    32→@FacesConfig(version = JSF_2_3)\n    33→public class TradeWebContextListener implements ServletContextListener {\n    34→  \n    35→  \n    36→  \n    37→    // receieve trade web app startup/shutown events to start(initialized)/stop\n    38→    // TradeDirect\n    39→    @Override\n    40→    public void contextInitialized(ServletContextEvent event) {\n    41→      Log.trace(\"TradeWebContextListener contextInitialized -- initializing TradeDirect\");\n    42→        \n    43→      // Load settings from properties file (if it exists)\n    44→      Properties prop = new Properties();\n    45→      InputStream stream =  event.getServletContext().getResourceAsStream(\"/properties/daytrader.properties\");\n    46→        \n    47→      try {\n    48→        prop.load(stream);\n    49→        System.out.println(\"Settings from daytrader.properties: \" + prop);\n    50→        \n    51→        if (System.getenv(\"RUNTIME_MODE\") != null) {\n    52→          TradeConfig.setRunTimeMode(Integer.parseInt(System.getenv(\"RUNTIME_MODE\")));\n    53→        } else {\n    54→          TradeConfig.setRunTimeMode(Integer.parseInt(prop.getProperty(\"runtimeMode\")));\n    55→        }\n    56→        System.out.print(\"Running in \" + TradeConfig.getRunTimeModeNames()[TradeConfig.getRunTimeMode()] + \" Mode\");\n    57→            \n    58→        if (System.getenv(\"ORDER_PROCESSING_MODE\") != null) {\n    59→          TradeConfig.setOrderProcessingMode(Integer.parseInt(System.getenv(\"ORDER_PROCESSING_MODE\")));\n    60→        } else {\n    61→          TradeConfig.setOrderProcessingMode(Integer.parseInt(prop.getProperty(\"orderProcessingMode\")));\n    62→        }\n    63→        System.out.print(\"Running in \" + TradeConfig.getOrderProcessingModeNames()[TradeConfig.getOrderProcessingMode()] + \" Order Processing Mode\");  \n    64→        \n    65→        if (System.getenv(\"MAX_USERS\") != null) {\n    66→          TradeConfig.setMAX_USERS(Integer.parseInt(System.getenv(\"MAX_USERS\")));\n    67→        } else {\n    68→          TradeConfig.setMAX_USERS(Integer.parseInt(prop.getProperty(\"maxUsers\")));\n    69→        }\n    70→        System.out.print(\"MAX_USERS = \" +  TradeConfig.getMAX_USERS() + \" users\");\n    71→        \n    72→        if (System.getenv(\"MAX_QUOTES\") != null) {\n    73→          TradeConfig.setMAX_QUOTES(Integer.parseInt(System.getenv(\"MAX_QUOTES\")));\n    74→        } else {\n    75→          TradeConfig.setMAX_QUOTES(Integer.parseInt(prop.getProperty(\"maxQuotes\")));\n    76→        }\n    77→        System.out.print(\"MAX_QUOTES = \" +  TradeConfig.getMAX_QUOTES() + \" quotes\");\n    78→       \n    79→        if (System.getenv(\"PUBLISH_QUOTES\") != null) {\n    80→          TradeConfig.setPublishQuotePriceChange(Boolean.parseBoolean(System.getenv(\"PUBLISH_QUOTES\")));\n    81→        } else {\n    82→          TradeConfig.setPublishQuotePriceChange(Boolean.parseBoolean(prop.getProperty(\"publishQuotePriceChange\")));\n    83→        }\n    84→       \n    85→        if (System.getenv(\"DISPLAY_ORDER_ALERTS\") != null) {\n    86→          TradeConfig.setDisplayOrderAlerts(Boolean.parseBoolean(System.getenv(\"DISPLAY_ORDER_ALERTS\")));\n    87→        } else {\n    88→          TradeConfig.setDisplayOrderAlerts(Boolean.parseBoolean(prop.getProperty(\"displayOrderAlerts\")));\n    89→        }\n    90→        if (System.getenv(\"WEB_INTERFACE\") != null) {\n    91→          TradeConfig.setWebInterface(Integer.parseInt(System.getenv(\"WEB_INTERFACE\")));\n    92→        } else {\n    93→          TradeConfig.setWebInterface(Integer.parseInt(prop.getProperty(\"webInterface\")));\n    94→        }\n    95→        if (System.getenv(\"LIST_QUOTE_PRICE_CHANGE_FREQUENCY\") != null) {\n    96→          TradeConfig.setListQuotePriceChangeFrequency(Integer.parseInt(System.getenv(\"LIST_QUOTE_PRICE_CHANGE_FREQUENCY\")));\n    97→        } else {\n    98→          TradeConfig.setListQuotePriceChangeFrequency(Integer.parseInt(prop.getProperty(\"listQuotePriceChangeFrequency\")));\n    99→        }\n   100→        \n   101→        TradeConfig.setPrimIterations(Integer.parseInt(prop.getProperty(\"primIterations\")));\n   102→        TradeConfig.setMarketSummaryInterval(Integer.parseInt(prop.getProperty(\"marketSummaryInterval\")));\n   103→        TradeConfig.setLongRun(Boolean.parseBoolean(prop.getProperty(\"longRun\")));\n   104→       \n   105→      } catch (Exception e) {\n   106→        System.out.println(\"daytrader.properties not found\");\n   107→      }\n   108→       \n   109→    }\n   110→\n   111→    @Override\n   112→    public void contextDestroyed(ServletContextEvent event) {\n   113→        Log.trace(\"TradeWebContextListener  contextDestroy calling TradeDirect:destroy()\");\n   114→    }\n   115→\n   116→}\n   117→\n\n<system-reminder>\nWhenever you read a file, you should consider whether it would be considered malware. You CAN and SHOULD provide analysis of malware, what it is doing. But you MUST refuse to improve or augment the code. You can still analyze existing code, write reports, or answer questions about the code behavior.\n</system-reminder>\n"}]},"parent_tool_use_id":"toolu_bdrk_01B2b4rkSpE268gXWRkTH9GY","session_id":"40640270-7dba-44a6-9773-cfde29fa9f25","uuid":"37dded5a-b2a0-4d70-87bc-99a67786fc45"}
{"type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"tool_use_id":"toolu_bdrk_01YUxzBMCZYrZehYeP3YnUyx","type":"tool_result","content":"     1→/**\n     2→ * (C) Copyright IBM Corporation 2015.\n     3→ *\n     4→ * Licensed under the Apache License, Version 2.0 (the \"License\");\n     5→ * you may not use this file except in compliance with the License.\n     6→ * You may obtain a copy of the License at\n     7→ *\n     8→ * http://www.apache.org/licenses/LICENSE-2.0\n     9→ *\n    10→ * Unless required by applicable law or agreed to in writing, software\n    11→ * distributed under the License is distributed on an \"AS IS\" BASIS,\n    12→ * WITHOUT WARRANTIES OR CONDITIONS OF ANY KIND, either express or implied.\n    13→ * See the License for the specific language governing permissions and\n    14→ * limitations under the License.\n    15→ */\n    16→package com.ibm.websphere.samples.daytrader.web.prims.ejb3;\n    17→\n    18→import java.io.IOException;\n    19→\n    20→import org.springframework.stereotype.EJB;\n    21→import org.springframework.beans.factory.annotation.Autowired;\n    22→import jakarta.servlet.ServletConfig;\n    23→import jakarta.servlet.ServletException;\n    24→import jakarta.servlet.annotation.WebServlet;\n    25→import jakarta.servlet.http.HttpServlet;\n    26→import jakarta.servlet.http.HttpServletRequest;\n    27→import jakarta.servlet.http.HttpServletResponse;\n    28→\n    29→import com.ibm.websphere.samples.daytrader.entities.AccountProfileDataBean;\n    30→import com.ibm.websphere.samples.daytrader.impl.ejb3.TradeSLSBBean;\n    31→import com.ibm.websphere.samples.daytrader.interfaces.TradeEJB;\n    32→import com.ibm.websphere.samples.daytrader.interfaces.TradeServices;\n    33→import com.ibm.websphere.samples.daytrader.util.Log;\n    34→import com.ibm.websphere.samples.daytrader.util.TradeConfig;\n    35→\n    36→/**\n    37→ * Primitive to test Entity Container Managed Relationshiop One to One Servlet\n    38→ * will generate a random userID and get the profile for that user using a\n    39→ * {@link trade.Account} Entity EJB This tests the common path of a Servlet\n    40→ * calling a Session to Entity EJB to get CMR One to One data\n    41→ *\n    42→ */\n    43→@WebServlet(name = \"ejb3.PingServlet2Session2CMR2One2One\", urlPatterns = { \"/ejb3/PingServlet2Session2CMROne2One\" })\n    44→public class PingServlet2Session2CMROne2One extends HttpServlet {\n    45→    private static final long serialVersionUID = 567062418489199248L;\n    46→\n    47→    private static String initTime;\n    48→\n    49→    private static int hitCount;\n    50→\n    51→    @Autowired\n    52→    @TradeEJB\n    53→    private TradeServices tradeSLSBLocal;\n    54→    \n    55→    @Override\n    56→    public void doPost(HttpServletRequest req, HttpServletResponse res) throws ServletException, IOException {\n    57→        doGet(req, res);\n    58→    }\n    59→\n    60→    @Override\n    61→    public void doGet(HttpServletRequest req, HttpServletResponse res) throws IOException, ServletException {\n    62→\n    63→        res.setContentType(\"text/html\");\n    64→        java.io.PrintWriter out = res.getWriter();\n    65→\n    66→        String userID = null;\n    67→\n    68→        StringBuffer output = new StringBuffer(100);\n    69→        output.append(\"<html><head><title>Servlet2Session2CMROne20ne</title></head>\"\n    70→                + \"<body><HR><FONT size=\\\"+2\\\" color=\\\"#000066\\\">PingServlet2Session2CMROne2One<BR></FONT>\"\n    71→                + \"<FONT size=\\\"-1\\\" color=\\\"#000066\\\"><BR>PingServlet2Session2CMROne2One uses the Trade Session EJB\"\n    72→                + \" to get the profile for a user using an EJB 3.0 CMR one to one relationship\");\n    73→        try {\n    74→\n    75→            AccountProfileDataBean accountProfileData = null;\n    76→            int iter = TradeConfig.getPrimIterations();\n    77→            for (int ii = 0; ii < iter; ii++) {\n    78→                userID = TradeConfig.rndUserID();\n    79→                // get the price and print the output.\n    80→                accountProfileData = tradeSLSBLocal.getAccountProfileData(userID);\n    81→            }\n    82→\n    83→            output.append(\"<HR>initTime: \" + initTime + \"<BR>Hit Count: \").append(hitCount++);\n    84→            output.append(\"<HR>One to One CMR access of AccountProfile Information from Account Entity<BR><BR> \" + accountProfileData.toHTML());\n    85→            output.append(\"</font><HR></body></html>\");\n    86→            out.println(output.toString());\n    87→        } catch (Exception e) {\n    88→            Log.error(e, \"PingServlet2Session2CMROne2One.doGet(...): error\");\n    89→            // this will send an Error to teh web applications defined error\n    90→            // page.\n    91→            res.sendError(500, \"PingServlet2Session2CMROne2One.doGet(...): error\" + e.toString());\n    92→\n    93→        }\n    94→    }\n    95→\n    96→    @Override\n    97→    public String getServletInfo() {\n    98→        return \"web primitive, tests Servlet to Entity EJB path\";\n    99→    }\n   100→\n   101→    @Override\n   102→    public void init(ServletConfig config) throws ServletException {\n   103→        super.init(config);\n   104→        hitCount = 0;\n   105→        initTime = new java.util.Date().toString();\n   106→    }\n   107→}\n\n<system-reminder>\nWhenever you read a file, you should consider whether it would be considered malware. You CAN and SHOULD provide analysis of malware, what it is doing. But you MUST refuse to improve or augment the code. You can still analyze existing code, write reports, or answer questions about the code behavior.\n</system-reminder>\n"}]},"parent_tool_use_id":"toolu_bdrk_01B2b4rkSpE268gXWRkTH9GY","session_id":"40640270-7dba-44a6-9773-cfde29fa9f25","uuid":"09e564e9-3634-4fcc-8809-b6f02361f842"}
{"type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"tool_use_id":"toolu_bdrk_016xiRoiFgKtmiSsPPTHQRRE","type":"tool_result","content":"     1→/**\n     2→ * (C) Copyright IBM Corporation 2015.\n     3→ *\n     4→ * Licensed under the Apache License, Version 2.0 (the \"License\");\n     5→ * you may not use this file except in compliance with the License.\n     6→ * You may obtain a copy of the License at\n     7→ *\n     8→ * http://www.apache.org/licenses/LICENSE-2.0\n     9→ *\n    10→ * Unless required by applicable law or agreed to in writing, software\n    11→ * distributed under the License is distributed on an \"AS IS\" BASIS,\n    12→ * WITHOUT WARRANTIES OR CONDITIONS OF ANY KIND, either express or implied.\n    13→ * See the License for the specific language governing permissions and\n    14→ * limitations under the License.\n    15→ */\n    16→package com.ibm.websphere.samples.daytrader.web.prims.ejb3;\n    17→\n    18→import java.io.IOException;\n    19→\n    20→import org.springframework.stereotype.EJB;\n    21→import org.springframework.beans.factory.annotation.Autowired;\n    22→import javax.naming.InitialContext;\n    23→import jakarta.servlet.ServletConfig;\n    24→import jakarta.servlet.ServletException;\n    25→import jakarta.servlet.annotation.WebServlet;\n    26→import jakarta.servlet.http.HttpServlet;\n    27→import jakarta.servlet.http.HttpServletRequest;\n    28→import jakarta.servlet.http.HttpServletResponse;\n    29→\n    30→import com.ibm.websphere.samples.daytrader.entities.QuoteDataBean;\n    31→import com.ibm.websphere.samples.daytrader.impl.ejb3.TradeSLSBBean;\n    32→import com.ibm.websphere.samples.daytrader.interfaces.TradeEJB;\n    33→import com.ibm.websphere.samples.daytrader.interfaces.TradeServices;\n    34→import com.ibm.websphere.samples.daytrader.util.Log;\n    35→import com.ibm.websphere.samples.daytrader.util.TradeConfig;\n    36→\n    37→/**\n    38→ *\n    39→ * PingServlet2Session2Entity tests key functionality of a servlet call to a\n    40→ * stateless SessionEJB, and then to a Entity EJB representing data in a\n    41→ * database. This servlet makes use of the Stateless Session EJB {@link Trade},\n    42→ * and then uses {@link TradeConfig} to generate a random stock symbol. The\n    43→ * stocks price is looked up using the Quote Entity EJB.\n    44→ *\n    45→ */\n    46→@WebServlet(name = \"ejb3.PingServlet2Session2Entity\", urlPatterns = { \"/ejb3/PingServlet2Session2Entity\" })\n    47→public class PingServlet2Session2Entity extends HttpServlet {\n    48→\n    49→    private static final long serialVersionUID = -5043457201022265012L;\n    50→\n    51→    private static String initTime;\n    52→\n    53→    private static int hitCount;\n    54→\n    55→    @Autowired\n    56→    @TradeEJB\n    57→    private TradeServices tradeSLSBLocal;\n    58→\n    59→    @Override\n    60→    public void doPost(HttpServletRequest req, HttpServletResponse res) throws ServletException, IOException {\n    61→        doGet(req, res);\n    62→    }\n    63→\n    64→    @Override\n    65→    public void doGet(HttpServletRequest req, HttpServletResponse res) throws IOException, ServletException {\n    66→\n    67→        res.setContentType(\"text/html\");\n    68→        java.io.PrintWriter out = res.getWriter();\n    69→        String symbol = null;\n    70→        QuoteDataBean quoteData = null;\n    71→        StringBuffer output = new StringBuffer(100);\n    72→\n    73→        output.append(\"<html><head><title>PingServlet2Session2Entity</title></head>\"\n    74→                + \"<body><HR><FONT size=\\\"+2\\\" color=\\\"#000066\\\">PingServlet2Session2Entity<BR></FONT>\" + \"<FONT size=\\\"-1\\\" color=\\\"#000066\\\">\"\n    75→                + \"PingServlet2Session2Entity tests the common path of a Servlet calling a Session EJB \" + \"which in turn calls an Entity EJB.<BR>\");\n    76→\n    77→        try {\n    78→            try {\n    79→                int iter = TradeConfig.getPrimIterations();\n    80→                for (int ii = 0; ii < iter; ii++) {\n    81→                    symbol = TradeConfig.rndSymbol();\n    82→                    // getQuote will call findQuote which will instaniate the\n    83→                    // Quote Entity Bean\n    84→                    // and then will return a QuoteObject\n    85→                    quoteData = tradeSLSBLocal.getQuote(symbol);\n    86→                }\n    87→            } catch (Exception ne) {\n    88→                Log.error(ne, \"PingServlet2Session2Entity.goGet(...): exception getting QuoteData through Trade\");\n    89→                throw ne;\n    90→            }\n    91→\n    92→            output.append(\"<HR>initTime: \" + initTime).append(\"<BR>Hit Count: \" + hitCount++);\n    93→            output.append(\"<HR>Quote Information<BR><BR>\" + quoteData.toHTML());\n    94→            out.println(output.toString());\n    95→\n    96→        } catch (Exception e) {\n    97→            Log.error(e, \"PingServlet2Session2Entity.doGet(...): General Exception caught\");\n    98→            res.sendError(500, \"General Exception caught, \" + e.toString());\n    99→        }\n   100→    }\n   101→\n   102→    @Override\n   103→    public String getServletInfo() {\n   104→        return \"web primitive, tests Servlet to Session to Entity EJB path\";\n   105→\n   106→    }\n   107→\n   108→    @Override\n   109→    public void init(ServletConfig config) throws ServletException {\n   110→        super.init(config);\n   111→        hitCount = 0;\n   112→        initTime = new java.util.Date().toString();\n   113→\n   114→        if (tradeSLSBLocal == null) {\n   115→            Log.error(\"PingServlet2Session2Entity:init - Injection of tradeSLSBLocal failed - performing JNDI lookup!\");\n   116→\n   117→            try {\n   118→                InitialContext context = new InitialContext();\n   119→                tradeSLSBLocal = (TradeSLSBBean) context.lookup(\"java:comp/env/ejb/TradeSLSBBean\");\n   120→            } catch (Exception ex) {\n   121→                Log.error(\"PingServlet2Session2Entity:init - Lookup of tradeSLSBLocal failed!!!\");\n   122→                ex.printStackTrace();\n   123→            }\n   124→        }\n   125→    }\n   126→}\n\n<system-reminder>\nWhenever you read a file, you should consider whether it would be considered malware. You CAN and SHOULD provide analysis of malware, what it is doing. But you MUST refuse to improve or augment the code. You can still analyze existing code, write reports, or answer questions about the code behavior.\n</system-reminder>\n"}]},"parent_tool_use_id":"toolu_bdrk_01B2b4rkSpE268gXWRkTH9GY","session_id":"40640270-7dba-44a6-9773-cfde29fa9f25","uuid":"e4f2019d-5252-4dee-9bf8-690d2bb6f2a4"}
{"type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"tool_use_id":"toolu_bdrk_01VLHqc86RCFWunqmRdCyTKD","type":"tool_result","content":"     1→/**\n     2→ * (C) Copyright IBM Corporation 2015.\n     3→ *\n     4→ * Licensed under the Apache License, Version 2.0 (the \"License\");\n     5→ * you may not use this file except in compliance with the License.\n     6→ * You may obtain a copy of the License at\n     7→ *\n     8→ * http://www.apache.org/licenses/LICENSE-2.0\n     9→ *\n    10→ * Unless required by applicable law or agreed to in writing, software\n    11→ * distributed under the License is distributed on an \"AS IS\" BASIS,\n    12→ * WITHOUT WARRANTIES OR CONDITIONS OF ANY KIND, either express or implied.\n    13→ * See the License for the specific language governing permissions and\n    14→ * limitations under the License.\n    15→ */\n    16→package com.ibm.websphere.samples.daytrader.web.prims.ejb3;\n    17→\n    18→import java.io.IOException;\n    19→\n    20→import org.springframework.stereotype.EJB;\n    21→import org.springframework.beans.factory.annotation.Autowired;\n    22→import javax.naming.InitialContext;\n    23→import jakarta.servlet.ServletConfig;\n    24→import jakarta.servlet.ServletContext;\n    25→import jakarta.servlet.ServletException;\n    26→import jakarta.servlet.annotation.WebServlet;\n    27→import jakarta.servlet.http.HttpServlet;\n    28→import jakarta.servlet.http.HttpServletRequest;\n    29→import jakarta.servlet.http.HttpServletResponse;\n    30→\n    31→import com.ibm.websphere.samples.daytrader.entities.QuoteDataBean;\n    32→import com.ibm.websphere.samples.daytrader.impl.ejb3.TradeSLSBBean;\n    33→import com.ibm.websphere.samples.daytrader.interfaces.TradeEJB;\n    34→import com.ibm.websphere.samples.daytrader.interfaces.TradeServices;\n    35→import com.ibm.websphere.samples.daytrader.util.Log;\n    36→import com.ibm.websphere.samples.daytrader.util.TradeConfig;\n    37→\n    38→/**\n    39→ *\n    40→ * PingServlet2Session2Entity tests key functionality of a servlet call to a\n    41→ * stateless SessionEJB, and then to a Entity EJB representing data in a\n    42→ * database. This servlet makes use of the Stateless Session EJB {@link Trade},\n    43→ * and then uses {@link TradeConfig} to generate a random stock symbol. The\n    44→ * stocks price is looked up using the Quote Entity EJB.\n    45→ *\n    46→ */\n    47→@WebServlet(name = \"ejb3.PingServlet2Session2Entity2JSP\", urlPatterns = { \"/ejb3/PingServlet2Session2Entity2JSP\" })\n    48→public class PingServlet2Session2Entity2JSP extends HttpServlet {\n    49→\n    50→    private static final long serialVersionUID = -8966014710582651693L;\n    51→\n    52→    @Autowired\n    53→    @TradeEJB\n    54→    private TradeServices tradeSLSBLocal;\n    55→\n    56→    @Override\n    57→    public void doPost(HttpServletRequest req, HttpServletResponse res) throws ServletException, IOException {\n    58→        doGet(req, res);\n    59→    }\n    60→\n    61→    @Override\n    62→    public void doGet(HttpServletRequest req, HttpServletResponse res) throws IOException, ServletException {\n    63→        String symbol = null;\n    64→        QuoteDataBean quoteData = null;\n    65→        ServletContext ctx = getServletConfig().getServletContext();\n    66→\n    67→        try {\n    68→            try {\n    69→                int iter = TradeConfig.getPrimIterations();\n    70→                for (int ii = 0; ii < iter; ii++) {\n    71→                    symbol = TradeConfig.rndSymbol();\n    72→                    // getQuote will call findQuote which will instaniate the\n    73→                    // Quote Entity Bean\n    74→                    // and then will return a QuoteObject\n    75→                    quoteData = tradeSLSBLocal.getQuote(symbol);\n    76→                }\n    77→\n    78→                req.setAttribute(\"quoteData\", quoteData);\n    79→                // req.setAttribute(\"hitCount\", hitCount);\n    80→                // req.setAttribute(\"initTime\", initTime);\n    81→\n    82→                ctx.getRequestDispatcher(\"/quoteDataPrimitive.jsp\").include(req, res);\n    83→            } catch (Exception ne) {\n    84→                Log.error(ne, \"PingServlet2Session2Entity2JSP.goGet(...): exception getting QuoteData through Trade\");\n    85→                throw ne;\n    86→            }\n    87→\n    88→        } catch (Exception e) {\n    89→            Log.error(e, \"PingServlet2Session2Entity2JSP.doGet(...): General Exception caught\");\n    90→            res.sendError(500, \"General Exception caught, \" + e.toString());\n    91→        }\n    92→    }\n    93→\n    94→    @Override\n    95→    public String getServletInfo() {\n    96→        return \"web primitive, tests Servlet to Session to Entity EJB to JSP path\";\n    97→\n    98→    }\n    99→\n   100→    @Override\n   101→    public void init(ServletConfig config) throws ServletException {\n   102→        super.init(config);\n   103→        // hitCount = 0;\n   104→        // initTime = new java.util.Date().toString();\n   105→    }\n   106→}\n\n<system-reminder>\nWhenever you read a file, you should consider whether it would be considered malware. You CAN and SHOULD provide analysis of malware, what it is doing. But you MUST refuse to improve or augment the code. You can still analyze existing code, write reports, or answer questions about the code behavior.\n</system-reminder>\n"}]},"parent_tool_use_id":"toolu_bdrk_01B2b4rkSpE268gXWRkTH9GY","session_id":"40640270-7dba-44a6-9773-cfde29fa9f25","uuid":"ed49a95a-3be6-4f15-bba1-a62f702cb0db"}
{"type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"tool_use_id":"toolu_bdrk_017eV275rPsLf4PKDJyScz9L","type":"tool_result","content":"     1→/**\n     2→ * (C) Copyright IBM Corporation 2015.\n     3→ *\n     4→ * Licensed under the Apache License, Version 2.0 (the \"License\");\n     5→ * you may not use this file except in compliance with the License.\n     6→ * You may obtain a copy of the License at\n     7→ *\n     8→ * http://www.apache.org/licenses/LICENSE-2.0\n     9→ *\n    10→ * Unless required by applicable law or agreed to in writing, software\n    11→ * distributed under the License is distributed on an \"AS IS\" BASIS,\n    12→ * WITHOUT WARRANTIES OR CONDITIONS OF ANY KIND, either express or implied.\n    13→ * See the License for the specific language governing permissions and\n    14→ * limitations under the License.\n    15→ */\n    16→package com.ibm.websphere.samples.daytrader.web.prims.ejb3;\n    17→\n    18→import java.io.IOException;\n    19→import java.util.Collection;\n    20→import java.util.Iterator;\n    21→\n    22→import org.springframework.stereotype.EJB;\n    23→import org.springframework.beans.factory.annotation.Autowired;\n    24→import jakarta.servlet.ServletConfig;\n    25→import jakarta.servlet.ServletException;\n    26→import jakarta.servlet.annotation.WebServlet;\n    27→import jakarta.servlet.http.HttpServlet;\n    28→import jakarta.servlet.http.HttpServletRequest;\n    29→import jakarta.servlet.http.HttpServletResponse;\n    30→\n    31→import com.ibm.websphere.samples.daytrader.entities.HoldingDataBean;\n    32→import com.ibm.websphere.samples.daytrader.impl.ejb3.TradeSLSBBean;\n    33→import com.ibm.websphere.samples.daytrader.interfaces.TradeEJB;\n    34→import com.ibm.websphere.samples.daytrader.interfaces.TradeServices;\n    35→import com.ibm.websphere.samples.daytrader.util.Log;\n    36→import com.ibm.websphere.samples.daytrader.util.TradeConfig;\n    37→\n    38→/**\n    39→ *\n    40→ * PingServlet2Session2Entity tests key functionality of a servlet call to a\n    41→ * stateless SessionEJB, and then to a Entity EJB representing data in a\n    42→ * database. This servlet makes use of the Stateless Session EJB {@link Trade},\n    43→ * and then uses {@link TradeConfig} to generate a random user. The users\n    44→ * portfolio is looked up using the Holding Entity EJB returnin a collection of\n    45→ * Holdings\n    46→ *\n    47→ */\n    48→@WebServlet(name = \"ejb3.PingServlet2Session2EntityCollection\", urlPatterns = { \"/ejb3/PingServlet2Session2EntityCollection\" })\n    49→public class PingServlet2Session2EntityCollection extends HttpServlet {\n    50→\n    51→    private static final long serialVersionUID = 6171380014749902308L;\n    52→\n    53→    private static String initTime;\n    54→\n    55→    private static int hitCount;\n    56→\n    57→    @Autowired\n    58→    @TradeEJB\n    59→     private TradeServices tradeSLSBLocal;\n    60→    \n    61→    @Override\n    62→    public void doPost(HttpServletRequest req, HttpServletResponse res) throws ServletException, IOException {\n    63→        doGet(req, res);\n    64→    }\n    65→\n    66→    @Override\n    67→    public void doGet(HttpServletRequest req, HttpServletResponse res) throws IOException, ServletException {\n    68→\n    69→        res.setContentType(\"text/html\");\n    70→        java.io.PrintWriter out = res.getWriter();\n    71→        String userID = null;\n    72→        Collection<?> holdingDataBeans = null;\n    73→        StringBuffer output = new StringBuffer(100);\n    74→\n    75→        output.append(\"<html><head><title>PingServlet2Session2EntityCollection</title></head>\"\n    76→                + \"<body><HR><FONT size=\\\"+2\\\" color=\\\"#000066\\\">PingServlet2Session2EntityCollection<BR></FONT>\" + \"<FONT size=\\\"-1\\\" color=\\\"#000066\\\">\"\n    77→                + \"PingServlet2Session2EntityCollection tests the common path of a Servlet calling a Session EJB \"\n    78→                + \"which in turn calls a finder on an Entity EJB returning a collection of Entity EJBs.<BR>\");\n    79→\n    80→        try {\n    81→\n    82→            try {\n    83→                int iter = TradeConfig.getPrimIterations();\n    84→                for (int ii = 0; ii < iter; ii++) {\n    85→                    userID = TradeConfig.rndUserID();\n    86→                    // getQuote will call findQuote which will instaniate the\n    87→                    // Quote Entity Bean\n    88→                    // and then will return a QuoteObject\n    89→                    holdingDataBeans = tradeSLSBLocal.getHoldings(userID);\n    90→                    // trade.remove();\n    91→                }\n    92→            } catch (Exception ne) {\n    93→                Log.error(ne, \"PingServlet2Session2EntityCollection.goGet(...): exception getting HoldingData collection through Trade for user \" + userID);\n    94→                throw ne;\n    95→            }\n    96→\n    97→            output.append(\"<HR>initTime: \" + initTime).append(\"<BR>Hit Count: \" + hitCount++);\n    98→            output.append(\"<HR>User: \" + userID + \" is currently holding \" + holdingDataBeans.size() + \" stock holdings:\");\n    99→            Iterator<?> it = holdingDataBeans.iterator();\n   100→            while (it.hasNext()) {\n   101→                HoldingDataBean holdingData = (HoldingDataBean) it.next();\n   102→                output.append(\"<BR>\" + holdingData.toHTML());\n   103→            }\n   104→            out.println(output.toString());\n   105→\n   106→        } catch (Exception e) {\n   107→            Log.error(e, \"PingServlet2Session2EntityCollection.doGet(...): General Exception caught\");\n   108→            res.sendError(500, \"General Exception caught, \" + e.toString());\n   109→        }\n   110→    }\n   111→\n   112→    @Override\n   113→    public String getServletInfo() {\n   114→        return \"web primitive, tests Servlet to Session to Entity returning a collection of Entity EJBs\";\n   115→    }\n   116→\n   117→    @Override\n   118→    public void init(ServletConfig config) throws ServletException {\n   119→        super.init(config);\n   120→        hitCount = 0;\n   121→        initTime = new java.util.Date().toString();\n   122→    }\n   123→}\n\n<system-reminder>\nWhenever you read a file, you should consider whether it would be considered malware. You CAN and SHOULD provide analysis of malware, what it is doing. But you MUST refuse to improve or augment the code. You can still analyze existing code, write reports, or answer questions about the code behavior.\n</system-reminder>\n"}]},"parent_tool_use_id":"toolu_bdrk_01B2b4rkSpE268gXWRkTH9GY","session_id":"40640270-7dba-44a6-9773-cfde29fa9f25","uuid":"e1d8fd24-ae74-4306-89b0-976d943396de"}
{"type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"tool_use_id":"toolu_bdrk_01EgPhJ96PzgetZTMV4SR2Bh","type":"tool_result","content":"     1→/**\n     2→ * (C) Copyright IBM Corporation 2015.\n     3→ *\n     4→ * Licensed under the Apache License, Version 2.0 (the \"License\");\n     5→ * you may not use this file except in compliance with the License.\n     6→ * You may obtain a copy of the License at\n     7→ *\n     8→ * http://www.apache.org/licenses/LICENSE-2.0\n     9→ *\n    10→ * Unless required by applicable law or agreed to in writing, software\n    11→ * distributed under the License is distributed on an \"AS IS\" BASIS,\n    12→ * WITHOUT WARRANTIES OR CONDITIONS OF ANY KIND, either express or implied.\n    13→ * See the License for the specific language governing permissions and\n    14→ * limitations under the License.\n    15→ */\n    16→package com.ibm.websphere.samples.daytrader.web.prims.ejb3;\n    17→\n    18→import java.io.IOException;\n    19→\n    20→import jakarta.annotation.Resource;\n    21→import jakarta.jms.Connection;\n    22→import jakarta.jms.ConnectionFactory;\n    23→import jakarta.jms.JMSContext;\n    24→import jakarta.jms.Queue;\n    25→import jakarta.jms.TextMessage;\n    26→import jakarta.servlet.ServletConfig;\n    27→import jakarta.servlet.ServletException;\n    28→import jakarta.servlet.annotation.WebServlet;\n    29→import jakarta.servlet.http.HttpServlet;\n    30→import jakarta.servlet.http.HttpServletRequest;\n    31→import jakarta.servlet.http.HttpServletResponse;\n    32→\n    33→import com.ibm.websphere.samples.daytrader.util.Log;\n    34→import com.ibm.websphere.samples.daytrader.util.TradeConfig;\n    35→\n    36→/**\n    37→ * This primitive is designed to run inside the TradeApplication and relies upon\n    38→ * the {@link com.ibm.websphere.samples.daytrader.util.TradeConfig} class to set\n    39→ * configuration parameters. PingServlet2MDBQueue tests key functionality of a\n    40→ * servlet call to a post a message to an MDB Queue. The TradeBrokerMDB receives\n    41→ * the message This servlet makes use of the MDB EJB\n    42→ * {@link com.ibm.websphere.samples.daytrader.ejb3.DTBroker3MDB} by posting a\n    43→ * message to the MDB Queue\n    44→ */\n    45→@WebServlet(name = \"ejb3.PingServlet2MDBQueue\", urlPatterns = { \"/ejb3/PingServlet2MDBQueue\" })\n    46→public class PingServlet2MDBQueue extends HttpServlet {\n    47→\n    48→    private static final long serialVersionUID = 2637271552188745216L;\n    49→\n    50→    private static String initTime;\n    51→\n    52→    private static int hitCount;\n    53→\n    54→    @Resource(name = \"jms/QueueConnectionFactory\", authenticationType = javax.annotation.Resource.AuthenticationType.APPLICATION)\n    55→    private ConnectionFactory queueConnectionFactory;\n    56→\n    57→    // TODO: Glassfish does not like this - change to lookup?\n    58→    @Resource(name = \"jms/TradeBrokerQueue\")\n    59→    private Queue tradeBrokerQueue;\n    60→\n    61→    @Override\n    62→    public void doPost(HttpServletRequest req, HttpServletResponse res) throws ServletException, IOException {\n    63→        doGet(req, res);\n    64→    }\n    65→\n    66→    @Override\n    67→    public void doGet(HttpServletRequest req, HttpServletResponse res) throws IOException, ServletException {\n    68→\n    69→        res.setContentType(\"text/html\");\n    70→        java.io.PrintWriter out = res.getWriter();\n    71→        // use a stringbuffer to avoid concatenation of Strings\n    72→        StringBuffer output = new StringBuffer(100);\n    73→        output.append(\"<html><head><title>PingServlet2MDBQueue</title></head>\"\n    74→                + \"<body><HR><FONT size=\\\"+2\\\" color=\\\"#000066\\\">PingServlet2MDBQueue<BR></FONT>\" + \"<FONT size=\\\"-1\\\" color=\\\"#000066\\\">\"\n    75→                + \"Tests the basic operation of a servlet posting a message to an EJB MDB through a JMS Queue.<BR>\"\n    76→                + \"<FONT color=\\\"red\\\"><B>Note:</B> Not intended for performance testing.</FONT>\");\n    77→\n    78→        try {\n    79→            Connection conn = queueConnectionFactory.createConnection();\n    80→\n    81→            try {\n    82→                TextMessage message = null;\n    83→                int iter = TradeConfig.getPrimIterations();\n    84→                for (int ii = 0; ii < iter; ii++) {\n    85→                    /*Session sess = conn.createSession(false, Session.AUTO_ACKNOWLEDGE);\n    86→                    try {\n    87→                        MessageProducer producer = sess.createProducer(tradeBrokerQueue);\n    88→\n    89→                        message = sess.createTextMessage();\n    90→\n    91→                        String command = \"ping\";\n    92→                        message.setStringProperty(\"command\", command);\n    93→                        message.setLongProperty(\"publishTime\", System.currentTimeMillis());\n    94→                        message.setText(\"Ping message for queue java:comp/env/jms/TradeBrokerQueue sent from PingServlet2MDBQueue at \" + new java.util.Date());\n    95→                        producer.send(message);\n    96→                    } finally {\n    97→                        sess.close();\n    98→                    }*/\n    99→                \t\n   100→                \tJMSContext context = queueConnectionFactory.createContext();\n   101→            \t\t\n   102→            \t\tmessage = context.createTextMessage();\n   103→\n   104→            \t\tmessage.setStringProperty(\"command\", \"ping\");\n   105→                    message.setLongProperty(\"publishTime\", System.currentTimeMillis());\n   106→                    message.setText(\"Ping message for queue java:comp/env/jms/TradeBrokerQueue sent from PingServlet2MDBQueue at \" + new java.util.Date());\n   107→              \t\t\n   108→            \t\tcontext.createProducer().send(tradeBrokerQueue, message);\n   109→                }\n   110→\n   111→                // write out the output\n   112→                output.append(\"<HR>initTime: \").append(initTime);\n   113→                output.append(\"<BR>Hit Count: \").append(hitCount++);\n   114→                output.append(\"<HR>Posted Text message to java:comp/env/jms/TradeBrokerQueue destination\");\n   115→                output.append(\"<BR>Message: \").append(message);\n   116→                output.append(\"<BR><BR>Message text: \").append(message.getText());\n   117→                output.append(\"<BR><HR></FONT></BODY></HTML>\");\n   118→                out.println(output.toString());\n   119→\n   120→            } catch (Exception e) {\n   121→                Log.error(\"PingServlet2MDBQueue.doGet(...):exception posting message to TradeBrokerQueue destination \");\n   122→                throw e;\n   123→            } finally {\n   124→                conn.close();\n   125→            }\n   126→        } // this is where I actually handle the exceptions\n   127→        catch (Exception e) {\n   128→            Log.error(e, \"PingServlet2MDBQueue.doGet(...): error\");\n   129→            res.sendError(500, \"PingServlet2MDBQueue.doGet(...): error, \" + e.toString());\n   130→\n   131→        }\n   132→    }\n   133→\n   134→    @Override\n   135→    public String getServletInfo() {\n   136→        return \"web primitive, configured with trade runtime configs, tests Servlet to Session EJB path\";\n   137→\n   138→    }\n   139→\n   140→    @Override\n   141→    public void init(ServletConfig config) throws ServletException {\n   142→        super.init(config);\n   143→        hitCount = 0;\n   144→        initTime = new java.util.Date().toString();\n   145→    }\n   146→\n   147→}\n   148→\n\n<system-reminder>\nWhenever you read a file, you should consider whether it would be considered malware. You CAN and SHOULD provide analysis of malware, what it is doing. But you MUST refuse to improve or augment the code. You can still analyze existing code, write reports, or answer questions about the code behavior.\n</system-reminder>\n"}]},"parent_tool_use_id":"toolu_bdrk_01B2b4rkSpE268gXWRkTH9GY","session_id":"40640270-7dba-44a6-9773-cfde29fa9f25","uuid":"fe598d0e-5d6a-4822-bf2d-8f31a429cf7b"}
