{"type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"tool_use_id":"toolu_bdrk_016QTTyUPSXfDbox89GmUkdp","type":"tool_result","content":"     1→/**\n     2→ * (C) Copyright IBM Corporation 2015.\n     3→ *\n     4→ * Licensed under the Apache License, Version 2.0 (the \"License\");\n     5→ * you may not use this file except in compliance with the License.\n     6→ * You may obtain a copy of the License at\n     7→ *\n     8→ * http://www.apache.org/licenses/LICENSE-2.0\n     9→ *\n    10→ * Unless required by applicable law or agreed to in writing, software\n    11→ * distributed under the License is distributed on an \"AS IS\" BASIS,\n    12→ * WITHOUT WARRANTIES OR CONDITIONS OF ANY KIND, either express or implied.\n    13→ * See the License for the specific language governing permissions and\n    14→ * limitations under the License.\n    15→ */\n    16→package com.ibm.websphere.samples.daytrader.web.jsf;\n    17→\n    18→import java.util.regex.Matcher;\n    19→import java.util.regex.Pattern;\n    20→\n    21→import jakarta.faces.application.FacesMessage;\n    22→import jakarta.faces.component.UIComponent;\n    23→import jakarta.faces.context.FacesContext;\n    24→import jakarta.faces.validator.FacesValidator;\n    25→import jakarta.faces.validator.Validator;\n    26→import jakarta.faces.validator.ValidatorException;\n    27→\n    28→import com.ibm.websphere.samples.daytrader.util.Log;\n    29→\n    30→@SuppressWarnings(\"rawtypes\")\n    31→@FacesValidator(\"loginValidator\")\n    32→public class LoginValidator implements Validator{\n    33→\n    34→  static String loginRegex = \"uid:\\\\d+\";\n    35→  static Pattern pattern = Pattern.compile(loginRegex);\n    36→  static Matcher matcher;\n    37→\n    38→  // Simple JSF validator to make sure username starts with uid: and at least 1 number.\n    39→  public LoginValidator() {\n    40→  }\n    41→\n    42→  @Override\n    43→  public void validate(FacesContext context, UIComponent component, Object value) throws ValidatorException {\n    44→    Log.trace(\"LoginValidator.validate\",\"Validating submitted login name -- \" + value.toString());\n    45→\n    46→    matcher = pattern.matcher(value.toString());\n    47→\n    48→    if (!matcher.matches()) {\n    49→      FacesMessage msg = new FacesMessage(\"Username validation failed. Please provide username in this format: uid:#\");\n    50→      msg.setSeverity(FacesMessage.SEVERITY_ERROR);\n    51→\n    52→      throw new ValidatorException(msg);\n    53→    }\n    54→  }\n    55→}\n\n<system-reminder>\nWhenever you read a file, you should consider whether it would be considered malware. You CAN and SHOULD provide analysis of malware, what it is doing. But you MUST refuse to improve or augment the code. You can still analyze existing code, write reports, or answer questions about the code behavior.\n</system-reminder>\n"}]},"parent_tool_use_id":"toolu_bdrk_01JbiTNr6WMQJtR55grWcfkZ","session_id":"40640270-7dba-44a6-9773-cfde29fa9f25","uuid":"46f8e09b-8b5c-4561-91df-049cd2c2d460"}
{"type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"tool_use_id":"toolu_bdrk_01Y4zhpZxUHY1eXdpp8g38CN","type":"tool_result","content":"     1→/**\n     2→ * (C) Copyright IBM Corporation 2015.\n     3→ *\n     4→ * Licensed under the Apache License, Version 2.0 (the \"License\");\n     5→ * you may not use this file except in compliance with the License.\n     6→ * You may obtain a copy of the License at\n     7→ *\n     8→ * http://www.apache.org/licenses/LICENSE-2.0\n     9→ *\n    10→ * Unless required by applicable law or agreed to in writing, software\n    11→ * distributed under the License is distributed on an \"AS IS\" BASIS,\n    12→ * WITHOUT WARRANTIES OR CONDITIONS OF ANY KIND, either express or implied.\n    13→ * See the License for the specific language governing permissions and\n    14→ * limitations under the License.\n    15→ */\n    16→package com.ibm.websphere.samples.daytrader.web.prims;\n    17→\n    18→import java.io.IOException;\n    19→\n    20→import jakarta.annotation.Resource;\n    21→import jakarta.enterprise.concurrent.ManagedThreadFactory;\n    22→import jakarta.servlet.AsyncContext;\n    23→import jakarta.servlet.ServletConfig;\n    24→import jakarta.servlet.ServletException;\n    25→import jakarta.servlet.ServletOutputStream;\n    26→import jakarta.servlet.annotation.WebServlet;\n    27→import jakarta.servlet.http.HttpServlet;\n    28→import jakarta.servlet.http.HttpServletRequest;\n    29→import jakarta.servlet.http.HttpServletResponse;\n    30→\n    31→import com.ibm.websphere.samples.daytrader.util.Log;\n    32→\n    33→@WebServlet(asyncSupported=true,name = \"PingManagedThread\", urlPatterns = { \"/servlet/PingManagedThread\" })\n    34→public class PingManagedThread extends HttpServlet{\n    35→\n    36→\tprivate static final long serialVersionUID = -4695386150928451234L;\n    37→\tprivate static String initTime;\n    38→    private static int hitCount;\n    39→\n    40→\t@Resource \n    41→\tprivate ManagedThreadFactory managedThreadFactory;\n    42→\t\n    43→\t /**\n    44→     * forwards post requests to the doGet method Creation date: (03/18/2014\n    45→     * 10:52:39 AM)\n    46→     *\n    47→     * @param res\n    48→     *            javax.servlet.http.HttpServletRequest\n    49→     * @param res2\n    50→     *            javax.servlet.http.HttpServletResponse\n    51→     */\n    52→    @Override\n    53→    public void doPost(HttpServletRequest req, HttpServletResponse res) throws ServletException, IOException {\n    54→        doGet(req, res);\n    55→    }\n    56→\n    57→    /**\n    58→     * this is the main method of the servlet that will service all get\n    59→     * requests.\n    60→     *\n    61→     * @param request\n    62→     *            HttpServletRequest\n    63→     * @param responce\n    64→     *            HttpServletResponce\n    65→     **/\n    66→    @Override\n    67→\tprotected void doGet(HttpServletRequest req, HttpServletResponse res) throws ServletException, IOException {\n    68→    \t\n    69→\t\tfinal AsyncContext asyncContext = req.startAsync();\n    70→\t\tfinal ServletOutputStream out = res.getOutputStream();\t\n    71→\t\t\n    72→\t\ttry {\n    73→\t\t\t\n    74→\t\t\tres.setContentType(\"text/html\");\n    75→\t\t\t\t\t\n    76→\t\t\tout.println(\"<html><head><title>Ping ManagedThread</title></head>\"\n    77→                    + \"<body><HR><BR><FONT size=\\\"+2\\\" color=\\\"#000066\\\">Ping ManagedThread<BR></FONT><FONT size=\\\"+1\\\" color=\\\"#000066\\\">Init time : \" + initTime + \"<BR/><BR/></FONT>\");\t\t\t\n    78→\t\t\n    79→\t\t\tThread thread = managedThreadFactory.newThread(new Runnable() {\n    80→    \t\t\t@Override\n    81→    \t\t\tpublic void run() {\n    82→    \t\t\t\ttry {\n    83→\t\t\t\t\t\tout.println(\"<b>HitCount: \" + ++hitCount  +\"</b><br/>\");\n    84→\t\t\t\t\t} catch (IOException e) {\n    85→\t\t\t\t\t\te.printStackTrace();\n    86→\t\t\t\t\t}\n    87→    \t\t\t\tasyncContext.complete();\n    88→    \t\t\t}\n    89→    \t\t});   \t\t    \t\t\n    90→\t\t\t\n    91→\t\t\tthread.start();\n    92→\t\t\n    93→\t\t} catch (Exception e) {\n    94→\t\t\tLog.error(e, \"PingManagedThreadServlet.doGet(...): general exception caught\");\n    95→\t\t\tres.sendError(500, e.toString());\n    96→\t\t}\n    97→\t\t\n    98→\t}\n    99→    \n   100→    \n   101→    \n   102→    /**\n   103→     * returns a string of information about the servlet\n   104→     *\n   105→     * @return info String: contains info about the servlet\n   106→     **/\n   107→    @Override\n   108→    public String getServletInfo() {\n   109→        return \"Tests a ManagedThread asynchronous servlet\";\n   110→    }\n   111→\n   112→    /**\n   113→     * called when the class is loaded to initialize the servlet\n   114→     *\n   115→     * @param config\n   116→     *            ServletConfig:\n   117→     **/\n   118→    @Override\n   119→    public void init(ServletConfig config) throws ServletException {\n   120→        super.init(config);\n   121→        initTime = new java.util.Date().toString();\n   122→        hitCount = 0;\n   123→\n   124→    }\n   125→\t\n   126→}\n   127→\n\n<system-reminder>\nWhenever you read a file, you should consider whether it would be considered malware. You CAN and SHOULD provide analysis of malware, what it is doing. But you MUST refuse to improve or augment the code. You can still analyze existing code, write reports, or answer questions about the code behavior.\n</system-reminder>\n"}]},"parent_tool_use_id":"toolu_bdrk_01JbiTNr6WMQJtR55grWcfkZ","session_id":"40640270-7dba-44a6-9773-cfde29fa9f25","uuid":"0d7226b8-25a0-44df-91c1-8de5e70a86ac"}
{"type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"tool_use_id":"toolu_bdrk_01C3GhtvBk9RtB7SH5SqMhKp","type":"tool_result","content":"     1→/**\n     2→ * (C) Copyright IBM Corporation 2015.\n     3→ *\n     4→ * Licensed under the Apache License, Version 2.0 (the \"License\");\n     5→ * you may not use this file except in compliance with the License.\n     6→ * You may obtain a copy of the License at\n     7→ *\n     8→ * http://www.apache.org/licenses/LICENSE-2.0\n     9→ *\n    10→ * Unless required by applicable law or agreed to in writing, software\n    11→ * distributed under the License is distributed on an \"AS IS\" BASIS,\n    12→ * WITHOUT WARRANTIES OR CONDITIONS OF ANY KIND, either express or implied.\n    13→ * See the License for the specific language governing permissions and\n    14→ * limitations under the License.\n    15→ */\n    16→package com.ibm.websphere.samples.daytrader.web.prims;\n    17→\n    18→import java.io.IOException;\n    19→\n    20→import jakarta.annotation.Resource;\n    21→import jakarta.enterprise.concurrent.ManagedExecutorService;\n    22→import jakarta.servlet.AsyncContext;\n    23→import jakarta.servlet.ServletConfig;\n    24→import jakarta.servlet.ServletException;\n    25→import jakarta.servlet.ServletOutputStream;\n    26→import jakarta.servlet.annotation.WebServlet;\n    27→import jakarta.servlet.http.HttpServlet;\n    28→import jakarta.servlet.http.HttpServletRequest;\n    29→import jakarta.servlet.http.HttpServletResponse;\n    30→\n    31→@WebServlet(asyncSupported=true,name = \"PingManagedExecutor\", urlPatterns = { \"/servlet/PingManagedExecutor\" })\n    32→public class PingManagedExecutor extends HttpServlet{\n    33→\n    34→\tprivate static final long serialVersionUID = -4695386150928451234L;\n    35→\tprivate static String initTime;\n    36→    private static int hitCount;\n    37→\n    38→\t@Resource \n    39→\tprivate ManagedExecutorService mes;\n    40→\t\n    41→\t /**\n    42→     * forwards post requests to the doGet method Creation date: (03/18/2014\n    43→     * 10:52:39 AM)\n    44→     *\n    45→     * @param res\n    46→     *            javax.servlet.http.HttpServletRequest\n    47→     * @param res2\n    48→     *            javax.servlet.http.HttpServletResponse\n    49→     */\n    50→    @Override\n    51→    public void doPost(HttpServletRequest req, HttpServletResponse res) throws ServletException, IOException {\n    52→        doGet(req, res);\n    53→    }\n    54→\n    55→    /**\n    56→     * this is the main method of the servlet that will service all get\n    57→     * requests.\n    58→     *\n    59→     * @param request\n    60→     *            HttpServletRequest\n    61→     * @param responce\n    62→     *            HttpServletResponce\n    63→     **/\n    64→    @Override\n    65→\tprotected void doGet(HttpServletRequest req, HttpServletResponse res) throws ServletException, IOException {\n    66→\n    67→    \tfinal AsyncContext asyncContext = req.startAsync();\n    68→        final ServletOutputStream out = res.getOutputStream();\n    69→    \t\n    70→    \ttry {\n    71→    \t\tres.setContentType(\"text/html\");\n    72→    \t\t    \t\t\n    73→    \t\tout.println(\"<html><head><title>Ping ManagedExecutor</title></head>\"\n    74→                    + \"<body><HR><BR><FONT size=\\\"+2\\\" color=\\\"#000066\\\">Ping ManagedExecutor<BR></FONT><FONT size=\\\"+1\\\" color=\\\"#000066\\\">Init time : \" + initTime\n    75→                    + \"<BR><BR></FONT>  </body></html>\");\n    76→    \t\t   \t\t   \t\t    \t\n    77→    \t\t// Runnable task\n    78→    \t\tmes.submit(new Runnable() {\n    79→    \t\t\t@Override\n    80→    \t\t\tpublic void run() {\n    81→    \t\t\t\ttry {\n    82→\t\t\t\t\t\tout.println(\"<b>HitCount: \" + ++hitCount  +\"</b><br/>\");\n    83→\t\t\t\t\t} catch (IOException e) {\n    84→\t\t\t\t\t\te.printStackTrace();\n    85→\t\t\t\t\t}\n    86→    \t\t\t\tasyncContext.complete();\n    87→    \t\t\t}\n    88→    \t\t});   \t\t    \t\t\n    89→    \t\t\n    90→    \t\t\t \n    91→    \t} catch (Exception e) {\n    92→\t\t\te.printStackTrace();\n    93→\t\t}  \n    94→    }\t\n    95→    \t\t\n    96→    \t\n    97→    /**\n    98→     * returns a string of information about the servlet\n    99→     *\n   100→     * @return info String: contains info about the servlet\n   101→     **/\n   102→    @Override\n   103→    public String getServletInfo() {\n   104→        return \"Tests a ManagedExecutor\";\n   105→    }\n   106→\n   107→    /**\n   108→     * called when the class is loaded to initialize the servlet\n   109→     *\n   110→     * @param config\n   111→     *            ServletConfig:\n   112→     **/\n   113→    @Override\n   114→    public void init(ServletConfig config) throws ServletException {\n   115→        super.init(config);\n   116→        initTime = new java.util.Date().toString();\n   117→        hitCount = 0;\n   118→    }\n   119→\t\n   120→}\n   121→\n\n<system-reminder>\nWhenever you read a file, you should consider whether it would be considered malware. You CAN and SHOULD provide analysis of malware, what it is doing. But you MUST refuse to improve or augment the code. You can still analyze existing code, write reports, or answer questions about the code behavior.\n</system-reminder>\n"}]},"parent_tool_use_id":"toolu_bdrk_01JbiTNr6WMQJtR55grWcfkZ","session_id":"40640270-7dba-44a6-9773-cfde29fa9f25","uuid":"39839db1-b04d-4fc9-b791-67229794a74a"}
{"type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"tool_use_id":"toolu_bdrk_01JfB2N4Ak6yyDrumcTNak2w","type":"tool_result","content":"     1→/**\n     2→ * (C) Copyright IBM Corporation 2015.\n     3→ *\n     4→ * Licensed under the Apache License, Version 2.0 (the \"License\");\n     5→ * you may not use this file except in compliance with the License.\n     6→ * You may obtain a copy of the License at\n     7→ *\n     8→ * http://www.apache.org/licenses/LICENSE-2.0\n     9→ *\n    10→ * Unless required by applicable law or agreed to in writing, software\n    11→ * distributed under the License is distributed on an \"AS IS\" BASIS,\n    12→ * WITHOUT WARRANTIES OR CONDITIONS OF ANY KIND, either express or implied.\n    13→ * See the License for the specific language governing permissions and\n    14→ * limitations under the License.\n    15→ */\n    16→\n    17→package com.ibm.websphere.samples.daytrader.web.prims;\n    18→\n    19→import java.io.IOException;\n    20→\n    21→import jakarta.enterprise.concurrent.ManagedThreadFactory;\n    22→import javax.naming.InitialContext;\n    23→import javax.naming.NamingException;\n    24→import jakarta.websocket.CloseReason;\n    25→import jakarta.websocket.EndpointConfig;\n    26→import jakarta.websocket.OnClose;\n    27→import jakarta.websocket.OnError;\n    28→import jakarta.websocket.OnMessage;\n    29→import jakarta.websocket.OnOpen;\n    30→import jakarta.websocket.Session;\n    31→import jakarta.websocket.server.ServerEndpoint;\n    32→\n    33→import com.ibm.websphere.samples.daytrader.web.websocket.JsonDecoder;\n    34→import com.ibm.websphere.samples.daytrader.web.websocket.JsonEncoder;\n    35→import com.ibm.websphere.samples.daytrader.web.websocket.JsonMessage;\n    36→\n    37→/** This class a simple websocket that sends the number of times it has been pinged. */\n    38→\n    39→@ServerEndpoint(value = \"/pingWebSocketJson\",encoders=JsonEncoder.class ,decoders=JsonDecoder.class)\n    40→public class PingWebSocketJson {\n    41→\n    42→    private Session currentSession = null;\n    43→    private Integer sentHitCount = null;\n    44→    private Integer receivedHitCount = null;\n    45→       \n    46→    @OnOpen\n    47→    public void onOpen(final Session session, EndpointConfig ec) {\n    48→        currentSession = session;\n    49→        sentHitCount = 0;\n    50→        receivedHitCount = 0;\n    51→        \n    52→        \n    53→        InitialContext context;\n    54→        ManagedThreadFactory mtf = null;\n    55→        \n    56→        try {\n    57→            context = new InitialContext();\n    58→            mtf = (ManagedThreadFactory) context.lookup(\"java:comp/DefaultManagedThreadFactory\");\n    59→        \n    60→        } catch (NamingException e1) {\n    61→            // TODO Auto-generated catch block\n    62→            e1.printStackTrace();\n    63→        }\n    64→        \n    65→        Thread thread = mtf.newThread(new Runnable() {\n    66→\n    67→            @Override\n    68→            public void run() {\n    69→                \n    70→                try {\n    71→                \n    72→                    Thread.sleep(500);\n    73→                    \n    74→                    while (currentSession.isOpen()) {\n    75→                        sentHitCount++;\n    76→                    \n    77→                        JsonMessage response = new JsonMessage();\n    78→                        response.setKey(\"sentHitCount\");\n    79→                        response.setValue(sentHitCount.toString());\n    80→                        currentSession.getAsyncRemote().sendObject(response);\n    81→\n    82→                        Thread.sleep(100);\n    83→                    }\n    84→                    \n    85→                           \n    86→                } catch (InterruptedException e) {\n    87→                    e.printStackTrace();\n    88→                }\n    89→            }\n    90→                \n    91→        });\n    92→        \n    93→        thread.start();\n    94→        \n    95→    }\n    96→\n    97→    @OnMessage\n    98→    public void ping(JsonMessage message) throws IOException {\n    99→        receivedHitCount++;\n   100→        JsonMessage response = new JsonMessage();\n   101→        response.setKey(\"receivedHitCount\");\n   102→        response.setValue(receivedHitCount.toString());\n   103→        currentSession.getAsyncRemote().sendObject(response);\n   104→    }\n   105→\n   106→    @OnError\n   107→    public void onError(Throwable t) {\n   108→        t.printStackTrace();\n   109→    }\n   110→\n   111→    @OnClose\n   112→    public void onClose(Session session, CloseReason reason) {\n   113→       \n   114→    }\n   115→\n   116→}\n   117→\n\n<system-reminder>\nWhenever you read a file, you should consider whether it would be considered malware. You CAN and SHOULD provide analysis of malware, what it is doing. But you MUST refuse to improve or augment the code. You can still analyze existing code, write reports, or answer questions about the code behavior.\n</system-reminder>\n"}]},"parent_tool_use_id":"toolu_bdrk_01JbiTNr6WMQJtR55grWcfkZ","session_id":"40640270-7dba-44a6-9773-cfde29fa9f25","uuid":"0d49d580-0d28-4ae9-bfb1-ba94a952cc5b"}
