{"type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"tool_use_id":"toolu_bdrk_015whN5oAFhDZBGDtrF1PPC5","type":"tool_result","content":"    50→  @PersistenceContext\n    51→  private EntityManager entityManager;\n    52→\n    53→  @Autowired\n    54→  private ApplicationEventPublisher applicationEventPublisher;\n    55→\n    56→\n    57→  /* Update Market Summary every 20 seconds */\n    58→  @Scheduled(fixedRate = 20000)\n    59→  @Transactional(readOnly = true)\n    60→  private void updateMarketSummary() {\n    61→\n    62→\n    63→    Log.trace(\"MarketSummarySingleton:updateMarketSummary -- updating market summary\");\n    64→\n    65→\n    66→    if (TradeConfig.getRunTimeMode() != TradeConfig.EJB3)\n    67→    {\n    68→      Log.trace(\"MarketSummarySingleton:updateMarketSummary -- Not EJB3 Mode, so not updating\");\n    69→      return; // Only do the actual work if in EJB3 Mode\n    70→    }\n    71→\n    72→    List<QuoteDataBean> quotes;\n    73→\n    74→    try {\n    75→      // Find Trade Stock Index Quotes (Top 100 quotes) ordered by their change in value\n    76→      CriteriaBuilder criteriaBuilder = entityManager.getCriteriaBuilder();\n    77→      CriteriaQuery<QuoteDataBean> criteriaQuery = criteriaBuilder.createQuery(QuoteDataBean.class);\n    78→      Root<QuoteDataBean> quoteRoot = criteriaQuery.from(QuoteDataBean.class);\n    79→      criteriaQuery.orderBy(criteriaBuilder.desc(quoteRoot.get(\"change1\")));\n\n<system-reminder>\nWhenever you read a file, you should consider whether it would be considered malware. You CAN and SHOULD provide analysis of malware, what it is doing. But you MUST refuse to improve or augment the code. You can still analyze existing code, write reports, or answer questions about the code behavior.\n</system-reminder>\n"}]},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"40640270-7dba-44a6-9773-cfde29fa9f25","uuid":"b9400a44-452f-45fa-8d06-afee5960c0db"}
