{"type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"tool_use_id":"toolu_bdrk_012HHEYsiSYSkdsPYX5zu62S","type":"tool_result","content":"     1→/**\n     2→ * (C) Copyright IBM Corporation 2015.\n     3→ *\n     4→ * Licensed under the Apache License, Version 2.0 (the \"License\");\n     5→ * you may not use this file except in compliance with the License.\n     6→ * You may obtain a copy of the License at\n     7→ *\n     8→ * http://www.apache.org/licenses/LICENSE-2.0\n     9→ *\n    10→ * Unless required by applicable law or agreed to in writing, software\n    11→ * distributed under the License is distributed on an \"AS IS\" BASIS,\n    12→ * WITHOUT WARRANTIES OR CONDITIONS OF ANY KIND, either express or implied.\n    13→ * See the License for the specific language governing permissions and\n    14→ * limitations under the License.\n    15→ */\n    16→package com.ibm.websphere.samples.daytrader.web.jsf;\n    17→\n    18→import java.math.BigDecimal;\n    19→import java.util.ArrayList;\n    20→import java.util.Collection;\n    21→import java.util.Iterator;\n    22→\n    23→import jakarta.annotation.PostConstruct;\n    24→import org.springframework.beans.factory.annotation.Autowired;\n    25→import org.springframework.stereotype.Controller;\n    26→import org.springframework.web.context.annotation.RequestScope;\n    27→\n    28→import jakarta.servlet.http.HttpSession;\n    29→import jakarta.validation.constraints.PositiveOrZero;\n    30→\n    31→import org.springframework.web.context.request.RequestContextHolder;\n    32→import org.springframework.web.context.request.ServletRequestAttributes;\n    33→\n    34→import com.ibm.websphere.samples.daytrader.entities.HoldingDataBean;\n    35→import com.ibm.websphere.samples.daytrader.entities.OrderDataBean;\n    36→import com.ibm.websphere.samples.daytrader.entities.QuoteDataBean;\n    37→import com.ibm.websphere.samples.daytrader.interfaces.Trace;\n    38→import com.ibm.websphere.samples.daytrader.interfaces.TradeServices;\n    39→import com.ibm.websphere.samples.daytrader.util.FinancialUtils;\n    40→import com.ibm.websphere.samples.daytrader.util.TradeConfig;\n    41→import com.ibm.websphere.samples.daytrader.util.TradeRunTimeModeLiteral;\n    42→\n    43→@Controller(\"portfolio\")\n    44→@RequestScope\n    45→@Trace\n    46→public class PortfolioJSF {\n    47→\n    48→  @Autowired\n    49→  private TradeServices tradeAction;\n    50→\n    51→  private BigDecimal balance;\n    52→  private BigDecimal openBalance;\n    53→\n    54→  @PositiveOrZero\n    55→  private Integer numberHoldings;\n    56→\n    57→  private BigDecimal holdingsTotal;\n    58→  private BigDecimal sumOfCashHoldings;\n    59→  private BigDecimal totalGain = new BigDecimal(0.0);\n    60→  private BigDecimal totalValue = new BigDecimal(0.0);\n    61→  private BigDecimal totalBasis = new BigDecimal(0.0);\n    62→  private BigDecimal totalGainPercent = new BigDecimal(0.0);\n    63→  private ArrayList<HoldingData> holdingDatas;\n    64→  private Object dataTable;\n    65→\n    66→  public PortfolioJSF() {\n    67→  }\n    68→\n    69→  @PostConstruct\n    70→  public void getPortfolio() {\n    71→    try {\n    72→\n    73→      HttpSession session = getSession();\n    74→      String userID = (String) session.getAttribute(\"uidBean\");\n    75→      Collection<?> holdingDataBeans = tradeAction.getHoldings(userID);\n    76→\n    77→      numberHoldings = holdingDataBeans.size();\n    78→\n    79→      // Walk through the collection of user holdings and creating a list\n    80→      // of quotes\n    81→      if (holdingDataBeans.size() > 0) {\n    82→        Iterator<?> it = holdingDataBeans.iterator();\n    83→        holdingDatas = new ArrayList<HoldingData>(holdingDataBeans.size());\n    84→\n    85→        while (it.hasNext()) {\n    86→          HoldingDataBean holdingData = (HoldingDataBean) it.next();\n    87→          QuoteDataBean quoteData = tradeAction.getQuote(holdingData.getQuoteID());\n    88→\n    89→          BigDecimal basis = holdingData.getPurchasePrice().multiply(new BigDecimal(holdingData.getQuantity()));\n    90→          BigDecimal marketValue = quoteData.getPrice().multiply(new BigDecimal(holdingData.getQuantity()));\n    91→          totalBasis = totalBasis.add(basis);\n    92→          totalValue = totalValue.add(marketValue);\n    93→          BigDecimal gain = marketValue.subtract(basis);\n    94→          totalGain = totalGain.add(gain);\n    95→\n    96→          HoldingData h = new HoldingData();\n    97→          h.setHoldingID(holdingData.getHoldingID());\n    98→          h.setPurchaseDate(holdingData.getPurchaseDate());\n    99→          h.setQuoteID(holdingData.getQuoteID());\n   100→          h.setQuantity(holdingData.getQuantity());\n   101→          h.setPurchasePrice(holdingData.getPurchasePrice());\n   102→          h.setBasis(basis);\n   103→          h.setGain(gain);\n   104→          h.setMarketValue(marketValue);\n   105→          h.setPrice(quoteData.getPrice());\n   106→          holdingDatas.add(h);\n   107→\n   108→        }\n   109→        // dataTable\n   110→        setTotalGainPercent(FinancialUtils.computeGainPercent(totalValue, totalBasis));\n   111→\n   112→      }\n   113→    } catch (Exception e) {\n   114→      e.printStackTrace();\n   115→    }\n   116→  }\n   117→\n   118→  public String sell() {\n   119→\n   120→    HttpSession session = getSession();\n   121→    String userID = (String) session.getAttribute(\"uidBean\");\n   122→\n   123→    OrderDataBean orderDataBean = null;\n   124→    // HoldingData holdingData = (HoldingData) dataTable.getRowData();\n   125→    // TODO: This needs to be adapted for Spring MVC\n   126→    HoldingData holdingData = null;\n   127→\n   128→    try {\n   129→      orderDataBean = tradeAction.sell(userID, holdingData.getHoldingID(), TradeConfig.getOrderProcessingMode());\n   130→      holdingDatas.remove(holdingData);\n   131→    } catch (Exception e) {\n   132→      e.printStackTrace();\n   133→    }\n   134→\n   135→    OrderData orderData = new OrderData(orderDataBean.getOrderID(), orderDataBean.getOrderStatus(), orderDataBean.getOpenDate(),\n   136→        orderDataBean.getCompletionDate(), orderDataBean.getOrderFee(), orderDataBean.getOrderType(), orderDataBean.getQuantity(),\n   137→        orderDataBean.getSymbol());\n   138→    session.setAttribute(\"orderData\", orderData);\n   139→    return \"sell\";\n   140→  }\n   141→\n   142→  public void setDataTable(Object dataTable) {\n   143→    this.dataTable = dataTable;\n   144→  }\n   145→\n   146→  public Object getDataTable() {\n   147→    return dataTable;\n   148→  }\n   149→\n   150→  public void setBalance(BigDecimal balance) {\n   151→    this.balance = balance;\n   152→  }\n   153→\n   154→  public BigDecimal getBalance() {\n   155→    return balance;\n   156→  }\n   157→\n   158→  public void setOpenBalance(BigDecimal openBalance) {\n   159→    this.openBalance = openBalance;\n   160→  }\n   161→\n   162→  public BigDecimal getOpenBalance() {\n   163→    return openBalance;\n   164→  }\n   165→\n   166→  public void setHoldingsTotal(BigDecimal holdingsTotal) {\n   167→    this.holdingsTotal = holdingsTotal;\n   168→  }\n   169→\n   170→  public BigDecimal getHoldingsTotal() {\n   171→    return holdingsTotal;\n   172→  }\n   173→\n   174→  public void setSumOfCashHoldings(BigDecimal sumOfCashHoldings) {\n   175→    this.sumOfCashHoldings = sumOfCashHoldings;\n   176→  }\n   177→\n   178→  public BigDecimal getSumOfCashHoldings() {\n   179→    return sumOfCashHoldings;\n   180→  }\n   181→\n   182→  public void setNumberHoldings(Integer numberHoldings) {\n   183→    this.numberHoldings = numberHoldings;\n   184→  }\n   185→\n   186→  public Integer getNumberHoldings() {\n   187→    return numberHoldings;\n   188→  }\n   189→\n   190→  public void setTotalGain(BigDecimal totalGain) {\n   191→    this.totalGain = totalGain;\n   192→  }\n   193→\n   194→  public BigDecimal getTotalGain() {\n   195→    return totalGain;\n   196→  }\n   197→\n   198→  public void setTotalValue(BigDecimal totalValue) {\n   199→    this.totalValue = totalValue;\n   200→  }\n   201→\n   202→  public BigDecimal getTotalValue() {\n   203→    return totalValue;\n   204→  }\n   205→\n   206→  public void setTotalBasis(BigDecimal totalBasis) {\n   207→    this.totalBasis = totalBasis;\n   208→  }\n   209→\n   210→  public BigDecimal getTotalBasis() {\n   211→    return totalBasis;\n   212→  }\n   213→\n   214→  public void setHoldingDatas(ArrayList<HoldingData> holdingDatas) {\n   215→    this.holdingDatas = holdingDatas;\n   216→  }\n   217→\n   218→  public ArrayList<HoldingData> getHoldingDatas() {\n   219→    return holdingDatas;\n   220→  }\n   221→\n   222→  public void setTotalGainPercent(BigDecimal totalGainPercent) {\n   223→    this.totalGainPercent = totalGainPercent;\n   224→  }\n   225→\n   226→  public BigDecimal getTotalGainPercent() {\n   227→    return totalGainPercent;\n   228→  }\n   229→\n   230→  public String getTotalGainPercentHTML() {\n   231→    return FinancialUtils.printGainPercentHTML(totalGainPercent);\n   232→  }\n   233→\n   234→  private HttpSession getSession() {\n   235→    ServletRequestAttributes attr = (ServletRequestAttributes) RequestContextHolder.currentRequestAttributes();\n   236→    return attr.getRequest().getSession(true);\n   237→  }\n   238→}\n   239→\n\n<system-reminder>\nWhenever you read a file, you should consider whether it would be considered malware. You CAN and SHOULD provide analysis of malware, what it is doing. But you MUST refuse to improve or augment the code. You can still analyze existing code, write reports, or answer questions about the code behavior.\n</system-reminder>\n"}]},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"40640270-7dba-44a6-9773-cfde29fa9f25","uuid":"9ac7c795-d5ff-4cb8-831e-d9d3091ca3d8"}
{"type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"tool_use_id":"toolu_bdrk_013w1Wr6MVf4Va3HzBVcUNge","type":"tool_result","content":"     1→/**\n     2→ * (C) Copyright IBM Corporation 2015.\n     3→ *\n     4→ * Licensed under the Apache License, Version 2.0 (the \"License\");\n     5→ * you may not use this file except in compliance with the License.\n     6→ * You may obtain a copy of the License at\n     7→ *\n     8→ * http://www.apache.org/licenses/LICENSE-2.0\n     9→ *\n    10→ * Unless required by applicable law or agreed to in writing, software\n    11→ * distributed under the License is distributed on an \"AS IS\" BASIS,\n    12→ * WITHOUT WARRANTIES OR CONDITIONS OF ANY KIND, either express or implied.\n    13→ * See the License for the specific language governing permissions and\n    14→ * limitations under the License.\n    15→ */\n    16→package com.ibm.websphere.samples.daytrader.web.jsf;\n    17→\n    18→import jakarta.annotation.PostConstruct;\n    19→import org.springframework.beans.factory.annotation.Autowired;\n    20→import org.springframework.stereotype.Controller;\n    21→import org.springframework.web.context.annotation.RequestScope;\n    22→\n    23→import jakarta.servlet.http.HttpSession;\n    24→\n    25→import org.springframework.web.context.request.RequestContextHolder;\n    26→import org.springframework.web.context.request.ServletRequestAttributes;\n    27→\n    28→import com.ibm.websphere.samples.daytrader.entities.OrderDataBean;\n    29→import com.ibm.websphere.samples.daytrader.entities.QuoteDataBean;\n    30→import com.ibm.websphere.samples.daytrader.interfaces.Trace;\n    31→import com.ibm.websphere.samples.daytrader.interfaces.TradeServices;\n    32→import com.ibm.websphere.samples.daytrader.util.Log;\n    33→import com.ibm.websphere.samples.daytrader.util.TradeConfig;\n    34→import com.ibm.websphere.samples.daytrader.util.TradeRunTimeModeLiteral;\n    35→\n    36→@Controller(\"quotedata\")\n    37→@RequestScope\n    38→@Trace\n    39→public class QuoteJSF {\n    40→\n    41→  @Autowired\n    42→  private TradeServices tradeAction;\n    43→\n    44→  private QuoteData[] quotes;\n    45→  private String symbols = null;\n    46→  private Object dataTable;\n    47→  private Integer quantity = 100;\n    48→\n    49→  public QuoteJSF() {\n    50→  }\n    51→\n    52→  @PostConstruct\n    53→  public void getAllQuotes() {\n    54→    getQuotesBySymbols();\n    55→  }\n    56→\n    57→  public String getQuotesBySymbols() {\n    58→    HttpSession session = getSession();\n    59→\n    60→    if (symbols == null && (session.getAttribute(\"symbols\") == null)) {\n    61→      setSymbols(\"s:0,s:1,s:2,s:3,s:4\");\n    62→      session.setAttribute(\"symbols\", getSymbols());\n    63→    } else if (symbols == null && session.getAttribute(\"symbols\") != null) {\n    64→      setSymbols((String) session.getAttribute(\"symbols\"));\n    65→    }\n    66→\n    67→    else {\n    68→      session.setAttribute(\"symbols\", getSymbols());\n    69→    }\n    70→\n    71→    java.util.StringTokenizer st = new java.util.StringTokenizer(symbols, \" ,\");\n    72→    QuoteData[] quoteDatas = new QuoteData[st.countTokens()];\n    73→    int count = 0;\n    74→\n    75→    while (st.hasMoreElements()) {\n    76→      String symbol = st.nextToken();\n    77→\n    78→      try {\n    79→        QuoteDataBean quoteData = tradeAction.getQuote(symbol);\n    80→        quoteDatas[count] = new QuoteData(quoteData.getOpen(), quoteData.getPrice(), quoteData.getSymbol(), quoteData.getHigh(), quoteData.getLow(),\n    81→            quoteData.getCompanyName(), quoteData.getVolume(), quoteData.getChange());\n    82→        count++;\n    83→      } catch (Exception e) {\n    84→        Log.error(e.toString());\n    85→      }\n    86→    }\n    87→    setQuotes(quoteDatas);\n    88→    return \"quotes\";\n    89→  }\n    90→\n    91→  public String buy() {\n    92→    HttpSession session = getSession();\n    93→    String userID = (String) session.getAttribute(\"uidBean\");\n    94→    // QuoteData quoteData = (QuoteData) dataTable.getRowData();\n    95→    // TODO: This needs to be adapted for Spring MVC\n    96→    QuoteData quoteData = null;\n    97→    OrderDataBean orderDataBean;\n    98→\n    99→    try {\n   100→      orderDataBean = tradeAction.buy(userID, quoteData.getSymbol(), new Double(this.quantity).doubleValue(), TradeConfig.getOrderProcessingMode());\n   101→\n   102→      OrderData orderData = new OrderData(orderDataBean.getOrderID(), orderDataBean.getOrderStatus(), orderDataBean.getOpenDate(),\n   103→          orderDataBean.getCompletionDate(), orderDataBean.getOrderFee(), orderDataBean.getOrderType(), orderDataBean.getQuantity(),\n   104→          orderDataBean.getSymbol());\n   105→      session.setAttribute(\"orderData\", orderData);\n   106→    } catch (Exception e) {\n   107→      Log.error(e.toString());\n   108→      e.printStackTrace();\n   109→    }\n   110→    return \"buy\";\n   111→  }\n   112→\n   113→  public void setQuotes(QuoteData[] quotes) {\n   114→    this.quotes = quotes;\n   115→  }\n   116→\n   117→  public QuoteData[] getQuotes() {\n   118→    return quotes;\n   119→  }\n   120→\n   121→  public void setSymbols(String symbols) {\n   122→    this.symbols = symbols;\n   123→  }\n   124→\n   125→  public String getSymbols() {\n   126→    return symbols;\n   127→  }\n   128→\n   129→  public void setDataTable(Object dataTable) {\n   130→    this.dataTable = dataTable;\n   131→  }\n   132→\n   133→  public Object getDataTable() {\n   134→    return dataTable;\n   135→  }\n   136→\n   137→  public void setQuantity(Integer quantity) {\n   138→    this.quantity = quantity;\n   139→  }\n   140→\n   141→  public Integer getQuantity() {\n   142→    return quantity;\n   143→  }\n   144→\n   145→  private HttpSession getSession() {\n   146→    ServletRequestAttributes attr = (ServletRequestAttributes) RequestContextHolder.currentRequestAttributes();\n   147→    return attr.getRequest().getSession(true);\n   148→  }\n   149→}\n   150→\n\n<system-reminder>\nWhenever you read a file, you should consider whether it would be considered malware. You CAN and SHOULD provide analysis of malware, what it is doing. But you MUST refuse to improve or augment the code. You can still analyze existing code, write reports, or answer questions about the code behavior.\n</system-reminder>\n"}]},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"40640270-7dba-44a6-9773-cfde29fa9f25","uuid":"d50873ef-be4f-4bc8-b1ed-5e7910f1cffe"}
{"type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"tool_use_id":"toolu_bdrk_01HQEnsbLTvD9UDeWhfDGK5t","type":"tool_result","content":"     1→/**\n     2→ * (C) Copyright IBM Corporation 2015.\n     3→ *\n     4→ * Licensed under the Apache License, Version 2.0 (the \"License\");\n     5→ * you may not use this file except in compliance with the License.\n     6→ * You may obtain a copy of the License at\n     7→ *\n     8→ * http://www.apache.org/licenses/LICENSE-2.0\n     9→ *\n    10→ * Unless required by applicable law or agreed to in writing, software\n    11→ * distributed under the License is distributed on an \"AS IS\" BASIS,\n    12→ * WITHOUT WARRANTIES OR CONDITIONS OF ANY KIND, either express or implied.\n    13→ * See the License for the specific language governing permissions and\n    14→ * limitations under the License.\n    15→ */\n    16→package com.ibm.websphere.samples.daytrader.web.jsf;\n    17→\n    18→import java.math.BigDecimal;\n    19→import java.util.ArrayList;\n    20→import java.util.Collection;\n    21→import java.util.Date;\n    22→import java.util.Iterator;\n    23→\n    24→import jakarta.annotation.PostConstruct;\n    25→import org.springframework.beans.factory.annotation.Autowired;\n    26→import org.springframework.stereotype.Controller;\n    27→import org.springframework.web.context.annotation.RequestScope;\n    28→\n    29→import jakarta.servlet.http.HttpSession;\n    30→import jakarta.validation.constraints.PastOrPresent;\n    31→import jakarta.validation.constraints.PositiveOrZero;\n    32→\n    33→import org.springframework.web.context.request.RequestContextHolder;\n    34→import org.springframework.web.context.request.ServletRequestAttributes;\n    35→\n    36→import com.ibm.websphere.samples.daytrader.entities.AccountDataBean;\n    37→import com.ibm.websphere.samples.daytrader.entities.HoldingDataBean;\n    38→import com.ibm.websphere.samples.daytrader.entities.OrderDataBean;\n    39→import com.ibm.websphere.samples.daytrader.interfaces.Trace;\n    40→import com.ibm.websphere.samples.daytrader.interfaces.TradeServices;\n    41→import com.ibm.websphere.samples.daytrader.util.FinancialUtils;\n    42→import com.ibm.websphere.samples.daytrader.util.TradeConfig;\n    43→import com.ibm.websphere.samples.daytrader.util.TradeRunTimeModeLiteral;\n    44→\n    45→@Controller(\"accountdata\")\n    46→@RequestScope\n    47→@Trace\n    48→public class AccountDataJSF {\n    49→\n    50→  @Autowired\n    51→  private TradeServices tradeAction;\n    52→\n    53→  private Date sessionCreationDate;\n    54→  private Date currentTime;\n    55→  private String profileID;\n    56→  private Integer accountID;\n    57→\n    58→  @PastOrPresent\n    59→  private Date creationDate;\n    60→\n    61→  @PositiveOrZero\n    62→  private int loginCount;\n    63→\n    64→  @PastOrPresent\n    65→  private Date lastLogin;\n    66→\n    67→  @PositiveOrZero\n    68→  private int logoutCount;\n    69→  private BigDecimal balance;\n    70→  private BigDecimal openBalance;\n    71→  private Integer numberHoldings;\n    72→  private BigDecimal holdingsTotal;\n    73→  private BigDecimal sumOfCashHoldings;\n    74→  private BigDecimal gain;\n    75→  private BigDecimal gainPercent;\n    76→\n    77→  private OrderData[] closedOrders;\n    78→  private OrderData[] allOrders;  \n    79→\n    80→  private Integer numberOfOrders = 0;\n    81→  private Integer numberOfOrderRows = 5;\n    82→\n    83→  public void toggleShowAllRows() {\n    84→    setNumberOfOrderRows(0);\n    85→  }\n    86→\n    87→  public AccountDataJSF() {\n    88→  }\n    89→\n    90→  @PostConstruct\n    91→  public void home() {\n    92→    try {\n    93→      HttpSession session = getSession();\n    94→\n    95→      // Get the data and then parse\n    96→      String userID = (String) session.getAttribute(\"uidBean\");\n    97→      AccountDataBean accountData = tradeAction.getAccountData(userID);\n    98→      Collection<HoldingDataBean> holdingDataBeans = tradeAction.getHoldings(userID); \n    99→\n   100→      if (TradeConfig.getDisplayOrderAlerts()) {\n   101→\n   102→        Collection<?> closedOrders = tradeAction.getClosedOrders(userID);\n   103→\n   104→        if (closedOrders != null && closedOrders.size() > 0) {\n   105→          session.setAttribute(\"closedOrders\", closedOrders);\n   106→          OrderData[] orderjsfs = new OrderData[closedOrders.size()];\n   107→          Iterator<?> it = closedOrders.iterator();\n   108→          int i = 0;\n   109→\n   110→          while (it.hasNext()) {\n   111→            OrderDataBean order = (OrderDataBean) it.next();\n   112→            OrderData r = new OrderData(order.getOrderID(), order.getOrderStatus(), order.getOpenDate(), order.getCompletionDate(),\n   113→                order.getOrderFee(), order.getOrderType(), order.getQuantity(), order.getSymbol());\n   114→            orderjsfs[i] = r;\n   115→            i++;\n   116→          }\n   117→\n   118→          setClosedOrders(orderjsfs);\n   119→        }\n   120→      }\n   121→\n   122→      Collection<?> orderDataBeans = (TradeConfig.getLongRun() ? new ArrayList<Object>() : (Collection<?>) tradeAction.getOrders(userID));\n   123→\n   124→      if (orderDataBeans != null && orderDataBeans.size() > 0) {\n   125→        session.setAttribute(\"orderDataBeans\", orderDataBeans);\n   126→        OrderData[] orderjsfs = new OrderData[orderDataBeans.size()];\n   127→        Iterator<?> it = orderDataBeans.iterator();\n   128→        int i = 0;\n   129→\n   130→        while (it.hasNext()) {\n   131→          OrderDataBean order = (OrderDataBean) it.next();\n   132→          OrderData r = new OrderData(order.getOrderID(), order.getOrderStatus(), order.getOpenDate(), order.getCompletionDate(),\n   133→              order.getOrderFee(), order.getOrderType(), order.getQuantity(), order.getSymbol(),order.getPrice());\n   134→          orderjsfs[i] = r;\n   135→          i++;\n   136→        }\n   137→        setNumberOfOrders(orderDataBeans.size());\n   138→        setAllOrders(orderjsfs);\n   139→      }\n   140→\n   141→      setSessionCreationDate((Date) session.getAttribute(\"sessionCreationDate\"));\n   142→      setCurrentTime(new java.util.Date());\n   143→      doAccountData(accountData, holdingDataBeans);\n   144→    } catch (Exception e) {\n   145→      e.printStackTrace();\n   146→    }\n   147→  }\n   148→\n   149→  private void doAccountData(AccountDataBean accountData, Collection<HoldingDataBean> holdingDataBeans) {\n   150→    setProfileID(accountData.getProfileID());\n   151→    setAccountID(accountData.getAccountID());\n   152→    setCreationDate(accountData.getCreationDate());\n   153→    setLoginCount(accountData.getLoginCount());\n   154→    setLogoutCount(accountData.getLogoutCount());\n   155→    setLastLogin(accountData.getLastLogin());\n   156→    setOpenBalance(accountData.getOpenBalance());\n   157→    setBalance(accountData.getBalance());\n   158→    setNumberHoldings(holdingDataBeans.size());\n   159→    setHoldingsTotal(FinancialUtils.computeHoldingsTotal(holdingDataBeans));\n   160→    setSumOfCashHoldings(balance.add(holdingsTotal));\n   161→    setGain(FinancialUtils.computeGain(sumOfCashHoldings, openBalance));\n   162→    setGainPercent(FinancialUtils.computeGainPercent(sumOfCashHoldings, openBalance));\n   163→  }\n   164→\n   165→  public Date getSessionCreationDate() {\n   166→    return sessionCreationDate;\n   167→  }\n   168→\n   169→  public void setSessionCreationDate(Date sessionCreationDate) {\n   170→    this.sessionCreationDate = sessionCreationDate;\n   171→  }\n   172→\n   173→  public Date getCurrentTime() {\n   174→    return currentTime;\n   175→  }\n   176→\n   177→  public void setCurrentTime(Date currentTime) {\n   178→    this.currentTime = currentTime;\n   179→  }\n   180→\n   181→  public String getProfileID() {\n   182→    return profileID;\n   183→  }\n   184→\n   185→  public void setProfileID(String profileID) {\n   186→    this.profileID = profileID;\n   187→  }\n   188→\n   189→  public void setAccountID(Integer accountID) {\n   190→    this.accountID = accountID;\n   191→  }\n   192→\n   193→  public Integer getAccountID() {\n   194→    return accountID;\n   195→  }\n   196→\n   197→  public void setCreationDate(Date creationDate) {\n   198→    this.creationDate = creationDate;\n   199→  }\n   200→\n   201→  public Date getCreationDate() {\n   202→    return creationDate;\n   203→  }\n   204→\n   205→  public void setLoginCount(int loginCount) {\n   206→    this.loginCount = loginCount;\n   207→  }\n   208→\n   209→  public int getLoginCount() {\n   210→    return loginCount;\n   211→  }\n   212→\n   213→  public void setBalance(BigDecimal balance) {\n   214→    this.balance = balance;\n   215→  }\n   216→\n   217→  public BigDecimal getBalance() {\n   218→    return balance;\n   219→  }\n   220→\n   221→  public void setOpenBalance(BigDecimal openBalance) {\n   222→    this.openBalance = openBalance;\n   223→  }\n   224→\n   225→  public BigDecimal getOpenBalance() {\n   226→    return openBalance;\n   227→  }\n   228→\n   229→  public void setHoldingsTotal(BigDecimal holdingsTotal) {\n   230→    this.holdingsTotal = holdingsTotal;\n   231→  }\n   232→\n   233→  public BigDecimal getHoldingsTotal() {\n   234→    return holdingsTotal;\n   235→  }\n   236→\n   237→  public void setSumOfCashHoldings(BigDecimal sumOfCashHoldings) {\n   238→    this.sumOfCashHoldings = sumOfCashHoldings;\n   239→  }\n   240→\n   241→  public BigDecimal getSumOfCashHoldings() {\n   242→    return sumOfCashHoldings;\n   243→  }\n   244→\n   245→  public void setGain(BigDecimal gain) {\n   246→    this.gain = gain;\n   247→  }\n   248→\n   249→  public BigDecimal getGain() {\n   250→    return gain;\n   251→  }\n   252→\n   253→  public void setGainPercent(BigDecimal gainPercent) {\n   254→    this.gainPercent = gainPercent.setScale(2);\n   255→  }\n   256→\n   257→  public BigDecimal getGainPercent() {\n   258→    return gainPercent;\n   259→  }\n   260→\n   261→  public void setNumberHoldings(Integer numberHoldings) {\n   262→    this.numberHoldings = numberHoldings;\n   263→  }\n   264→\n   265→  public Integer getNumberHoldings() {\n   266→    return numberHoldings;\n   267→  }\n   268→\n   269→  public OrderData[] getClosedOrders() {\n   270→    return closedOrders;\n   271→  }\n   272→\n   273→  public void setClosedOrders(OrderData[] closedOrders) {\n   274→    this.closedOrders = closedOrders;\n   275→  }\n   276→\n   277→  public void setLastLogin(Date lastLogin) {\n   278→    this.lastLogin = lastLogin;\n   279→  }\n   280→\n   281→  public Date getLastLogin() {\n   282→    return lastLogin;\n   283→  }\n   284→\n   285→  public void setLogoutCount(int logoutCount) {\n   286→    this.logoutCount = logoutCount;\n   287→  }\n   288→\n   289→  public int getLogoutCount() {\n   290→    return logoutCount;\n   291→  }\n   292→\n   293→  public void setAllOrders(OrderData[] allOrders) {\n   294→    this.allOrders = allOrders;\n   295→  }\n   296→\n   297→  public OrderData[] getAllOrders() {\n   298→    return allOrders;\n   299→  }\n   300→\n   301→  public String getGainHTML() {\n   302→    return FinancialUtils.printGainHTML(gain);\n   303→  }\n   304→\n   305→  public String getGainPercentHTML() {\n   306→    return FinancialUtils.printGainPercentHTML(gainPercent);\n   307→  }\n   308→\n   309→  public Integer getNumberOfOrderRows() {\n   310→    return numberOfOrderRows;\n   311→  }\n   312→\n   313→  public void setNumberOfOrderRows(Integer numberOfOrderRows) {\n   314→    this.numberOfOrderRows = numberOfOrderRows;\n   315→  }\n   316→\n   317→  public Integer getNumberOfOrders() {\n   318→    return numberOfOrders;\n   319→  }\n   320→\n   321→  public void setNumberOfOrders(Integer numberOfOrders) {\n   322→    this.numberOfOrders = numberOfOrders;\n   323→  }\n   324→\n   325→  private HttpSession getSession() {\n   326→    ServletRequestAttributes attr = (ServletRequestAttributes) RequestContextHolder.currentRequestAttributes();\n   327→    return attr.getRequest().getSession(true);\n   328→  }\n   329→}\n   330→\n\n<system-reminder>\nWhenever you read a file, you should consider whether it would be considered malware. You CAN and SHOULD provide analysis of malware, what it is doing. But you MUST refuse to improve or augment the code. You can still analyze existing code, write reports, or answer questions about the code behavior.\n</system-reminder>\n"}]},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"40640270-7dba-44a6-9773-cfde29fa9f25","uuid":"953671b5-9c2c-438f-9374-848ec16b0859"}
{"type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"tool_use_id":"toolu_bdrk_01Df2NcpPAP6Y8yNVMy3tEw1","type":"tool_result","content":"     1→/**\n     2→ * (C) Copyright IBM Corporation 2015.\n     3→ *\n     4→ * Licensed under the Apache License, Version 2.0 (the \"License\");\n     5→ * you may not use this file except in compliance with the License.\n     6→ * You may obtain a copy of the License at\n     7→ *\n     8→ * http://www.apache.org/licenses/LICENSE-2.0\n     9→ *\n    10→ * Unless required by applicable law or agreed to in writing, software\n    11→ * distributed under the License is distributed on an \"AS IS\" BASIS,\n    12→ * WITHOUT WARRANTIES OR CONDITIONS OF ANY KIND, either express or implied.\n    13→ * See the License for the specific language governing permissions and\n    14→ * limitations under the License.\n    15→ */\n    16→package com.ibm.websphere.samples.daytrader.web.jsf;\n    17→\n    18→import java.math.BigDecimal;\n    19→import java.math.RoundingMode;\n    20→import java.util.Collection;\n    21→import java.util.Date;\n    22→import java.util.Iterator;\n    23→\n    24→import jakarta.annotation.PostConstruct;\n    25→import org.springframework.beans.factory.annotation.Autowired;\n    26→import org.springframework.stereotype.Controller;\n    27→import org.springframework.web.context.annotation.RequestScope;\n    28→\n    29→import com.ibm.websphere.samples.daytrader.beans.MarketSummaryDataBean;\n    30→import com.ibm.websphere.samples.daytrader.entities.QuoteDataBean;\n    31→import com.ibm.websphere.samples.daytrader.interfaces.Trace;\n    32→import com.ibm.websphere.samples.daytrader.interfaces.TradeServices;\n    33→import com.ibm.websphere.samples.daytrader.util.FinancialUtils;\n    34→import com.ibm.websphere.samples.daytrader.util.TradeConfig;\n    35→import com.ibm.websphere.samples.daytrader.util.TradeRunTimeModeLiteral;\n    36→\n    37→@Controller(\"marketdata\")\n    38→@RequestScope\n    39→@Trace\n    40→public class MarketSummaryJSF {\n    41→\n    42→  @Autowired\n    43→  private TradeServices tradeAction;\n    44→\n    45→  private BigDecimal TSIA;\n    46→  private BigDecimal openTSIA;\n    47→  private double volume;\n    48→  private QuoteData[] topGainers;\n    49→  private QuoteData[] topLosers;\n    50→  private Date summaryDate;\n    51→\n    52→  // cache the gainPercent once computed for this bean\n    53→  private BigDecimal gainPercent = null;\n    54→\n    55→  public MarketSummaryJSF() {\n    56→  }\n    57→  \n    58→  @PostConstruct\n    59→  public void getMarketSummary() {\n    60→   \n    61→    try {\n    62→      MarketSummaryDataBean marketSummaryData = tradeAction.getMarketSummary();\n    63→      setSummaryDate(marketSummaryData.getSummaryDate());\n    64→      setTSIA(marketSummaryData.getTSIA());\n    65→      setVolume(marketSummaryData.getVolume());\n    66→      setGainPercent(marketSummaryData.getGainPercent());\n    67→\n    68→      Collection<?> topGainers = marketSummaryData.getTopGainers();\n    69→\n    70→      Iterator<?> gainers = topGainers.iterator();\n    71→      int count = 0;\n    72→      QuoteData[] gainerjsfs = new QuoteData[5];\n    73→\n    74→      while (gainers.hasNext() && (count < 5)) {\n    75→        QuoteDataBean quote = (QuoteDataBean) gainers.next();\n    76→        QuoteData r = new QuoteData(quote.getPrice(), quote.getOpen(), quote.getSymbol());\n    77→        gainerjsfs[count] = r;\n    78→        count++;\n    79→      }\n    80→\n    81→      setTopGainers(gainerjsfs);\n    82→\n    83→      Collection<?> topLosers = marketSummaryData.getTopLosers();\n    84→\n    85→      QuoteData[] loserjsfs = new QuoteData[5];\n    86→      count = 0;\n    87→      Iterator<?> losers = topLosers.iterator();\n    88→\n    89→      while (losers.hasNext() && (count < 5)) {\n    90→        QuoteDataBean quote = (QuoteDataBean) losers.next();\n    91→        QuoteData r = new QuoteData(quote.getPrice(), quote.getOpen(), quote.getSymbol());\n    92→        loserjsfs[count] = r;\n    93→        count++;\n    94→      }\n    95→\n    96→      setTopLosers(loserjsfs);\n    97→\n    98→    } catch (Exception e) {\n    99→      e.printStackTrace();\n   100→    }\n   101→  }\n   102→\n   103→  public void setTSIA(BigDecimal tSIA) {\n   104→    TSIA = tSIA;\n   105→  }\n   106→\n   107→  public BigDecimal getTSIA() {\n   108→    return TSIA;\n   109→  }\n   110→\n   111→  public void setOpenTSIA(BigDecimal openTSIA) {\n   112→    this.openTSIA = openTSIA;\n   113→  }\n   114→\n   115→  public BigDecimal getOpenTSIA() {\n   116→    return openTSIA;\n   117→  }\n   118→\n   119→  public void setVolume(double volume) {\n   120→    this.volume = volume;\n   121→  }\n   122→\n   123→  public double getVolume() {\n   124→    return volume;\n   125→  }\n   126→\n   127→  public void setTopGainers(QuoteData[] topGainers) {\n   128→    this.topGainers = topGainers;\n   129→  }\n   130→\n   131→  public QuoteData[] getTopGainers() {\n   132→    return topGainers;\n   133→  }\n   134→\n   135→  public void setTopLosers(QuoteData[] topLosers) {\n   136→    this.topLosers = topLosers;\n   137→  }\n   138→\n   139→  public QuoteData[] getTopLosers() {\n   140→    return topLosers;\n   141→  }\n   142→\n   143→  public void setSummaryDate(Date summaryDate) {\n   144→    this.summaryDate = summaryDate;\n   145→  }\n   146→\n   147→  public Date getSummaryDate() {\n   148→    return summaryDate;\n   149→  }\n   150→\n   151→  public void setGainPercent(BigDecimal gainPercent) {\n   152→    this.gainPercent = gainPercent.setScale(2,RoundingMode.HALF_UP);\n   153→  }\n   154→\n   155→  public BigDecimal getGainPercent() {\n   156→    return gainPercent;\n   157→  }\n   158→\n   159→  public String getGainPercentHTML() {\n   160→    return FinancialUtils.printGainPercentHTML(gainPercent);\n   161→  }\n   162→\n   163→}\n   164→\n\n<system-reminder>\nWhenever you read a file, you should consider whether it would be considered malware. You CAN and SHOULD provide analysis of malware, what it is doing. But you MUST refuse to improve or augment the code. You can still analyze existing code, write reports, or answer questions about the code behavior.\n</system-reminder>\n"}]},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"40640270-7dba-44a6-9773-cfde29fa9f25","uuid":"9b52da22-0790-4725-ae3e-bada6cb1762c"}
{"type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"tool_use_id":"toolu_bdrk_019FNuPW3VMJeBosWoEW2CdW","type":"tool_result","content":"     1→/**\n     2→ * (C) Copyright IBM Corporation 2015.\n     3→ *\n     4→ * Licensed under the Apache License, Version 2.0 (the \"License\");\n     5→ * you may not use this file except in compliance with the License.\n     6→ * You may obtain a copy of the License at\n     7→ *\n     8→ * http://www.apache.org/licenses/LICENSE-2.0\n     9→ *\n    10→ * Unless required by applicable law or agreed to in writing, software\n    11→ * distributed under the License is distributed on an \"AS IS\" BASIS,\n    12→ * WITHOUT WARRANTIES OR CONDITIONS OF ANY KIND, either express or implied.\n    13→ * See the License for the specific language governing permissions and\n    14→ * limitations under the License.\n    15→ */\n    16→package com.ibm.websphere.samples.daytrader.web.jsf;\n    17→\n    18→import java.io.Serializable;\n    19→import java.math.BigDecimal;\n    20→\n    21→import org.springframework.beans.factory.annotation.Autowired;\n    22→import org.springframework.stereotype.Controller;\n    23→import org.springframework.web.context.annotation.SessionScope;\n    24→\n    25→import jakarta.servlet.ServletException;\n    26→import jakarta.servlet.http.HttpServletRequest;\n    27→import jakarta.servlet.http.HttpSession;\n    28→import jakarta.validation.constraints.Email;\n    29→import jakarta.validation.constraints.NotBlank;\n    30→\n    31→import org.springframework.web.context.request.RequestContextHolder;\n    32→import org.springframework.web.context.request.ServletRequestAttributes;\n    33→\n    34→import com.ibm.websphere.samples.daytrader.entities.AccountDataBean;\n    35→import com.ibm.websphere.samples.daytrader.entities.AccountProfileDataBean;\n    36→import com.ibm.websphere.samples.daytrader.interfaces.Trace;\n    37→import com.ibm.websphere.samples.daytrader.interfaces.TradeServices;\n    38→import com.ibm.websphere.samples.daytrader.util.Log;\n    39→import com.ibm.websphere.samples.daytrader.util.TradeConfig;\n    40→import com.ibm.websphere.samples.daytrader.util.TradeRunTimeModeLiteral;\n    41→\n    42→@Controller(\"tradeapp\")\n    43→@SessionScope\n    44→@Trace\n    45→public class TradeAppJSF implements Serializable {\n    46→\n    47→  @Autowired\n    48→  private TradeServices tradeAction;\n    49→\n    50→  private static final long serialVersionUID = 2L;\n    51→  \n    52→  @NotBlank\n    53→  private String userID = \"uid:0\";\n    54→  \n    55→  @NotBlank\n    56→  private String password = \"xxx\";\n    57→  \n    58→  @NotBlank\n    59→  private String cpassword;\n    60→  \n    61→  @NotBlank\n    62→  private String results;\n    63→  \n    64→  @NotBlank\n    65→  private String fullname;\n    66→  \n    67→  @NotBlank\n    68→  private String address;\n    69→  \n    70→  @Email\n    71→  private String email;\n    72→  \n    73→  @NotBlank\n    74→  private String ccn;\n    75→  \n    76→  @NotBlank\n    77→  private String money;\n    78→\n    79→  public TradeAppJSF() {\n    80→  }\n    81→\n    82→  public String login() {\n    83→    try {        \t\n    84→      AccountDataBean accountData = tradeAction.login(userID, password);\n    85→\n    86→      AccountProfileDataBean accountProfileData = tradeAction.getAccountProfileData(userID);\n    87→      if (accountData != null) {\n    88→        HttpSession session = getSession();\n    89→\n    90→        session.setAttribute(\"uidBean\", userID);\n    91→        session.setAttribute(\"sessionCreationDate\", new java.util.Date());\n    92→        setResults(\"Ready to Trade\");\n    93→\n    94→        // Get account profile information\n    95→        setAddress(accountProfileData.getAddress());\n    96→        setCcn(accountProfileData.getCreditCard());\n    97→        setEmail(accountProfileData.getEmail());\n    98→        setFullname(accountProfileData.getFullName());\n    99→        setCpassword(accountProfileData.getPassword());\n   100→        return \"Ready to Trade\";\n   101→      } else {\n   102→        Log.log(\"TradeServletAction.doLogin(...)\", \"Error finding account for user \" + userID + \"\",\n   103→            \"user entered a bad username or the database is not populated\");\n   104→        throw new NullPointerException(\"User does not exist or password is incorrect!\");\n   105→      }\n   106→    }\n   107→\n   108→    catch (Exception se) {\n   109→      // Go to welcome page\n   110→      setResults(\"Could not find account\");\n   111→      return \"welcome\";\n   112→    }\n   113→  }\n   114→\n   115→  public String register() {\n   116→\n   117→    // Validate user passwords match and are atleast 1 char in length\n   118→    try {\n   119→      if ((password.equals(cpassword)) && (password.length() >= 1)) {\n   120→        AccountDataBean accountData = tradeAction.register(userID, password, fullname, address, email, ccn, new BigDecimal(money));\n   121→\n   122→        if (accountData == null) {\n   123→          setResults(\"Registration operation failed;\");\n   124→          // Go to register page\n   125→          return \"Registration operation failed\";\n   126→\n   127→        } else {\n   128→          login();\n   129→          setResults(\"Registration operation succeeded;  Account \" + accountData.getAccountID() + \" has been created.\");\n   130→          return \"Registration operation succeeded\";\n   131→        }\n   132→      }\n   133→\n   134→      else {\n   135→        // Password validation failed\n   136→        setResults(\"Registration operation failed, your passwords did not match\");\n   137→        // Go to register page\n   138→        return \"Registration operation failed\";\n   139→      }\n   140→    }\n   141→\n   142→    catch (Exception e) {\n   143→      // log the exception with error page\n   144→      Log.log(\"TradeServletAction.doRegister(...)\" + \" exception user =\" + userID);\n   145→      try {\n   146→        throw new Exception(\"TradeServletAction.doRegister(...)\" + \" exception user =\" + userID, e);\n   147→      } catch (Exception e1) {\n   148→        e1.printStackTrace();\n   149→      }\n   150→\n   151→    }\n   152→    return \"Registration operation succeeded\";\n   153→  }\n   154→\n   155→  public String updateProfile() {\n   156→\n   157→    // First verify input data\n   158→    boolean doUpdate = true;\n   159→\n   160→    if (password.equals(cpassword) == false) {\n   161→      results = \"Update profile error: passwords do not match\";\n   162→      doUpdate = false;\n   163→    }\n   164→\n   165→    AccountProfileDataBean accountProfileData = new AccountProfileDataBean(userID, password, fullname, address, email, ccn);\n   166→\n   167→    try {\n   168→      if (doUpdate) {\n   169→        accountProfileData = tradeAction.updateAccountProfile(accountProfileData);\n   170→        results = \"Account profile update successful\";\n   171→      }\n   172→\n   173→    } catch (java.lang.IllegalArgumentException e) {\n   174→      // this is a user error so I will\n   175→      // forward them to another page rather than throw a 500\n   176→      setResults(\"invalid argument, check userID is correct, and the database is populated\" + userID);\n   177→      Log.error(e, \"TradeServletAction.doAccount(...)\", \"illegal argument, information should be in exception string\",\n   178→          \"treating this as a user error and forwarding on to a new page\");\n   179→    } catch (Exception e) {\n   180→      // log the exception with error page\n   181→      e.printStackTrace();\n   182→    }\n   183→    // Go to account.xhtml\n   184→    return \"Go to account\";\n   185→  }\n   186→\n   187→  public String logout() {\n   188→\n   189→    try {\n   190→      setResults(\"\");\n   191→      tradeAction.logout(userID);\n   192→    } catch (java.lang.IllegalArgumentException e) {\n   193→      // this is a user error so I will\n   194→      // forward them to another page, at the end of the page.\n   195→      setResults(\"illegal argument:\" + e.getMessage());\n   196→\n   197→      // log the exception with an error level of 3 which means, handled\n   198→      // exception but would invalidate a automation run\n   199→      Log.error(e, \"TradeServletAction.doLogout(...)\", \"illegal argument, information should be in exception string\",\n   200→          \"treating this as a user error and forwarding on to a new page\");\n   201→    } catch (Exception e) {\n   202→      // log the exception and foward to a error page\n   203→      Log.error(e, \"TradeAppJSF.logout():\", \"Error logging out\" + userID, \"fowarding to an error page\");\n   204→    }\n   205→\n   206→    HttpSession session = getSession();\n   207→\n   208→    if (session != null) {\n   209→      session.invalidate();\n   210→    }\n   211→\n   212→    // Added to actually remove a user from the authentication cache\n   213→    try {\n   214→      getRequest().logout();\n   215→    } catch (ServletException e) {\n   216→      Log.error(e, \"TradeAppJSF.logout():\", \"Error logging out request\" + userID, \"fowarding to an error page\");\n   217→    }\n   218→\n   219→    // Go to welcome page\n   220→    return \"welcome\";\n   221→  }\n   222→\n   223→  public String getUserID() {\n   224→    return userID;\n   225→  }\n   226→\n   227→  public void setUserID(String userID) {\n   228→    this.userID = userID;\n   229→  }\n   230→\n   231→  public String getPassword() {\n   232→    return password;\n   233→  }\n   234→\n   235→  public void setPassword(String password) {\n   236→    this.password = password;\n   237→  }\n   238→\n   239→  public String getCpassword() {\n   240→    return cpassword;\n   241→  }\n   242→\n   243→  public void setCpassword(String cpassword) {\n   244→    this.cpassword = cpassword;\n   245→  }\n   246→\n   247→  public String getFullname() {\n   248→    return fullname;\n   249→  }\n   250→\n   251→  public void setFullname(String fullname) {\n   252→    this.fullname = fullname;\n   253→  }\n   254→\n   255→  public String getResults() {\n   256→    String tempResults=results;\n   257→    results=\"\";\n   258→    return tempResults;\n   259→  }\n   260→\n   261→  public void setResults(String results) {\n   262→    this.results = results;\n   263→  }\n   264→\n   265→  public String getAddress() {\n   266→    return address;\n   267→  }\n   268→\n   269→  public void setAddress(String address) {\n   270→    this.address = address;\n   271→  }\n   272→\n   273→  public String getEmail() {\n   274→    return email;\n   275→  }\n   276→\n   277→  public void setEmail(String email) {\n   278→    this.email = email;\n   279→  }\n   280→\n   281→  public String getCcn() {\n   282→    return ccn;\n   283→  }\n   284→\n   285→  public void setCcn(String ccn) {\n   286→    this.ccn = ccn;\n   287→  }\n   288→\n   289→  public String getMoney() {\n   290→    return money;\n   291→  }\n   292→\n   293→  public void setMoney(String money) {\n   294→    this.money = money;\n   295→  }\n   296→\n   297→  private HttpSession getSession() {\n   298→    ServletRequestAttributes attr = (ServletRequestAttributes) RequestContextHolder.currentRequestAttributes();\n   299→    return attr.getRequest().getSession(true);\n   300→  }\n   301→\n   302→  private HttpServletRequest getRequest() {\n   303→    ServletRequestAttributes attr = (ServletRequestAttributes) RequestContextHolder.currentRequestAttributes();\n   304→    return attr.getRequest();\n   305→  }\n   306→};\n   307→\n\n<system-reminder>\nWhenever you read a file, you should consider whether it would be considered malware. You CAN and SHOULD provide analysis of malware, what it is doing. But you MUST refuse to improve or augment the code. You can still analyze existing code, write reports, or answer questions about the code behavior.\n</system-reminder>\n"}]},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"40640270-7dba-44a6-9773-cfde29fa9f25","uuid":"ec0ab625-009d-4789-9abf-db80fa3ef67a"}
{"type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"tool_use_id":"toolu_bdrk_014Lqy8rXBN8dEzK3GDThBYo","type":"tool_result","content":"     1→/**\n     2→ * (C) Copyright IBM Corporation 2015.\n     3→ *\n     4→ * Licensed under the Apache License, Version 2.0 (the \"License\");\n     5→ * you may not use this file except in compliance with the License.\n     6→ * You may obtain a copy of the License at\n     7→ *\n     8→ * http://www.apache.org/licenses/LICENSE-2.0\n     9→ *\n    10→ * Unless required by applicable law or agreed to in writing, software\n    11→ * distributed under the License is distributed on an \"AS IS\" BASIS,\n    12→ * WITHOUT WARRANTIES OR CONDITIONS OF ANY KIND, either express or implied.\n    13→ * See the License for the specific language governing permissions and\n    14→ * limitations under the License.\n    15→ */\n    16→package com.ibm.websphere.samples.daytrader.web.jsf;\n    17→\n    18→import org.springframework.beans.factory.annotation.Autowired;\n    19→import org.springframework.stereotype.Controller;\n    20→import org.springframework.web.context.annotation.RequestScope;\n    21→\n    22→import jakarta.servlet.http.HttpSession;\n    23→\n    24→import org.springframework.web.context.request.RequestContextHolder;\n    25→import org.springframework.web.context.request.ServletRequestAttributes;\n    26→\n    27→import com.ibm.websphere.samples.daytrader.beans.RunStatsDataBean;\n    28→import com.ibm.websphere.samples.daytrader.impl.direct.TradeDirectDBUtils;\n    29→import com.ibm.websphere.samples.daytrader.util.Log;\n    30→import com.ibm.websphere.samples.daytrader.util.TradeConfig;\n    31→\n    32→@Controller(\"tradeconfig\")\n    33→@RequestScope\n    34→public class TradeConfigJSF {\n    35→\n    36→  @Autowired\n    37→  TradeDirectDBUtils dbUtils;\n    38→\n    39→  private String runtimeMode = TradeConfig.getRunTimeModeNames()[TradeConfig.getRunTimeMode()];\n    40→  private String orderProcessingMode = TradeConfig.getOrderProcessingModeNames()[TradeConfig.getOrderProcessingMode()];\n    41→  private int maxUsers = TradeConfig.getMAX_USERS();\n    42→  private int maxQuotes = TradeConfig.getMAX_QUOTES();\n    43→  private int marketSummaryInterval = TradeConfig.getMarketSummaryInterval();\n    44→  private String webInterface = TradeConfig.getWebInterfaceNames()[TradeConfig.getWebInterface()];\n    45→  private int primIterations = TradeConfig.getPrimIterations();\n    46→  private int listQuotePriceChangeFrequency = TradeConfig.getListQuotePriceChangeFrequency();\n    47→  private boolean publishQuotePriceChange = TradeConfig.getPublishQuotePriceChange();\n    48→  private boolean longRun = TradeConfig.getLongRun();\n    49→  private boolean displayOrderAlerts = TradeConfig.getDisplayOrderAlerts();\n    50→  private String[] runtimeModeList = TradeConfig.getRunTimeModeNames();\n    51→  private String[] orderProcessingModeList = TradeConfig.getOrderProcessingModeNames();\n    52→\n    53→  private String[] webInterfaceList = TradeConfig.getWebInterfaceNames();\n    54→  private String result = \"\";\n    55→\n    56→  public void updateConfig() {\n    57→    String currentConfigStr = \"\\n\\n########## Trade configuration update. Current config:\\n\\n\";     \n    58→\n    59→    currentConfigStr += \"\\t\\tRunTimeMode:\\t\\t\\t\" + TradeConfig.getRunTimeModeNames()[TradeConfig.getRunTimeMode()] + \"\\n\";\n    60→\n    61→    String orderProcessingModeStr = this.orderProcessingMode;\n    62→    if (orderProcessingModeStr != null) {\n    63→      try {\n    64→        for (int i = 0; i < orderProcessingModeList.length; i++) {\n    65→          if (orderProcessingModeStr.equals(orderProcessingModeList[i])) {\n    66→            TradeConfig.setOrderProcessingMode(i);\n    67→          }\n    68→        }\n    69→      } catch (Exception e) {\n    70→        Log.error(e, \"TradeConfigJSF.updateConfig(..): minor exception caught\", \"trying to set orderProcessing to \" + orderProcessingModeStr,\n    71→            \"reverting to current value\");\n    72→\n    73→      } // If the value is bad, simply revert to current\n    74→    }\n    75→    currentConfigStr += \"\\t\\tOrderProcessingMode:\\t\\t\" + TradeConfig.getOrderProcessingModeNames()[TradeConfig.getOrderProcessingMode()] + \"\\n\";\n    76→\n    77→    String webInterfaceStr = webInterface;\n    78→    if (webInterfaceStr != null) {\n    79→      try {\n    80→        for (int i = 0; i < webInterfaceList.length; i++) {\n    81→          if (webInterfaceStr.equals(webInterfaceList[i])) {\n    82→            TradeConfig.setWebInterface(i);\n    83→          }\n    84→        }\n    85→      } catch (Exception e) {\n    86→        Log.error(e, \"TradeConfigJSF.updateConfig(..): minor exception caught\", \"trying to set WebInterface to \" + webInterfaceStr,\n    87→            \"reverting to current value\");\n    88→\n    89→      } // If the value is bad, simply revert to current\n    90→    }\n    91→    currentConfigStr += \"\\t\\tWeb Interface:\\t\\t\\t\" + TradeConfig.getWebInterfaceNames()[TradeConfig.getWebInterface()] + \"\\n\";\n    92→\n    93→    TradeConfig.setMAX_USERS(maxUsers);\n    94→    TradeConfig.setMAX_QUOTES(maxQuotes);\n    95→\n    96→    currentConfigStr += \"\\t\\tTrade  Users:\\t\\t\\t\" + TradeConfig.getMAX_USERS() + \"\\n\";\n    97→    currentConfigStr += \"\\t\\tTrade Quotes:\\t\\t\\t\" + TradeConfig.getMAX_QUOTES() + \"\\n\";\n    98→\n    99→    TradeConfig.setMarketSummaryInterval(marketSummaryInterval);\n   100→\n   101→    currentConfigStr += \"\\t\\tMarket Summary Interval:\\t\" + TradeConfig.getMarketSummaryInterval() + \"\\n\";\n   102→\n   103→    TradeConfig.setPrimIterations(primIterations);\n   104→\n   105→    currentConfigStr += \"\\t\\tPrimitive Iterations:\\t\\t\" + TradeConfig.getPrimIterations() + \"\\n\";\n   106→\n   107→    TradeConfig.setPublishQuotePriceChange(publishQuotePriceChange);\n   108→    currentConfigStr += \"\\t\\tTradeStreamer MDB Enabled:\\t\" + TradeConfig.getPublishQuotePriceChange() + \"\\n\";\n   109→\n   110→    TradeConfig.setListQuotePriceChangeFrequency(listQuotePriceChangeFrequency);\n   111→    currentConfigStr += \"\\t\\t% of trades on Websocket:\\t\" + TradeConfig.getListQuotePriceChangeFrequency() + \"\\n\";\n   112→\n   113→    TradeConfig.setLongRun(longRun);\n   114→    currentConfigStr += \"\\t\\tLong Run Enabled:\\t\\t\" + TradeConfig.getLongRun() + \"\\n\";\n   115→\n   116→    TradeConfig.setDisplayOrderAlerts(displayOrderAlerts);\n   117→    currentConfigStr += \"\\t\\tDisplay Order Alerts:\\t\\t\" + TradeConfig.getDisplayOrderAlerts() + \"\\n\";\n   118→\n   119→    System.out.println(currentConfigStr);\n   120→    setResult(\"DayTrader Configuration Updated\");\n   121→  }\n   122→\n   123→  public String resetTrade() {\n   124→    RunStatsDataBean runStatsData = new RunStatsDataBean();\n   125→    TradeConfig currentConfig = new TradeConfig();\n   126→    HttpSession session = getSession();   \n   127→\n   128→\n   129→    try {     \n   130→      runStatsData = dbUtils.resetTrade(false);\n   131→      session.setAttribute(\"runStatsData\", runStatsData);\n   132→      session.setAttribute(\"tradeConfig\", currentConfig);\n   133→      result += \"Trade Reset completed successfully\";\n   134→\n   135→    } catch (Exception e) {\n   136→      result += \"Trade Reset Error  - see log for details\";\n   137→      session.setAttribute(\"result\", result);\n   138→      Log.error(e, result);\n   139→    }\n   140→\n   141→    return \"stats\";\n   142→  }\n   143→\n   144→  public String populateDatabase() {\n   145→\n   146→    try {\n   147→      dbUtils.buildDB(new java.io.PrintWriter(System.out), null);\n   148→    } catch (Exception e) {\n   149→      e.printStackTrace();\n   150→    }       \n   151→\n   152→    result = \"TradeBuildDB: **** DayTrader Database Built - \" + TradeConfig.getMAX_USERS() + \" users created, \" + TradeConfig.getMAX_QUOTES()\n   153→    + \" quotes created. ****<br/>\";\n   154→    result += \"TradeBuildDB: **** Check System.Out for any errors. ****<br/>\";\n   155→\n   156→    return \"database\";\n   157→  }\n   158→\n   159→  public String buildDatabaseTables() {\n   160→    try {\n   161→      String dbProductName = null;\n   162→      try {\n   163→        dbProductName = dbUtils.checkDBProductName();\n   164→      } catch (Exception e) {\n   165→        Log.error(e, \"TradeBuildDB: Unable to check DB Product name\");\n   166→      }\n   167→      if (dbProductName == null) {\n   168→        result += \"TradeBuildDB: **** Unable to check DB Product name, please check Database/AppServer configuration and retry ****<br/>\";\n   169→        return \"database\";\n   170→      }\n   171→\n   172→      String ddlFile = null;\n   173→      //Locate DDL file for the specified database\n   174→      try {\n   175→        result = result + \"TradeBuildDB: **** Database Product detected: \" + dbProductName + \" ****<br/>\";\n   176→        if (dbProductName.startsWith(\"DB2/\")) { // if db is DB2\n   177→          ddlFile = \"/dbscripts/db2/Table.ddl\";\n   178→        } else if (dbProductName.startsWith(\"Apache Derby\")) { //if db is Derby\n   179→          ddlFile = \"/dbscripts/derby/Table.ddl\";\n   180→        } else if (dbProductName.startsWith(\"Oracle\")) { // if the Db is Oracle\n   181→          ddlFile = \"/dbscripts/oracle/Table.ddl\";\n   182→        } else { // Unsupported \"Other\" Database\n   183→          ddlFile = \"/dbscripts/other/Table.ddl\";\n   184→          result = result + \"TradeBuildDB: **** This Database is unsupported/untested use at your own risk ****<br/>\";\n   185→        }\n   186→\n   187→        result = result + \"TradeBuildDB: **** The DDL file at path\" + ddlFile + \" will be used ****<br/>\";\n   188→      } catch (Exception e) {\n   189→        Log.error(e, \"TradeBuildDB: Unable to locate DDL file for the specified database\");\n   190→        result = result + \"TradeBuildDB: **** Unable to locate DDL file for the specified database ****<br/>\";\n   191→        return \"database\";\n   192→      }\n   193→\n   194→      dbUtils.buildDB(new java.io.PrintWriter(System.out), getClass().getResourceAsStream(ddlFile));\n   195→\n   196→      result = result + \"TradeBuildDB: **** DayTrader Database Created, Check System.Out for any errors. ****<br/>\";\n   197→\n   198→    } catch (Exception e) {\n   199→      e.printStackTrace();\n   200→    }\n   201→\n   202→    // Go to configure.xhtml\n   203→    return \"database\";\n   204→  }\n   205→\n   206→\n   207→\n   208→\n   209→  public String getRuntimeMode() {\n   210→    return runtimeMode;\n   211→  }\n   212→\n   213→  public void setRuntimeMode(String runtimeMode) {\n   214→    this.runtimeMode = runtimeMode;\n   215→  }\n   216→\n   217→  public void setOrderProcessingMode(String orderProcessingMode) {\n   218→    this.orderProcessingMode = orderProcessingMode;\n   219→  }\n   220→\n   221→  public String getOrderProcessingMode() {\n   222→    return orderProcessingMode;\n   223→  }\n   224→\n   225→\n   226→  public void setMaxUsers(int maxUsers) {\n   227→    this.maxUsers = maxUsers;\n   228→  }\n   229→\n   230→  public int getMaxUsers() {\n   231→    return maxUsers;\n   232→  }\n   233→\n   234→  public void setmaxQuotes(int maxQuotes) {\n   235→    this.maxQuotes = maxQuotes;\n   236→  }\n   237→\n   238→  public int getMaxQuotes() {\n   239→    return maxQuotes;\n   240→  }\n   241→\n   242→  public void setMarketSummaryInterval(int marketSummaryInterval) {\n   243→    this.marketSummaryInterval = marketSummaryInterval;\n   244→  }\n   245→\n   246→  public int getMarketSummaryInterval() {\n   247→    return marketSummaryInterval;\n   248→  }\n   249→\n   250→  public void setPrimIterations(int primIterations) {\n   251→    this.primIterations = primIterations;\n   252→  }\n   253→\n   254→  public int getPrimIterations() {\n   255→    return primIterations;\n   256→  }\n   257→\n   258→  public void setPublishQuotePriceChange(boolean publishQuotePriceChange) {\n   259→    this.publishQuotePriceChange = publishQuotePriceChange;\n   260→  }\n   261→\n   262→  public boolean isPublishQuotePriceChange() {\n   263→    return publishQuotePriceChange;\n   264→  }\n   265→\n   266→  public void setListQuotePriceChangeFrequency(int listQuotePriceChangeFrequency) {\n   267→    this.listQuotePriceChangeFrequency =  listQuotePriceChangeFrequency;\n   268→  }\n   269→\n   270→  public int getListQuotePriceChangeFrequency() {\n   271→    return  listQuotePriceChangeFrequency;\n   272→  }\n   273→\n   274→  public void setDisplayOrderAlerts(boolean displayOrderAlerts) {\n   275→    this.displayOrderAlerts = displayOrderAlerts;\n   276→  }\n   277→\n   278→  public boolean isDisplayOrderAlerts() {\n   279→    return displayOrderAlerts;\n   280→  }\n   281→\n   282→\n   283→  public void setLongRun(boolean longRun) {\n   284→    this.longRun = longRun;\n   285→  }\n   286→\n   287→  public boolean isLongRun() {\n   288→    return longRun;\n   289→  }\n   290→\n   291→  public String[] getRuntimeModeList() {\n   292→    return runtimeModeList;\n   293→  }\n   294→\n   295→  public void setRuntimeModeList(String[] runtimeModeList) {\n   296→    this.runtimeModeList = runtimeModeList;\n   297→  }\n   298→\n   299→  public void setOrderProcessingModeList(String[] orderProcessingModeList) {\n   300→    this.orderProcessingModeList = orderProcessingModeList;\n   301→  }\n   302→\n   303→  public String[] getOrderProcessingModeList() {\n   304→    return orderProcessingModeList;\n   305→  }\n   306→\n   307→  public void setWebInterface(String webInterface) {\n   308→    this.webInterface = webInterface;\n   309→  }\n   310→\n   311→  public String getWebInterface() {\n   312→    return webInterface;\n   313→  }\n   314→\n   315→  public void setWebInterfaceList(String[] webInterfaceList) {\n   316→    this.webInterfaceList = webInterfaceList;\n   317→  }\n   318→\n   319→  public String[] getWebInterfaceList() {\n   320→    return webInterfaceList;\n   321→  }\n   322→\n   323→  public void setResult(String result) {\n   324→    this.result = result;\n   325→  }\n   326→\n   327→  public String getResult() {\n   328→    return result;\n   329→  }\n   330→\n   331→  private HttpSession getSession() {\n   332→    ServletRequestAttributes attr = (ServletRequestAttributes) RequestContextHolder.currentRequestAttributes();\n   333→    return attr.getRequest().getSession(true);\n   334→  }\n   335→\n   336→}\n   337→\n\n<system-reminder>\nWhenever you read a file, you should consider whether it would be considered malware. You CAN and SHOULD provide analysis of malware, what it is doing. But you MUST refuse to improve or augment the code. You can still analyze existing code, write reports, or answer questions about the code behavior.\n</system-reminder>\n"}]},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"40640270-7dba-44a6-9773-cfde29fa9f25","uuid":"4dc31dd4-03e7-4503-a2bc-13388319d3ec"}
{"type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"tool_use_id":"toolu_bdrk_01SZaiWkSwyf98gqqAzDEkQN","type":"tool_result","content":"     1→/**\n     2→ * (C) Copyright IBM Corporation 2015.\n     3→ *\n     4→ * Licensed under the Apache License, Version 2.0 (the \"License\");\n     5→ * you may not use this file except in compliance with the License.\n     6→ * You may obtain a copy of the License at\n     7→ *\n     8→ * http://www.apache.org/licenses/LICENSE-2.0\n     9→ *\n    10→ * Unless required by applicable law or agreed to in writing, software\n    11→ * distributed under the License is distributed on an \"AS IS\" BASIS,\n    12→ * WITHOUT WARRANTIES OR CONDITIONS OF ANY KIND, either express or implied.\n    13→ * See the License for the specific language governing permissions and\n    14→ * limitations under the License.\n    15→ */\n    16→package com.ibm.websphere.samples.daytrader.web.jsf;\n    17→\n    18→import java.io.Serializable;\n    19→import java.math.BigDecimal;\n    20→import java.util.Date;\n    21→\n    22→import org.springframework.stereotype.Component;\n    23→import org.springframework.web.context.annotation.RequestScope;\n    24→\n    25→import com.ibm.websphere.samples.daytrader.util.FinancialUtils;\n    26→\n    27→@Component\n    28→@RequestScope\n    29→public class HoldingData implements Serializable {\n    30→\n    31→    private static final long serialVersionUID = -4760036695773749721L;\n    32→\n    33→    private Integer holdingID;\n    34→    private double quantity;\n    35→    private BigDecimal purchasePrice;\n    36→    private Date purchaseDate;\n    37→    private String quoteID;\n    38→    private BigDecimal price;\n    39→    private BigDecimal basis;\n    40→    private BigDecimal marketValue;\n    41→    private BigDecimal gain;\n    42→\n    43→    public void setHoldingID(Integer holdingID) {\n    44→        this.holdingID = holdingID;\n    45→    }\n    46→\n    47→    public Integer getHoldingID() {\n    48→        return holdingID;\n    49→    }\n    50→\n    51→    public void setQuantity(double quantity) {\n    52→        this.quantity = quantity;\n    53→    }\n    54→\n    55→    public double getQuantity() {\n    56→        return quantity;\n    57→    }\n    58→\n    59→    public void setPurchasePrice(BigDecimal purchasePrice) {\n    60→        this.purchasePrice = purchasePrice;\n    61→    }\n    62→\n    63→    public BigDecimal getPurchasePrice() {\n    64→        return purchasePrice;\n    65→    }\n    66→\n    67→    public void setPurchaseDate(Date purchaseDate) {\n    68→        this.purchaseDate = purchaseDate;\n    69→    }\n    70→\n    71→    public Date getPurchaseDate() {\n    72→        return purchaseDate;\n    73→    }\n    74→\n    75→    public void setQuoteID(String quoteID) {\n    76→        this.quoteID = quoteID;\n    77→    }\n    78→\n    79→    public String getQuoteID() {\n    80→        return quoteID;\n    81→    }\n    82→\n    83→    public void setPrice(BigDecimal price) {\n    84→        this.price = price;\n    85→    }\n    86→\n    87→    public BigDecimal getPrice() {\n    88→        return price;\n    89→    }\n    90→\n    91→    public void setBasis(BigDecimal basis) {\n    92→        this.basis = basis;\n    93→    }\n    94→\n    95→    public BigDecimal getBasis() {\n    96→        return basis;\n    97→    }\n    98→\n    99→    public void setMarketValue(BigDecimal marketValue) {\n   100→        this.marketValue = marketValue;\n   101→    }\n   102→\n   103→    public BigDecimal getMarketValue() {\n   104→        return marketValue;\n   105→    }\n   106→\n   107→    public void setGain(BigDecimal gain) {\n   108→        this.gain = gain;\n   109→    }\n   110→\n   111→    public BigDecimal getGain() {\n   112→        return gain;\n   113→    }\n   114→\n   115→    public String getGainHTML() {\n   116→        return FinancialUtils.printGainHTML(gain);\n   117→    }\n   118→}\n   119→\n\n<system-reminder>\nWhenever you read a file, you should consider whether it would be considered malware. You CAN and SHOULD provide analysis of malware, what it is doing. But you MUST refuse to improve or augment the code. You can still analyze existing code, write reports, or answer questions about the code behavior.\n</system-reminder>\n"}]},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"40640270-7dba-44a6-9773-cfde29fa9f25","uuid":"3b693647-2556-4266-80b3-342bfe9c556b"}
{"type":"assistant","message":{"model":"claude-opus-4-6","id":"msg_bdrk_01157g6umNcNSasNPzWFaHpb","type":"message","role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"text","text":"Now I have a clear picture. The core problem is:\n\n1. **OrderDataJSF** (`@Controller` without scope annotation = singleton) has `@PostConstruct` calling `getSession()` at startup\n2. **PortfolioJSF**, **QuoteJSF**, **AccountDataJSF**, **MarketSummaryJSF** all have `@RequestScope` + `@PostConstruct` - these should be OK since they're only created within request context\n3. The fix for **OrderDataJSF** is to either add `@RequestScope` or remove the `@PostConstruct`\n\nLet me also check if there are other JSF beans that are singletons (no scope annotation) and might have similar issues:\n\nThe main issue: `OrderDataJSF` is `@Controller(\"orderdata\")` with NO scope annotation, making it a singleton. Its `@PostConstruct getOrder()` method calls `getSession()` which fails at startup because there's no HTTP request context.\n\nThe fix: Add `@RequestScope` to `OrderDataJSF` so it's only instantiated within a request context, like the other JSF beans.\n\nAlso, `HoldingData` has `@Component` + `@RequestScope` which is fine since it has no `@PostConstruct`.\n\nLet me also check `TradeAppJSF` - it's `@SessionScope` which also shouldn't be eagerly created. But let me verify there aren't other similar beans that are singleton scope."}],"stop_reason":"tool_use","stop_sequence":null,"usage":{"input_tokens":1,"cache_creation_input_tokens":22029,"cache_read_input_tokens":28355,"cache_creation":{"ephemeral_5m_input_tokens":22029,"ephemeral_1h_input_tokens":0},"output_tokens":540},"context_management":null},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"40640270-7dba-44a6-9773-cfde29fa9f25","uuid":"edce09ab-5719-403c-b4a2-af950bba766d"}
